var DATA = {"Q48764447":{"lon":120.68722,"address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.02405,"date":"1982","locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the bust of Hilario which is located to the right of the main entrance of the capitol building.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zoilo J. Hilario historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Zoilo J. Hilario y Sangalang","subtitle":"1892–1963"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"975jfPampanga+Provincial Monuments Capitolfvf 08.JPG"},"name":"Zoilo J. Hilario y Sangalang"},"Q43301980":{"lon":120.99469,"lat":14.60431,"address":"National University, M. F. Jhocson Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1952","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"National University","inscription":"<p>The first private non-sectarian university in the Philippines. Founded, August 1, 1900, as Colegio Filipino by Mariano F. Jhocson. Renamed Colegio Mercantil, 1905; National Academy, 1916. Converted into a university, 1921. Camilo Osias, first president.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"National University"},"Q28922986":{"date":"2004","name":"Simbahang Inmaculada Concepcion ng Tamontaka","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Church of the Immaculate Conception of Tamontaka Seal.JPG","credit":"Erichmercado {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo ng mga paring Heswita sa pampang ng panlahatan sa ilog Tamontaka noong 1872 bilang bahagi ng misyong Tamontaka upang pangalagaan ang kapakanan ng mga kabataan at palaganapin ang ebanghelyo sa rehiyon ng Cotabato. Ipinatayo ang paaralan para sa mga kabataang lalaki sa pangangasiwa ng mga Heswita at paaralan para sa mga kabataang babae sa pangangalaga ng mga Beata ng San Ignacio (ngayo'y Religious of the Virgin Mary o RVM). Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1879 at naging sentro ng misyong Heswita. Nilisan ng mga paring Heswita, 1899 at inilagay sa pangangalaga ng mga Heswita ng Zamboanga. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring Oblates of Mary Immaculate at naging bahagi ng kanilang misyon sa Cotabato, 1939. Nasira ng lindol, 17 Agosto 1976. Muling itinayo,, 1978. Nasunog, 11 Mayo 1994, at isinaayos nang taon ding iyon. Ipinahayag ang pook na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 19 Hulyo 2004.</p>","title":"Simbahang Inmaculada Concepcion ng Tamontaka"}}},"address":"Tamontaka Church, Cotabato City","lat":7.18353,"lon":124.22226},"Q28871691":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng pagpapatibay ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan noong Setyembre 22,1977 na binigyan ng karapatan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo ng Pilipinas bilang 260, Agosto 1,1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Makasaysayang Simbahan ng San Joaquin"},"photo":{"file":"Simbahan ng San Joaquin historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"name":"Makasaysayang Simbahan ng San Joaquin","locPhoto":null,"date":"1980","lon":122.14091,"address":"San Joaquin Church, San Joaquin, Iloilo","lat":10.58593},"Q50881819":{"lon":122.86881,"lat":10.09638,"address":"Negros South Road, Himamaylan, Negros Occidental","date":"1993-05-17","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1843–1917)","inscription":"","title":"Pascual V. Ledesma"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pascual V. Ledesma"},"Q24702097":{"date":"1953","locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Lucena","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang parokya ng San Fernando noong 1 Marso 1881. Si Fr. Mariano Granja ang unang paroko. Ipinagawa ang simbahang ito noong Mayo 1882 at natapos noong Hulyo 1884. Nasunog noong 24 Mayo 1887. Muling ipinagawa noong Nobyembre 1887. Ang Diyosesis ng Lucena ay itinatag noong 8 Setyembre 1950.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Lucena","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"San Fernando Cathedral Lucena City Marker.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Lucena","lat":13.93592,"lon":121.61258},"Q44558486":{"lat":9.74014,"address":"Plaza Cuartel, Taft Street, Puerto Princesa","lon":118.72965,"date":true,"name":"Plaza Cuartel","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Plaza Cuartel.JPG"},"date":"2005","text":{"title":"Plaza Cuartel","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito na dating tanggulang militar noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig naganap ang pagsunog ng mga sundalong Hapon sa humigit kumulang 150 Amerikanong bihag ng digma noong 14 Disyembre 1944. Ilang nakaligtas ay lumangoy sa dagat patungong Iwahig. Ang mga labi ng mga nasawi ay dinala at inilibing sa St. Louis County sa isang panlahatang libingan sa Jefferson Barracks National Cemetery, Missouri, Estados Unidos, 1952.</p>","subtitle":null}},"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this site, once a military base during the Second World War, some 150 American prisoners of war were burned to death by Japanese soldiers, 14 December 1944. A few survivors swam to Iwahig. The remains of those who died were brought and interred in a common grave at the Jefferson Barracks National Cemetery, St. Louis County, Missouri, United States of America, 1952.</p>","title":"Plaza Cuartel","subtitle":null},"date":"2016-04-22"}}},"Q41998118":{"lon":120.86896,"address":"Marcelo H. del Pilar Shrine, Barangay San Nicolas Street, Bulakan, Bulacan","lat":14.79754,"date":"2012-01-17","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"JC Marcelo Shrine 16.JPG","credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Birthplace of Marcelo H. del Pilar"}}},"name":"Birthplace of Marcelo H. del Pilar","locPhoto":null},"Q35090763":{"address":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly Monument, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.19524,"lon":120.59263,"date":"1958","locPhoto":null,"name":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Government tobacco monopoly formally established March 1782 by Governor Jose Basco y Vargas by virtue of the Royal Decree of 9 February 1780. </p><p> While this monopoly increased government revenue and stimulated the tobacco industry, it led to many abuses by the government officials. </p><p> Abolished in 1882 by the Royal Decree of 25 June 1881 during the incumbency of Governor Fernando Primo de Rivera.</p><p> Erected by the people as an expression of joy over the abolition of the tobacco monopoly.</p>","title":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker of Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly Monument.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}}},"Q24061618":{"lon":120.98927,"address":"San Sebastian Church, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59961,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng San Sebastian"},"photo":{"file":"Historical marker of declaration of San Sebastian Church as a National Historical Landmark (corrected).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"San Sebastian Basilica main entrance.jpg"},"name":"Simbahan ng San Sebastian","date":"1976"},"Q24711215":{"date":"2004-11-26","locPhoto":null,"name":"Tulay Malagonlong","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ginawa noong 1840 sa ilalim ng pangagasiwa ng kura paroko ng Tayabas, si P. Antonio Mateos, at natapos noong 1850. Isa sa mga nalalabing tulay na bato sa bansa na ipinagawa sa panahon ng pananakop ng mga Espanyol.</p>","title":"Tulay Malagonlong","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Malagonlong Bridge Historical Marker.JPG"}}},"locDesc":null,"address":"Malagonlong Bridge, Tayabas, Quezon","lat":14.01312,"lon":121.61681},"Q51920412":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"WVSU historical marker.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"West Visayas State University","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"West Visayas State University","locPhoto":null,"date":"2007","lon":122.56277,"lat":10.71334,"address":"West Visayas State University, Luna Street, La Paz, Iloilo City"},"Q42931929":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical [Institute] 26 April 2007</p>","title":"Casa Narvas"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Casa Narvas","locPhoto":null,"date":"2007","lon":121.83949,"address":"Casa Narvas, Governor D. Reyes Street cor. Del Mundo Street, Boac, Marinduque","lat":13.44844},"Q36031375":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the extreme left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church of Malate historical marker 2.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This section of the city dates back to 1588. The titular patroness of this church is Nuestra Señora de los Remedios whose statue was brought from Spain in 1624 by Rev. Juan Guevara, O.S.A. The British landed their troops near these shores in 1762 and used the church of Malate for protection for their rear-guard in the capture of Manila. This church was greatly damaged by the earthquake of June 3, 1863 and was rebuilt by Rev. Francisco Cuadrado, O.S.A. The parish has been under the successive administration of the Augustinians, the secular clergy, the Redemptorists, and the Columbans.</p>","title":"Church of Malate"}}},"name":"Church of Malate","locPhoto":{"file":"Church of Malate historical marker vicinity.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":"1937","lon":120.98432,"address":"Malate Church, Marcelo H. del Pilar Street cor. Remedios Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.56921},"Q41217073":{"lon":120.59211,"lat":18.19448,"address":"Tupas Street, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","date":"1985","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1890–1972)","inscription":"","title":"Anastacia Giron-Tupas"},"photo":{"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Anastacia Giron Tupas Marker 1.JPG"}}},"name":"Anastacia Giron-Tupas","locPhoto":null},"Q31440688":{"lon":123.85593,"lat":9.63949,"address":"Tagbilaran Church, Tagbilaran, Bohol","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Tagbilaran Church Plaque.JPG","credit":"Malou Buenconsejo {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Church of Tagbilaran","inscription":"<p>One of the six parishes founded in Bohol by the Jesuit Missionaries, 1595. Turned over to the Recollects, 1768. Original church built by the Jesuits on this spot was burned, 23 December 1798. Reconstructed and enlarged by Fr. Valero de San Pascual, 1839-1855; Fr. Lucas Corominas built the convent, 1872; Fr. Jose Sancho the tower, 1884-1888. Father Escolastico Enciso improved the premises by placing iron cornices, tile flooring and chandeliers, 1884-1894.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Church of Tagbilaran","locPhoto":null,"date":"1953"},"Q37703111":{"date":"2006","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of an elongated monument of 8 soldiers charging in battle led by General Emilio Aguinaldo with the flag of the Philippines as backdrop.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Labanan sa Imus historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sinalakay ng puwersa nina Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo at Kor. Jose Tagle ang mga prayle at guardia civil na nanganlong sa Casa Hacienda 1 Setyembre 1896. Samantalong nakikipaglaban sa Bacoor si Hen. Aguinaldo at kanyang mga tauhan. Muling sinalakay ng mga rebolusyonaryong pinamumunuan ni Kor. Tagle ang Casa Hacienda 2 Setyembre 1896. Nagapi ang karagdagang puwersang Espanyol na pinamumunuan ni Hen. Ernesto de Aguirre, 3 Setyembre 1896. Sa labanang ito nahulog ang sable de mando ni Hen. de Aguirre na nakuha ng mga rebolusyonaryo. Nagsilbing inspirasyon ang tagumpay na ito sa mga rebolusyonaryo sa pakikipaglaban para sa kalayaan.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Imus"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Battle of Imus Monument.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Labanan sa Imus","lon":120.94027,"address":"Battle of Imus, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42996},"Q28942441":{"lat":7.22146,"address":"Tantawan Park, Sinsuat Avenue, Cotabato City","lon":124.24599,"date":"2004-12-19","name":"Sultan Dipatuan Kudarat","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Sultan Dipatuan Kudarat","inscription":"<p>Ikapitong Sultan ng Maguindanao. Kilala sa mga tala ng Espanyol bilang Corralat. Namuno mula 1619 hanggang 1671. Pinagbuklod ang mga pinunong Muslim at nakipagkaisa sa Sultanato ng Sulu. Lumaban sa mga Espanyol, 1635–1645. Naging tanging pinuno ng malawak na bahagi ng Mindanao kabilang ang Davao, Cotabato at Zamboanga. Nilagdaan ang kasunduang pangkapayapaan na nagbunga ng ilang taong katiwasayan sa Mindanao, 1645. Kinilala na walang takot na tagapagtanggol ng pananampalatayang Islam at umuusbong na kalayaan ng Pilipinas. Namatay, 1671.</p>","subtitle":"c. 1590–1671"},"photo":{"file":"Sultan Kudarat historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}}},"Q28923100":{"date":"2012","locPhoto":null,"name":"Fort Pikit","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Fort Pikit","inscription":"<p>Kabilang sa mga kutang ipinatayo ng Pamahalaang Espanyol upang sakupin ang Mindanao at magapi ang mga Morong patuloy na nagtaguyod ng kanilang kalayaan mula sa pamahalaang kolonyal, 1893. Ginamit ng mga sundalong Amerikano at Philippine Constabulary na binubuo ng mga Pilipinong Kristiyano at Muslim. Inokupahan ng mga puwersang Hapon, 1942-1945. Binawi ng puwersang Amerikano para sa pagpapalaya ng silangang bahagi ng Mindanao, Abril 1945. Naging himpilan ng Philippine Marine Corps hanggang 2005. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 24 Abril 2012.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"lat":7.06124,"address":"Fort Pikit, Pikit, Cotabato","lon":124.67795},"Q50385359":{"date":"1940","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly historical marker (corrected).jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly","inscription":"<p>The First Philippine Assembly was inaugurated here on October 16, 1907, by United States Secretary of War William Howard Taft in the presence of thousands of people, including Governor General James F. Smith, members of the Philippine Commission, Justices of the Supreme Court, representatives of foreign governments, officers of the United States Army and Navy, ecclesiastical dignitaries, and ranking officials of the insular, provincial, and municipal governments. Of the 80 duly elected delegates, 79 were present. The first Filipino bishop of Nueva Caceres, the Right Reverend Jorge Barlin, pronounced the invocation.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a marble pedestal to the right of the main entrance of the hotel.","locPhoto":{"file":"ManilaOperaHousejf7591 28.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly","lon":120.98166,"lat":14.60531,"address":"Manila Grand Opera Hotel & Casino, 925 Doroteo Jose Street cor. Rizal Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q35007957":{"lon":124.36982,"address":"Jagna Church, Jagna, Bohol","lat":9.65218,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Jagna","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Simbahan ng Jagna","locPhoto":null,"date":"2015"},"Q28912870":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dumaong sa dalampasigan ng bayang ito ang US 24th Corps, sa ilalim ni Maj. Gen. John R. Hodge, 20 Oktubre 1944, kasabay ng pagdaong sa Palo, Leyte ng 10th Corps bilang unang hakbang ng mga Amerikano sa pagbawi ng Pilipinas mula sa mga pwersang Hapones. Sa tulong ng mga gerilya ng 9th Military District sa pamumuno ni Col. Ruperto Kangleon, nabawi ang Dulag Airstrip. Nasagip ang limang daang sibilyan sa Lambak ng Leyte, at muling nabuksan ang San Juanico at Panaon Straits.</p>","title":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte","date":"2008","lon":125.03575,"lat":10.95269,"address":"Dulag, Leyte"},"Q43282748":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Liwasan ng Kalayaan"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Liwasan ng Kalayaan","locPhoto":null,"date":"1975-12-06","lon":121.83987,"address":"Mercader Street cor. 1 de Noviembre Street, Boac, Marinduque","lat":13.44778},"Q50562657":{"date":"2004-10-28","name":"Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres","inscription":""}}},"lat":9.30802,"address":"Rizal Avenue, Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","lon":123.30982},"Q30131050":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"fr":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896 Héros National des Philippines","inscription":"<p>[Rizal] vécut dans cette maison en 1883.</p>","title":"José Rizal"}}},"name":"José Rizal","locPhoto":null,"date":"1959","lon":2.32642,"address":"124 Rue de Rennes, 6th arrondissement of Paris, Paris, arrondissement of Paris, Île-de-France, France","lat":48.84667},"Q24058217":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Dasig.studio {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Bahay Nakpil-Bautista -National Historical Marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Ang Bahay ng mga Nakpil at Bautista","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Ariston Bautista Lin (1863–1928) at ng kanyang maybahay na si Petrona Nakpil sa pamamagitan ng kilalang arkitektong si Arcadio Arellano noong 1914.</p><p>Si Dr. Bautista ay isang manggagamot, pilantropo at imbentor ng isang gamot na panlaban sa kolera. Nanirahan din dito sina Julio Nakpil (1877–1960), rebolusyonaryo at konpositor ng mga awit ng Katipunan; kanyang asawang si Gregoria de Jesus (1876–1943), lakambini ng Katipunan at biyuda ni Andres Bonifacio; kanilang anak na si Juan (1899–1986) at pinsang buo nitong si Angel (1914–1979), na pawang mga tanyag na arkitekto.</p><p>Sa bahay ding ito ay dating katatagpuan ng Plateria Nakpil na dinadayo dahil sa mga masusing panindang mga alahas.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the house.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09626jfBautista Street Bahay Nakpil Bautista Ancestral House Quiapo Manilafvf 06.jpg"},"name":"Ang Bahay ng mga Nakpil at Bautista","date":"1995","lon":120.98465,"lat":14.59846,"address":"Nakpil–Bautista House, 432 Ariston Bautista Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q25079737":{"lat":14.27426,"address":"Maragondon, Cavite","lon":120.73702,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Where Bonifacio was Court-Martialled","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Where Bonifacio was Court-Martialled","inscription":"<p>In this house, erected in 1889, by its owner, Teodorico Reyes, Andres Bonifacio, founder of the Katipunan, was tried with his brother, Procopio, May 1897, by a court-martial headed by Brigadier-General Mariano Noriel. He was shot, May 10, 1897, at Mt. Buntis.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Bonifacio court-martial location historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1948"},"Q24836055":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Miguel Malvar","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Miguel Malvar historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1865–1911","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa baryo ng San Miguel, Santo Tomas, Batangas, noong Setyembre 27, 1865 sa mag-asawang Maximo Malvar at Tiburcia Carpio. Unang nag-aral sa paaralan ni Padre Valerio Malabanan. Naging Gobernadorsilyo ng Sto. Tomas noong 1892. Isa sa kauna-unahang sumapi sa Himagsikang Filipino laban sa mga Kastila noong 1896. Kahuli-hulihang Pilipinong Heneral na sumuko sa mga Amerikano noong Abril 18, 1902. Namatay noong Oktubre 13, 1911.</p>","title":"Miguel Malvar"}}},"date":"1973-09-27","lat":14.11027,"address":"Santo Tomas, Batangas","lon":121.1427},"Q41643044":{"lon":120.81257,"lat":14.84628,"address":"Barasoain Church, Paseo del Congreso cor. Don Antonio Bautista Street, Malolos, Bulacan","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the central main door of the church.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Barasoain","inscription":"<p>Barasoain was originally part of Malolos until its official separation on August 31, 1859. In 1903 it became part of Malolos again. The old Church constructed by Rev. Francisco Royo, O.S.A., was destroyed by fire in May, 1884, but rebuilt by Rev. Juan Giron, O.S.A., in 1885. This Church was the seat of the Revolutionary Congress which convened from the middle of September, 1898, to the last week of February, 1899, under the presidency of Pedro A. Paterno. Among the important measures passed by the Congress was the Malolos Constitution, drafted chiefly by Felipe G. Calderon.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Philippines Historical Committee Marker for Barasoain Church.JPG","credit":"Cool2compute {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}","file":"Historical markers on the facade of Barasoain Church.jpg"},"name":"Church of Barasoain","date":"1940"},"Q24733593":{"lon":120.92436,"lat":13.88042,"address":"Taal Basilica, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1575)","inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo ni Padre Diego Espina noong 1575 sa ngayon ay San Nicolas na dating bahagi ng Balangon. Nagiba noong 1754 nang pumutok ang bulkan. Ipinagawa sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan noong 1755 at iginuho ng lindol. Noong 1849, kinikilalang pinakamalaking simbahang Katoliko sa dakong silangan, ang kasalukuyang simbahan ay sinimulan noong 1756 ayon sa ibinalangkas ni Luciano Oliver, isang arkitektong. Pinasinayaan ito nooong 1865.</p>","title":"Ang Basilika ng Taal"},"photo":{"file":"Ang Basilika ng Taal historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located immediately to the left of the main door of the basilica.","locPhoto":{"file":"Taal, Batangas (50).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Ang Basilika ng Taal","date":"1986-12-08"},"Q24817240":{"lat":13.93814,"address":"Balayan, Batangas","lon":120.72936,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Galicano C. Apacible","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1864–1949)","inscription":"<p>Manggagamot, propagandista, diplomatiko, mambabatas at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Balayan, Batangas 24 Hunyo 1864. Kasama si Dr. Jose Rizal at iba pang mga mag-aaral na Filipino, itinatag sa Maynila ang El Compañerismo. Isang lihim na samahang pulitikal noong 1880. Isa sa mga nagtatag ng pahayagang propagandistang La Solidaridad noong 1889. Pangulo ng Asociacion Solidaridad Filipina sa Barcelona noong 1888 at ng komite sentral ng mga Filipino sa Hong Kong noong 1898. Tagapayo ng mataas na konseho ng mga rebolusyonaryong Filipino at kinatawan ng Republika ng Pilipinas sa Tsina, 1898-1899. Natatanging sugo sa Amerika at Europa, 1900-1901. Isa sa mga tagapagtatag ng Lapiang Nacionalista, 1906. Gobernador ng Batangas, 1908-1909; Kinatawan ng Batangas sa Asamblea ng Pilipinas, 1910-1916: Kalihim ng Pagsasaka at Likas na Yaman, 1917-1921. Yumao 22 Marso 1949.</p>","title":"Galicano C. Apacible"},"photo":{"file":"Galicano Apacible marker at his monument in Balayan,Batangas.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"2003"},"Q44640888":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Turtle Islands","locDesc":null,"details":{"text":{"tl":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang mga pulong ito ay pinaupahan ng Sultan ng Sulu sa British North Borneo Company noong 22 Enero 1878. Naging bahagi ng Pilipinas noong 10 Disyembre 1898 ayon sa Kasunduan ng Paris na nilagdaan ng Espanya at Estados Unidos. Patuloy na pinamahalaan ng British North Borneo Company ayon sa kasunduang nilagdaan noong 1932 ng Estados Unidos at Gran Bretanya. Pinagkayarian ding ibabalik sa may-ari pagkatapos mapagpatalastasan ang nangungupahan sa loob ng isang taon. Inilipat sa Republika ng Pilipinas noong 16 Oktubre 1947.</p>","title":"Turtle Islands"},"en":{"title":"Turtle Islands","inscription":"<p>These islets were leased by the Sultan of Sulu on 22 January 1878 to the British North Borneo Company. Became part of the Philippines by virtue of the Treaty of Paris, 10 December 1898, between Spain and the United States. Lessee continued administering them under the 1932 United States–Great Britain treaty to be relinquished to owner upon a year’s notice. Transferred to the Republic of the Philippines, 16 October 1947.</p>","subtitle":null}},"photo":null},"date":"1969","address":"Turtle Islands, Tawi-Tawi","lat":6.07322,"lon":118.31266},"Q24188594":{"date":"1939","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The Rt. Rev. Francisco C. Gainza, O.P., Bishop of Nueva Caceres (1862-1879), was the promoter and founder of this college named in honor of Saint Isabel, Queen of Hungary. It was solemnly blessed and opened September 18, 1870. By a royal decree of January 11, 1872, it became the first normal school for girls in the Philippines. During its existence from 1877 to 1898, three hundred students were graduated.</p>","title":"Colegio de Santa Isabel"},"photo":{"file":"Colegio de Santa Isabel historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem (schadow1) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Colegio de Santa Isabel","lon":123.18786,"address":"Universidad de Sta. Isabel, Elias Angeles Street, Naga, Camarines Sur","lat":13.62833},"Q24702138":{"date":"1982","locPhoto":null,"name":"Balangiga Massacre","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical marker at the foot of Valeriano Abanador statue.JPG","credit":"Jojit Ballesteros {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bayang ito, noong ika-28 ng Setyembre 1901, nilusob ng mga Pilipinong nasasandatahan ng gulok ang Kumpanya “C”, ika-9 na Impanteriya ng E.U. Napatay nila halos lahat ang lahat ng mga sundalong Amerikano. Bilang ganti ay naglunsad ang mga Amerikano ng may anim na buwang “pagpatay at pagsunog,” ang bayan ay nagmistulang “humahagulgol na kagubatan.” Dahil sa kanilang kalupitan, sina Brig. Hen. Jacob H. Smith at Medyor Littleton W. T. Waller ay nilitis ng hukumang militar at itiniwalag.</p>","title":"Balangiga Massacre","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"lat":11.10959,"address":"Balangiga, Eastern Samar","lon":125.3861},"Q43223320":{"lon":123.27756,"lat":13.46861,"address":"Bula, Camarines Sur","date":"1939","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The town dates from 1578. The first church was destroyed by fire in 1676. The second church, built in 1688, was destroyed by a typhoon in 1700. The present Church was completed in 1706 and repaired in 1876 and 1885.</p>","title":"Church of Bula"},"photo":{"file":"Church of Bula signage WTR.JPG","credit":"Yawrei {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Bula"},"Q45058955":{"lon":123.41629,"address":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lat":8.63917,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital","date":"2017-07-13"},"Q28933475":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Macapagal-Macaraeg Ancestral House","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute, 14 August 2002.</p>","title":"Macapagal-Macaraeg Ancestral House"},"photo":{"file":"Macapagal-Macaraeg House historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"date":"2002","lat":8.19101,"address":"Macapagal-Macaraeg House, Iligan","lon":124.17882},"Q24025942":{"lon":120.9887,"address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.5809,"date":"1998-02-17","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Memorare","inscription":"<p>The mortal remains of the three martyred priests, Fathers Jose A. Burgos, Mariano C. Gomes and Jacinto R. Zamora, were buried in this hallowed ground after their execution on 17 February 1872 for complicity in the Cavite Mutiny.</p><p>This marker was unveiled by His Excellency Fidel V. Ramos, President, Republic of the Philippines, February 17, 1998 on the occasion of the martyrdom of the three priests.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Carlo Joseph Moskito; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gomburza burial Memorare historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a cross memorial.","name":"Memorare","locPhoto":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GOMBURZA Burial Site.JPG"}},"Q35096799":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Katedral ng Talibon","inscription":"","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Katedral ng Talibon","locPhoto":null,"date":"2015","lon":124.32616,"lat":10.15097,"address":"Talibon Cathedral, Talibon, Bohol"},"Q41082784":{"date":"1968","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Pintong Sta. Lucia","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Pintong Sta. Lucia.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"name":"Pintong Sta. Lucia","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97365,"lat":14.58845,"address":"Sta. Lucia Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q30130266":{"lat":35.69686,"address":"The Kudan, Fujimi, Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo, Japan","lon":139.74881,"date":"2014-03-03","name":"Embahada ng Pilipinas","locPhoto":{"file":"The Kudan main gate (3).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the exterior wall of the security building beside the main gate of the residence.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Embahada ng Pilipinas historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"Fujimi, Chiyoda-Ku, Tokyo","inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 1 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 11 Marso 2013.</p>","title":"Embahada ng Pilipinas"}}}},"Q46880345":{"date":"2014-03-13","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo ang kapilya yari sa nipa nang gawing sentro ng pagmimisyon sa Panay ang Araut (ngayo’y Dumangas) ni Padre Juan de Alva, O.S.A., 1569. Ipinatayo ang simbahan at kumbento na yari sa bato sa patronato ni San Agustin, 1572. Nasunog, 1628. Muling ipinatayo ngunit nasira ng lindol, 1787. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 28 Agosto 1989.</p>","title":"Guho ng Kapilya ng Ermita"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Guho ng Kapilya ng Ermita","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.69477,"lat":10.817,"address":"Ermita Chapel, Dumangas, Iloilo"},"Q28942530":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa Bud Dajo","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Labanan sa pagitan ng mga Muslim at hukbong Amerikano mula 6 Marso hanggang 8 Marso 1906, bilang pagtutol ng mga Muslim sa pamamalakad at pagpataw ng buwis ng mga Amerikano. Nang matapos ang labanan, may isang libong mandirigmang Muslim ang napatay kabilang ang mga babae at bata samantalang 21 ang napatay sa panig ng mga Amerikano. Dito nagtapos ang serye ng mga labnana na nagsimula noong 1903 sa pamumuno ni Panglima Hassan, pagpapatunay ng pagmamahal ng mga Muslim sa kalayaan.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Bud Dajo"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2004","address":"Jolo, Sulu","lat":6.05122,"lon":121.01664},"Q41658841":{"lat":14.59102,"address":"General Luna Street cor. Beaterio Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97352,"locPhoto":{"file":"FvfIntramuros0485 15.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro"},"name":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council No. 1000","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council No. 1000","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang unang orden ng Knights of Columbus sa Maynila at tinawag na Manila Council No. 1000, 1905. Grand Knight Richard Campbell, unang pinuno. Antonio Opisso at Anastacio Quijano, unang mga Pilipino sa orden, 1907. Itinatag ng kasaping si Dr. Jose Ma. Delgado ang San Pablo Council No. 1900 sa Laguna, 1918. Sinimulan ng Manila Council No. 1000 ang pagbuo ng mga sangay sa lungsod ng Cebu, Albay, Laoag, Baguio, Lingayen, at Tacloban, dekada 1920. Lumaban para sa kalayaan at nasawi ang mga kasaping sina Benito Soliven, Manuel Colayco at Enrique Albert noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Itinuon ang mga gawaing pampamayanan sa pamumuno ni Rev. Fr. George Willmann S.J, 1947–1953 at ipinagtibay ang ganitong layunin nang mabuo ang “Patriotic Degree” ng orden, 1949. Binuo ang Columbian Farmers’ Aid Association, 1951. Ipinalaganap ang Credit Unions – Consumers’ Cooperatives Movement, 1963. Inilunsad ang Barrio Uplift Program, 1967.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council no. 1000 historical marker, Intramuros.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located by the eastern corner of the council building beside the side entrance facing the Manila Cathedral.","date":"2013"},"Q50385026":{"lat":14.60575,"address":"Manila Grand Opera Hotel & Casino, 925 Doroteo Jose Street cor. Rizal Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98188,"name":"The Manila Grand Opera House","locPhoto":{"file":"The Manila Grand Opera House historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the corner of the landscaping at the entrance of the hotel’s parking area.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Manila Grand Opera House historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"The Manila Grand Opera House","inscription":"<p>Erected on this site, and the scene of the inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly, was burned November 16, 1943. This new building was erected and inaugurated April 11, 1947.</p>"}}},"date":"1948"},"Q41105872":{"lon":120.71546,"lat":18.16616,"address":"Don Claro Caluya Green Garden, Estella Street, Piddig, Ilocos Norte","date":"1958","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Foremost vernacular poet and dramatist in Ilocos Norte. Born 22 June 1868. Son of Rafael Caluya and Norberta Pasion. Studied n his hometown; later went to a higher school in Laoag 1882; became Cabeza de Barangay, 1890 and Capitan Municipal, 1893-1896; Joined the Revolutionary Forces, 1896-1897; distinguished himself in the Filipino-American war; served as Municipal President of his town, 1903-1905. Under his administration, the first public market was built and several primary schools were opened. Founded civic and cultural organizations. Wrote many plays and poems in Ilocano, including a translation of Rizal's Ultimo Adios, which is considered as the most lyrical Ilocano version of the poem. Married to Sabina Aquino. Died 14 December 1914.</p>","title":"Claro Caluya"},"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Claro Caluya historical marker 2.jpg"}}},"name":"Claro Caluya","locPhoto":null},"Q46996608":{"lon":120.9842,"address":"Baywalk, Roxas Boulevard, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.56555,"date":"2017-12-08","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a pedestal on which a sculpture representing comfort women stands.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Comfort women Memorare historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Memorare","inscription":"<p>Ang bantayog na ito ay alaala sa mga Pilipinang naging biktima ng pang-aabuso sa Pilipinas noong panahon ng pananakop ng Hapon (1942–1945). Mahabang panahon ang lumipas bago sila tumestigo at nagbigay pahayag hinggil sa kanilang naranasan.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Memorare","locPhoto":{"file":"Memorare Comfort Women Statue and Historical Marker, Roxas Boulevard.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"Q28928492":{"name":"Taluksangay Mosque","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Taluksangay Mosque","inscription":"<p>Unang Mosque sa Peninsula ng Zamboanga na ipinatayo ni Hadji Abdullah Maas Nuno noong mga taong 1885. Ito ang unang sentrong Islam na kinilala ng ibang bansa tulad ng Turkey, Saudi Arabia, India, Malaysia, Indonesia at Borneo. Itinuturo dito ang mga tuntunin, kautusan at hurisprudensiya ng Islam na nagbunga ng mabilis na paglaganap ng Islam sa Peninsula ng Zamboanga, Basilan at kapuluan ng Sulu.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1992","lat":6.95075,"address":"Taluksangay Mosque, Zamboanga City","lon":122.18137},"Q24813802":{"date":"1941","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Ibaan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Church of Ibaan","inscription":"<p>In 1874 a chapel was built at Matala, but fire destroyed the convent in 1801. Constituted as a town in 1804, Ibaan had it's first church in 1817. In 1832, it was under Rev. Manuel Grijalbo, O.S.A., afterward Bishop of Nueva Caceres. Constructed by Rev. Manuel Diez Gonzales, O.S.A., in 1854, the present church was completed by Rev. Bruno Laredo, O.S.A., in 1869. Rev Vicente Maril, O.S.A., erected the towers and rebuilt the facade in 1876..</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Ibaan","lon":121.13267,"address":"Ibaan Church, Ibaan, Batangas","lat":13.81873},"Q23886446":{"lon":121.45618,"address":"Our Lady of Guadalupe Parish Church, Pagsanjan, Laguna","lat":14.27271,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker of Pagsanjan Church.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church of Pagsanjan","inscription":"<p>Founded, 1687. Father Agustin de la Magdalena, first curate. Original chapel of bamboo and nipa reconstructed, 1690, under the direction of Miguel Guan-co and Alguacil Mayor Alonso Garcia. Improved, 1853 by Fr. Joaquin de Coria. Transept added, 1872 by Fr. Serafin Linares and Fr. Cipriano Bac. Damaged during World War II.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Pagsanjan","date":"1953"},"Q28944815":{"address":"Balangiga Church, Balangiga, Eastern Samar","lat":11.10939,"lon":125.38564,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Balangiga","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Balangiga","inscription":"<p>Ipinagawang yari sa bato sa loob ng kutang patyo na may apat na baluarte ng mga paring Heswita noong mga ika-17 na dantaon sa patronato ni San Lorenzo. Muling ipinagawa ni P. Cristobal Miralles, 1653. Visita ng Guian, 1773. Ipinaayos ni P. Manuel Valverde, 1850. Naging isang bayan, Abril 3, 1854; parokya, Setyembre 27, 1859. Dito ang mag manghihimagsik ay nagtipon-tipon para hintayin ang pagtunog ng kampana na siyang hudyat sa pagsisimula ng pag-aaklas sa Balangiga laban sa mga Amerikano, Setyempre 28, 1901. Muling ipinagawa, 1927; inayos at pinaganda, 1962-1993.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Balangiga Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"date":"1993"},"Q45181046":{"date":"2017-12-01","name":"Molino Dam","locPhoto":{"file":"Molino Dam historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Molino Dam historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Molino Dam","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall facing the dam of the river station building on the Las Piñas end of the dam.","address":"Molino Dam, Florlina dela Cruz Street, Las Piñas, Metro Manila","lat":14.43859,"lon":120.97552},"Q23336728":{"lon":121.05996,"address":"People Power Monument, EDSA cor. White Plains Avenue, Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.60002,"date":"2011-02-25","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"EDSA People Power","inscription":"<p>Nagtipon ang libu-libong mamamayan bilang tugon sa panawagan ng Arsobispo ng Maynila, Jaime Cardinal Sin[,] upang bigyan proteksyon sina Juan Ponce Enrile, Ministro ng Tanggulang Pambansa; Ten. Heneral Fidel V. Ramos, pangalawang pinuno ng Hukbong Sandatahan ng Pilipinas at ang mga rebeldeng sundalong kabilang sa Reform the Armed Forces Movement, na tumiwalag sa administrasyon ni Pangulong Ferdinand E. Marcos at nagkanlong sa Kampo Crame at Aguinaldo, 22–25 Pebrero 1986. Nanumpa si Ginang Corazon C. Aquino bilang Pangulo ng Pilipinas sa Club Filipino, San Juan, Metro Manila, 25 Pebrero 1986. Kinagabihan ng araw ding iyon nilisan ng pamilyang Marcos ang Malacañang, kasama ang ilang tagasunod. Ito ang naging katapusan ng 20 taong rehimeng Marcos at kulminasyon ng mahabang panahong pakikibaka upang ibalik at pairaling muli ang demokrasya sa bansa.</p><p>Inalisan ng tabing ng Kagalang-galang na Pangulong Benigno S. Aquino, III, 25 Pebrero 2011 bilang paggunita sa ika-25 anibersaryo ng mapayapang People Power EDSA Revolution.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"EDSA People Power historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"EDSA People Power","locPhoto":null},"Q32093140":{"lon":120.96625,"lat":14.46388,"address":"Zapote Bridge, Aguinaldo Highway, Bacoor, Cavite","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a monument at the southern end of Zapote Bridge that is depicting General Edilberto Evangelista.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Zapote Battlefield","inscription":"<p>On this site the Filipino revolutionary forces fought two decisive battles: one against the Spanish forces, 17 February 1897, in which Filipino General Edilberto Evangelista was killed; the other, against the American forces, 13 June 1899, led by General H. W. Lawton, who later was killed in San Mateo, Rizal, by Filipino General Licerio Geronimo.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Zapote Battlefield historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zapote Battlefield Monument.jpg"},"name":"Zapote Battlefield","date":"1952"},"Q28861697":{"date":"1961","details":{"es":{"photo":{"file":"Quezon arch of the centuries.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Manuel L. Quezon","inscription":"<p>Primer Presidente de la Mancomunidad de Filipinas. Alumno de la Real y Pontificia Universidad de Santo Tomas, Manila, Filipinas, 1894–1898.</p>","subtitle":"1878–1944"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right post of the arch looking from España Boulevard.","name":"Manuel L. Quezon","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ms.popsie21 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Arch of the Centuries- University of Santo Tomas.jpg"},"lon":120.99086,"address":"Arch of the Centuries, España Boulevard, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.60844},"Q28937488":{"lon":125.623,"address":"Davao Prison and Penal Farm, Carmen, Davao del Norte","lat":7.41277,"date":"1956","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Established 21 January 1932 under Act 3732 of the Philippine Legislature on a site reserved by Proclamation no. 414 issued by Governor-General Dwight F. Davis on 7 October 1931; first penal colony founded under the administration of a Filipino Director of Prisons, Lt. Col. Paulino Santos. First superintendent, Pablo I. Norona, later assistant director of prisons. The official and prisoners of the colony were transferred by the Japanese forces to Iwahig Penal Colony, 8 November 1942; served as evacuation center for residents of Davao city during the early part of World War II; used as concentration camp for American prisoners of war; Colony was reopened 2 August 1946.</p>","title":"Davao Penal Colony","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Davao Penal Colony"},"Q35006081":{"address":"Inabanga Church, Inabanga, Bohol","lat":10.02882,"lon":124.0683,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Inabanga","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Inabanga","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Pablo Apostol, 1724. Winasak ng mga nag-alsang tagasunod ni Francisco Dagohoy ang simbahang yari sa bato, ika-18 siglo. Inilipat ang parokya sa pangangasiwa ng mga Rekoleto, 1768-1898. Sinimulang ipaayos ang apsis, 1889. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1899. Sinunog ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Enero 1902. Ipinagawa ang harapang bahagi ng simbahan sa panunungkulan ni Padre Quiterio Sarigumba, 1931; at ni Padre Valeriano Cabantan ang kampanaryo, 1940. Pinalitan ng bakal at tisa ang bubong, 2002. Nasira ng lindol, 15 Oktubre 2013.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2015"},"Q41743198":{"lon":120.97801,"address":"Lyceum of the Philippines University, Muralla Street cor. Real Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.592,"date":"1991","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1891–1959)","title":"Jose P. Laurel","inscription":""},"photo":{"file":"Jose P. Laurel (1891 - 1959).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jose P. Laurel"},"Q28912809":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Tanauan, Leyte","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Tanauan, Leyte","inscription":"<p>Constructed by the Jesuit Missionaries, 1704, and turned over to the Augustinians, 1768-1843. Repaired and enlarged 1850-1860 by Fr. Francisco de Paula Marquez who added a transept and surrounded the premises with thick rock-wall having a watch tower on each four corners for defense against pirates. Withstood hurricane and tidal wave of 1897.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Tanauan Church historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1949","address":"Tanauan Church, Tanauan, Leyte","lat":11.11273,"lon":125.01739},"Q24068225":{"lon":120.36743,"address":"Agoo Basilica, MacArthur Highway cor. Cases Boulevard, Agoo, La Union","lat":16.32294,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right-side wall of the recessed main entrance of the basilica.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity","inscription":"<p>Located in La Union's oldest town, Agoo. Parish and town founded in 1578 by Franciscan Frs. Juan Bautista Lucarelli and Sebastian de Baeza. Original church in Barangay Nagrugcan. Improved by Augustinian Fr. Saturnino Franco; Belfry built by Frs. Casimiro Melgosa and Aquilino Garcia. All destroyed by 1892 earthquake. </p><p> Built on this site was the next church where the long-venerated image of Our Lady of Charity was canonically crowned by Apostolic Nuncio Salvatore Sinno on 1 May 1971 by rescript of Pope Paul VI. Demolished in 1975 for a new shrine. Cornerstone laid on 8 Sept. 1975, feast of Our Lady's Nativity, by Archbishop Mariano A. Madriaga, native of the town. Construction started 8 Jan. 1976 from donations by the faithful led by a son of the town, Tourism minister Jose D. Aspiras and his family and encouragement of Bishop Victorino Ligot of San Fernando de La Union Diocese.</p><p>Consecrated Marian shrine on 8 Dec. 1978, feast of the Immaculate Conception by Sebastiano Cardinal Baggio, Prefect of the Sacred Congregation of Bishops, with President Ferdinand E. Marcos and first lady Imelda Romualdez Marcos in Attendance. </p><p>Elevated to rank of Basilica Minore by Pope John Paul II, on 15 July 1982, on petition of Bishop Salvador Lazo through Archbishop Bruno Torpigliani, Apostolic Nuncio to the Philipines. Dedicated as such by Sebastiano Cardinal Baggio on 8 Dec. 1982. </p><p>Msgr. Benito P. Sison, first rector; Msgr. Jose G. Tongson, present rector; Tomas M. Asprer, provincial governor; Jose Luis M. Aspiras, municipal mayor; Ignacio Palma Bautista, architect; Bernardo M. Vergara, Edmundo Tolentino, Jose Manantan and Bernabe Corpuz, supervising engineers.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Agoo Basilica entrance.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"name":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity","date":"1982"},"Q28912789":{"date":"1950","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944-1945 historical marker.jpg","credit":"John Martin PERRY {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>On the steps of this Capitol Building of Leyte was formally installed, 23 October 1944, Sergio Osmeña as President of the Commonwealth of the Philippines by Gen. Douglas Mac Arthur in the presence of Cabinet men, Liberation Forces and many other grateful people. Henceforth, until 27 February 1945, this edifice served as the Capitol of the Philippines.</p>","title":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944–1945","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944–1945","lon":125.00359,"address":"Leyte Provincial Capitol, Tacloban","lat":11.25056},"Q29018404":{"name":"Simbahan ng Capul","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker of Capul Church, Northern Samar.JPG","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Capul","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Paring Heswita bilang Misyon, 1596. Ipinatayo yari sa nipa at kahoy ang unang simbahan sa patronato ni San Ignacio de Loyola; muling ipinatayo kasabay ang kuta na yari sa bato bilang tanggulan laban sa mga mandirigmang Moro ca. 1600. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1768. Ipinaayos ni Padre Mariano Valero ang simbahan at ipinatayo ang kampanaryo, 1781. Itinalaga ng obispo ng Cebu bilang parokya, 8 Nobyembre 1864. Isinagawa ang lagusan ng kuta sa kanang bahagi ng simbahan, 1898. Pangunahing halimbawa ng simbahang tanggulan noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2011","lat":12.4228,"address":"Capul Church, Capul, Northern Samar","lon":124.18232},"Q22340895":{"date":"1988","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Pakil","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"TurumbaChurchjf6544 18.JPG"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the bell tower which is to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pakil Church in Laguna historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa kawayan at nipa ni Padre Francisco Barajas sa patronato ni San Pedro de Alcantara nang ang Pakil ay mahiwalay sa Paete, 1676. Ipinagawa ang kumbento at simbahang bato ni Padre Fernando Haro, 1732. Dinugtungan ang tore, 1777; Idinambana ang Birhen ng Turumba, 1788; Nasunog na muli, 1851 at ipinaayos ni Padre Juan de Llarena. Nasira ng lindol ang tore at bubong ng simbahan, 1881 at pinaayos ni Padre Juan de Dios de Villayos. Inilagay ang kisame at pinadorado ang altar ni Padre Paulino Camba, 1883. Sinirang muli ng lindol, 1937 at pinaayos ni Padre Federico Diaz Pines sa tulong ng Kapisanang Unidad Catolica. Ginawang marmol ang altar ni Padre Joseph Reagan at kinonsagrahan ang altar ni Obispo Alejandro Olaila, 1959. Pinaayos ang tore at kisame sa pamamahala ng Parish Council of the Laity, 1980-84.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Pakil"}}},"address":"Pakil Church, Pakil, Laguna","lat":14.38083,"lon":121.47891},"Q52024197":{"lon":121.07639,"lat":14.55983,"address":"Colegio del Buen Consejo, A. Luna Street cor. R. Jabson Street, Pasig, Metro Manila","date":"1937","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This College was founded in 1740 by Rev. Felix Trillo, O.S.A. with the assistance of Pedro and Rita Quijano, for the education of girls. The building was occupied by the British after the expulsion of the Spanish forces. It was greatly damaged by the earthquakes of 1880.</p>","title":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas"}}},"name":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas","locPhoto":null},"Q24702203":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Tayabas","inscription":"<p>Ang unang simbahan na yari sa kawayan, nipa at anahaw ay ipinatayo ng mga prayleng Pransiskano noong 1585 sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel. Ito ay muling ipinaayos ni san Juan Bautista noong 1590. Noong 1600 isang simbahang yari sa tisa ang ipinatayo subalit ito ay giniba ng lindol noong 1743. Nang sumunod na mga taon ang simbahan ay muling ipinagawa at pinalakihan. Ito ay higit pang pinalaki noong 1856 sa pamamagitan ng pagpapagawa ng transepto at kupola. Ang bubong na tisa ng transepto ay pinalitan ng gabanisadong yero noong 1894. Ang simbahang ito ay isa sa pinakamagandang simbahan sa Pilipinas.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tayabas Basilica Historical Marker.JPG"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Tayabas","date":"1978","lon":121.59105,"address":"Tayabas Basilica, Tayabas, Quezon","lat":14.02583},"Q30097887":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1898–1980)","title":"Lazaro Francisco","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, pangunahing nobelista sa Panitikang Pilipino. Isinilang sa Orani, Bataan, Pebrero 22, 1898. Lumaki sa Cabanatuan at nagsulat ng nobela sa bayang ito mula 1925. Mahalagang bahagi ng kanyang panulat ang pakikisangkot sa mga suliraning tumutukoy sa kapakanan ng bansa. Tagapagtatag ng Kapatiran ng mga Alagad ng Wikang Pilipino (KAWIKA), 1958. Tampok sa mga tinanggap niyang gawad: Republic Cultural Heritage Award, 1970; Patnubay ng Kalinangan, Maynila, 1975; Dangal ng Lahi, Lungsod ng Quezon, 1976; Tanglaw ng Lahi, Ateneo de Manila, 1979. Sa kanyang alaala ang Cabanatuan West Central School ay pinangalanan noong 1987 ng \"Paaralang Elementaryang Lazaro Francisco.\" Namatay noong Hunyo 17, 1980.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Lazaro Francisco historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Lazaro Francisco","date":"1990","lon":120.95902,"lat":15.48652,"address":"Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija"},"Q28871785":{"lat":10.64178,"address":"Miagao Church, Miagao, Iloilo","lon":122.23529,"date":"1976","name":"Simbahan ng Miag-ao","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1,1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Miag-ao","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Miagao Church historical marker 2.JPG"}}}},"Q40314993":{"date":"1934","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Built of Guadalupe Volcanic Tuff By Governor Gomez Perez Dasmariñas 1590–1593 In Place of the Wooden Palisade of Raja Matanda</p>","title":"Fort Santiago","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker Fort Santiago.jpg"}}},"name":"Fort Santiago","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97176,"lat":14.59269,"address":"Fort Santiago, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q28927631":{"lon":121.92189,"lat":6.99399,"address":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm, Zamboanga City","date":"2014","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm","inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa patronato ni San Ramon Nonato Colonia Penitenciaria Agricola upang palawakin ang agrikultura sa paggawa ng mga bilangong manggagawa, 31 Agosto 1870. Piitan ng mga nahatulang kalaban ng pamahalaang Espanyol. Kalauna’y dito itinapon ang mga nagkasalang Kristiyano at Muslim. Nasunog ang mga gusali sa labanan ng Pilipino at Espanyol, 1899. Ipinagpatuloy ng mga Amerikano ang pamamahala dito, 1901. Pinamunuan ng Moro Province, 1911, ng Department of Mindanao and Sulu, 1914, at ng Bureau of Prisons, 1915. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang piitan noong ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig. Isa sa mga unang kolonyang penal sa bansa.</p>"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm","locPhoto":null},"Q24188864":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The early church dedicated to \"Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia \" was built about 1711 trough the generosity of the Rev. Miguel de Covarrubias as a vow-offering for blessings he received in his youth. The present church was built about 1750 by Bishop Isidoro de Arevalo and repaired and improved in 1876-1877 by Bishop Francisco Gainza. The image was solemnly crowned by the Rt. Rev. Guillermo Piani on September 20, 1924.</p>","title":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia"},"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker of Peñafrancia Shrine.jpg"}}},"date":"1940","lat":13.6342,"address":"Our Lady of Peñafrancia Shrine, Naga, Camarines Sur","lon":123.19545},"Q28855130":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 1 dated March 8, 1994 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","title":"Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"date":"1994","lat":10.80005,"address":"Balay Negrense, Silay, Negros Occidental","lon":122.97316},"Q28912601":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Liwasan ng Dapitan historical marker 08.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinaayos ayon sa plano ni Jose Rizal habang nakadistiyero sa Dapitan, 1892-1896. May limang landas patungo sa kiyoskong kinatatayuan ngayon ng bantayog ng pambansang bayani. Itinanim ni Rizal ang mga punong akasya sa liwasan. Ipinagkaoob niya ang sistemang pangliwanag na gumagamit ng langis ng niyog mula sa bayao ng isang pasyenteng Ingles. Binuo ni Rizal at ng kanyang dating guro P. Francisco de Padua Sanchez, S.J., ang mapa ng Mindanao, sa tulong ng mga tauhan ng simbahan at ng mga mag-aaral ng paaralang parokyal ng Dapitan, 1892. Inayos ang mapa noong panahon ni Jose Aseniero, dating mag-aaral ni Rizal, Gobernador ng Zamboanga, 1925-1928. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Marso 2002 at ang mapa ng Mindanao bilang isang Yamang Pangkalinangan ng Pambansang Museo, 20 Hunyo 2005.</p>","title":"Liwasan ng Dapitan","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Liwasan ng Dapitan","locPhoto":null,"date":"2003","lon":123.42409,"lat":8.65493,"address":"City Hall Drive, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte"},"Q24702174":{"date":"1939","locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Atimonan","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first Church here and the town were burned by the Dutch in 1640. The second Church, built of stone in 1643, was partially destroyed by fire in 1648. The third Church, rebuilt in 1650, likewise was destroyed by earthquakes. The present Church and the Convent were constructed between 1687 and 1700, but were seriously damaged by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>","title":"Church of Atimonan"},"photo":{"file":"Our Lady of the Angels Parish Marker in Atimonan, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Atimonan Church, Quezon Street, Atimonan, Quezon","lat":14.00164,"lon":121.92139},"Q24702362":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Quezon Provincial Capitol","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Quezon Provincial Capitol Marker.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating Tayabas capitol na ipinatayo sa loteng ipinagkaloob ni abogado Filemon E. Perez noong 1908. Ginawang kongkreto batay sa balangkas at detalye ng kasangguning arkitekto ayon sa itinakda ng Public Act 1637, April 30, 1907. Binago at pinalaki noong 1930 sa panunungkulan ni Governador Leon G. Guinto at tinapos noong 1935 sa panunungkulan ni Governador Maximo Rodriguez. Nasira noong ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig at ipinaayos sa pamamagitan ng U.S. Philippine Rehabilitation (Tydings) Act, April 30, 1946. Pinangalanang Quezon Provincial Capitol sa bisa ng Republic Act No. 14 September 7, 1946, na nagpalit sa pangalan ng lalawigang Tayabas ng Quezon.</p>","title":"Quezon Provincial Capitol"}}},"date":"1987-08-17","address":"Lucena","lat":13.9285,"lon":121.61317},"Q24817360":{"address":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House, 3 Calle Jose P. Rizal, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.87814,"lon":120.92475,"locPhoto":{"file":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House main entrance.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Ylagan-de la Rosa Ancestral House historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This heritage house of the Ylagan–de la Rosa family is registered with the National Historical Institute, pursuant to NHI Board Resolution No. 9 S. 1998.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the house.","date":"1999-05-30"},"Q47092288":{"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.02476,"lon":120.68763,"date":"2009","locPhoto":{"file":"08685jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 08.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"name":"Jose Abad Santos","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of José Abad Santos.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1886–1942)","title":"Jose Abad Santos","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"08685jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 01.jpg"}}}},"Q48649068":{"lon":120.58669,"lat":16.4245,"address":"Easter College, Baguio","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang Easter School ni Charles Henry Brent, obispo ng Simbahang Episkopal upang mabigyan ng pormal ma edukasyon ang mga batang lalaki mula sa Mountain Province, 1906. Tumanggap ng mga babaeng mag-aaral, 1909. Sa pagsisikap ni Dyakonesa Anne Hargreaves itinatag ang pagsasanay sa paghahabi ng tela para sa mga babaeng mag-aaral. Nagsilbing himpilan ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Idinagdag ang sekondaryang edukasyon, 1963. Naging Easter College, 1995.</p>","title":"Easter College"},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Easter College","date":"2017-12-12"},"Q43442579":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1893–1934)","inscription":"","title":"Nicanor Abelardo at Sta. Ana"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Nicanor Abelardo at Sta. Ana","locPhoto":null,"date":"1963-06-20","lon":120.97562,"lat":15.14055,"address":"Payawal Street, San Miguel, Bulacan"},"Q24702224":{"address":"Manuel Quezon Avenue, Lucena","lat":13.93581,"lon":121.61311,"date":"1952","locPhoto":null,"name":"Lucena","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lucena","inscription":"<p>Dating nayon ng Tayabas na sunod-sunod na pinangalanang Buenavista, Oroquieta at Cotta bago tinawag na bayang Lucena, 1 Hunyo 1882, na siyang pangalan ng bayang sinilangan sa Espanya ni P. Mariano Granja, unang paroko. Faustino Enriquez, unang punong-bayan.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Lucena historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q43276986":{"lon":121.84153,"lat":13.44676,"address":"Boac Municipal Hall, Boac, Marinduque","date":"1982-05-24","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Salvador del Mundo"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Salvador del Mundo"},"Q24708066":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall between the main and eastern front doors of the church.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ang unang simbahan ni P. Diego Mojica, pastor na Augustino ng Calapan, Mindoro, noong 1581 at inialay sa Immaculada Concepcion de Nuestra Señora bilang parokya. Inilagay noong 1601 ang pundasyong bato ng ikalawang simbahan na ipinagawa ng mga pari noong 1682-1721. Idinagdag noong 1693 ang kumbentong may artileriya upang maitaboy ang mga tulisang-dagat. Giniba pagkaraan ng 179 na taon at muling ipinatayo ni P. Pedro Cuesta noong 1851. Binasbasan noong Pebrero 2, 1857, itinalaga bilang Basilika Menor noong Pebrero 13, 1948 at nagdiwang ng ikasandaang taon noong 1957.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Batangas Basilica historical marker location.jpg"},"name":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion","date":"1984-01-15","lon":121.05922,"lat":13.75434,"address":"Minor Basilica of the Immaculate Conception, M.H. del Pilar Street cor. Natividad Street, Batangas City, Batangas"},"Q40176443":{"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","lat":14.44516,"lon":120.90692,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo:Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1849","title":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo","inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito, na itinayo noong 1849, ipinanganak si Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo noong Marso 22, 1869. Sa durungawang nakaharap sa daan ipinahayag ni Aguinaldo ang kasarinlan ng Pilipinas noong Hunyo 12, 1898. Ipinagkaloob ang bahay sa Pamahalaang Pilipino bilang alaala sa mga nakihamok upang makamtan ang kalayaan. Inilibing siya sa loteng kinatatayuan ng bahay noong Pebrero 16, 1964.</p>"}}},"date":"1971"},"Q28865328":{"date":"1953","name":"Pagsanjan","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Formerly a barrio of Lumbang. Organized into a municipality, 1668. Francisco Umali, first Gobernadorcillo. Became capital of Laguna, 1688-1858. Town Gate constructed, 1878-1880. Inaugurated, 1984, by Don Pedro A. Paterno. Occupied by the Revolutionists, 1896; by the Americans, 1899; by the Japanese, 1942. Liberated, 1945, by the Filipinos</p>","title":"Pagsanjan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker of Pagsanjan.jpg"}}},"address":"Pagsanjan Arch, J. P. Rizal Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna","lat":14.27328,"lon":121.44906},"Q41645242":{"date":"1976","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Barasoain","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Simbahan ng Barasoain historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the southern main door of the church.","locPhoto":{"file":"Historical markers on the facade of Barasoain Church.jpg","credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}"},"name":"Simbahan ng Barasoain","lon":120.81255,"address":"Barasoain Church, Paseo del Congreso cor. Don Antonio Bautista Street, Malolos, Bulacan","lat":14.84623},"Q28864749":{"date":"1956","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker of Pagsanjan Municipal Building.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Originally constructed in the middle of the nineteenth century and housed the \"Tribunal del Gremio de Naturales\"; Occupied by the Filipino Revolutionary Forces in 1898 and by the American Expeditionary Forces in 1899-1903; Served as the first public high school in Laguna 1903-1907; housed the municipal elementary school until 1911; later became the seat of the Municipal Government. Destroyed on 20 March 1945; Rehabilitated and reconstructed in 1951 and completed in 1955.</p>","title":"Pagsanjan Municipal Building"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pagsanjan Municipal Building","lon":121.45581,"lat":14.27255,"address":"Pagsanjan Municipal Hall, J. P. Rizal Street cor. Gen. Taino Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna"},"Q46571641":{"date":"1992","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Altavas"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Altavas","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.48759,"lat":11.53837,"address":"Altavas Municipal Hall, Altavas, Aklan"},"Q52144815":{"address":"Pan-Philippine Highway cor. Recto Mayo Street, Tiaong, Quezon","lat":13.95873,"lon":121.32446,"date":"1984-02-08","name":"Claro Recto y Mayo","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"CMRectoTiaongjf0271 19.JPG"},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Claro Recto y Mayo","inscription":"","subtitle":"(1890–1960)"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Claro M. Recto historical marker in Tiaong, Quezon.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal several meters in front of the monument to Recto."},"Q24068386":{"address":"Cathedral of St. William the Hermit, San Fernando, La Union","lat":16.61665,"lon":120.3168,"date":"1949","name":"Church of San Fernando, La Union","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"San Fernando, La Union historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Chapel made of stone and thatch erected, 1764 by Fr. Francisco Romero and Santiago Holarte at Barrio San Vicente formerly known as Pindangan after which San Fernando was first called. Moved to Tanque, then to Kabaroan, and afterwards to its present site where it was built of stone and brick by Fr. Juan Sorolla, Simon Guillermo and Pedro Fernando, 1773-1786. Damaged by earthquake, 1892. Occupied by the revolutionists under Col. Blas Villamor, 1898, when they overwhelmed the Spanish forces that sought shelter therein. Destroyed during the liberation, 26 February 1945. Reconstructed by the residents through the efforts of Bishop Santiago C. Sancho, 1947-1949. Rededicated, 10 February 1949.</p>","title":"Church of San Fernando, La Union"}}}},"Q46519998":{"lon":123.71245,"lat":13.15,"address":"Daraga Church, Santa Maria Street, Daraga, Albay","date":"2008-10-16","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Daraga","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Pransiskano na yari sa bato, 1773. Dito lumipat ang mga mananampalataya ng Cagsawa matapos masira ang kanilang simbahan sa pagsabog ng Mayon, 1814. Inialay sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora de la Porteria, 1854. Ginamit na himpilan ng mga Hapones at nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1945. Muling ipinaayos, 1971–1973. Halimbawa ng istilong Baroque ayon sa kahusayan ng mga manggagawang Filipino noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Simbahan ng Daraga.JPG"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Daraga"},"Q24702093":{"lon":121.52397,"lat":13.96347,"address":"Sariaya Church, General Luna Street, Sariaya, Quezon","date":"1938","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church at the base of the bell tower.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first church dates from 1599. The second church, built in 1605, was replaced by a third in 1641. In 1703 the town was transferred to Lumangbayan, but the earthquakes and floods of 1743 destroyed the church and the town and caused the people to transfer to the present site. The present church was built in 1748.</p>","title":"Church of Sariaya"},"photo":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sariaya Church Historical Marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Sariaya historical marker vicinity.jpg"},"name":"Church of Sariaya"},"Q36172767":{"lat":14.59888,"address":"San Fernando Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97238,"date":"2014","name":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito namatay si Teodora Alonso, ina ni Jose Rizal, noong 16 Agosto 1911.</p>"}}}},"Q43222507":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum.jpg","credit":"Free2barredo {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Philtranco Service Enterprises, Inc.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Philtranco Service Enterprises, Inc.","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ringer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Philtranco Marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the entrance to the Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum.","date":"2000","lat":13.42681,"address":"Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum, Iriga–Baao Road, Iriga, Camarines Sur","lon":123.41653},"Q52021836":{"date":null,"name":"Tumira Dito si Claro Mayo Recto","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1890–1960)","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, estadista, hurista, parlamentaryo at manunulat kung saan ginugol ang pinakamahulugang bahagi ng kanyang buhay na naging huwaran ng kadakilaan, karangalan at pagpipitagan sa sariling kakayahan ng sambayanang Pilipino.</p>","title":"Tumira Dito si Claro Mayo Recto"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.5588,"address":"Leveriza Street cor. Fresno Street, Pasay, Metro Manila","lon":120.99332},"Q24702612":{"name":"Kutang San Diego","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Kutang San Diego Marker Gumaca, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Yari sa tinabtab na bato at may bubong na tisa, ang kutang ito ang tanging nalalabi sa ipinatayo ng mga Kastila sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring Pransiskano noong huling bahagi ng ika-18 siglo upang ipagtanggol ang bayan laban sa pagsalakay ng mga tulisang-dagat. Sa pagitan ng dalawang moog, si P. Francisco Costa ay nagpatayo noong 1850 ng matibay na pader na yari sa apog at bato upang ipangsanggalang ang bayan buhay sa hanging mula sa hilagang-silangan.</p>","title":"Kutang San Diego","subtitle":"Gumaca, Quezon"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1981-03-17","lat":13.92294,"address":"Lakan Bugtali Boulevard, Gumaca, Quezon","lon":122.10028},"Q28919864":{"lon":123.84671,"lat":8.14045,"address":"Fort of the Conception and Triumph, Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Fuerte de la Concepcion y del Triunfo","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa korales sa hugis-parihaba na may apat na balwarte: San Fernando, San Jose, Santigo at San Ignacio, 1756. Punong Himpilan ng Konstabularya ng Pilipinas noong Panahon ng mga Amerikano at mga Hapon. Giniba ng lindol, 1955. Dito idinambana ang Inmaculada Concepcion na kilala rin sa tawag na Santa Mariang Birhen, Virgen sa Cota, na pinagpipitaganan at dinadayo ng mga deboto tuwing Hulyo 16. Isinaayos, 2002. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Panandang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Marso 2002.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Fuerte De La Concepcion Y Del Triunfo historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Fuerte de la Concepcion y del Triunfo","date":"2002"},"Q43302121":{"address":"Kapitan Moy Residence, J. P. Rizal Street cor. Deguangco Street, Marikina, Metro Manila","lat":14.63071,"lon":121.09568,"name":"Unang Pagawaan ng Sapatos sa Marikina","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Marikina First Shoe Factory historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito, na naging paaralan, ipinanganak si Laureano Guevara (Kapitan Moy), pangunahing manggagawa ng sapatos sa Marikina. Anak nina Jose Emiterio Guevara at Matea Mariquita Andres, nagsimulang gumawa ng sapatos nang mga huling araw ng taong 1887 sa tulong nina Tiburcio Eustaquio, Ambrosio Santa Ines, Gervasio Carlos, at iba pa. Nakatuklas sila ng mga wastong pamamaraan sa paggawa ng sapatos. Ang kanilang patuloy na pananagumpay sa gawaing ito ang nagbunsod sa kapulungang-bayan na magpatibay ng isang resolusyon noong Hulyo 2, 1968 upang gawing isang museo ang bahay na ito.</p>","title":"Unang Pagawaan ng Sapatos sa Marikina","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1970-04-16"},"Q24846678":{"lon":120.72864,"lat":13.93783,"address":"Balayan Church, Balayan, Batangas","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BalayanAcademyChurchjf0400 29.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Balayan","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Balayan","date":"1986-12-09"},"Q43360070":{"lon":120.5915,"address":"Baguio City Hall, City Hall Drive, Baguio","lat":16.41376,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the second column from the left of the building facade.","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Baguio City Hall","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo na yari sa kahoy at yero noong panunungkulan ni E.W. Reynolds, unang punong lungsod, 1910. Sentro ng pamahaalang lokal sa pagtataguyod ng Baguio bilang Summer Capital ng Pilipinas. Sergio Bayan, unang Filipinong punong lungsod, 1937–1939. Dito itinaas ang watawat ng bansang Hapon tanda ng pagsakop sa lungsod, 27 Disyembre 1941. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1945. Muling ipinatayo na yari sa konkreto, 1949–1950. Pinasinayaan ni Pangulong Elpidio Quirino, Mayo 1950. Ipinaayos, 1997–1999. Pinasinayaan, 15 Pebrero 1999.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Baguio City Hall, a heritage site.JPG","credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Baguio City Hall","date":"2009-09-02"},"Q46575606":{"date":"2003","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Roca Encantada","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 14 August 2002</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Roca Encantada","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.67928,"lat":10.74259,"address":"Roca Encantada, Buenavista, Guimaras"},"Q28868870":{"lat":14.16179,"address":"Baker Memorial Hall, Mariano M. Mondoñedo Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","lon":121.24247,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pook ng Bilangguang Kampo sa Los Baños","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Baker Hall historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook ng Bilangguang Kampo sa Los Baños","inscription":"<p>Ginamit ng mga Hapones bilang bilangguang kampo para sa mga bihag na Amerikano at ibang banyaga noong 1943. Nilusob ng pinagsanib na pangkat ng mga gerilyang Filipino mula sa mga kasapi ng ROTC Hunters, HUKBALAHAP ika-48 iskwadrong Tsino, sariling pangkat ni Pangulong Quezon, Pangkat Marking, at iba pang di-regular na tropa noong 23 Pebrero 1945. Ang pinagsanib na puwersa ay inorganisa ni Tinyente Koronel Gustavo Ingles na kasapi ng Hunters at kinatawan ng puwersang Amerikanong nangangasiwa sa mga gerilya ng Katimugang Luzon. Pinamunuan ni Tinyente Koronel Honorio Guerrero at ng ROTC Hunters ang unang salakay. Matagumpay nilang nakontrol ang paligi ng kampo at sa tulong ng mga Amerikanong miyembro ng Company B 511th Paratroop Infantry ay napalaya ang 2,147 bilanggo.</p>"}}},"date":"2005"},"Q50085885":{"lat":14.46244,"address":"Bataan Provincial Highway cor. Cabcaben Road, Mariveles, Bataan","lon":120.59592,"date":"1977","locPhoto":null,"name":"Cabcaben","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"Mariveles, Bataan","title":"Cabcaben","inscription":""}}}},"Q28937532":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Port Sta. Ana","inscription":"<p>Dinaungan ng mga unang manggagawang agrikultural na Hapon sa Davao, Mayo 1903 na nanguna sa pagpapaunlad ng industriya ng abaka dito.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Port Sta. Ana","locPhoto":null,"date":"2003","lon":125.62608,"lat":7.07524,"address":"Magsaysay Park, Davao City"},"Q44504751":{"lat":14.59452,"address":"Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.9762,"date":"2014","name":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Ang Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (Filipino).jpg"}},"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (English).jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands","inscription":""}},"es":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (Spanish).jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"La Cámara de Comercio de las Islas Filipinas","subtitle":null}}}},"Q47004026":{"date":"2011-05-02","name":"Labanan sa Baryo Piis","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Labanan sa Baryo Piis","subtitle":"Lucban, Quezon"}}},"lat":14.14867,"address":"Kilometer 134, Lucban–Sampaloc Road, Lucban, Quezon","lon":121.59587},"Q22262589":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Tulay ng San Juan","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Tulay ng San Juan","inscription":"<p>Sa tulay na ito, noong 29 Enero 1899, nagtagpo sina Kol. Luciano San Miguel, Filipinong komandante sa pook na iyon, at Col. John Stotsenburg, Commander, First Nebraska Volunteer Infantry, U.S. Army, upang ilatag ang hangganang sakop ng mga puwersang Filipino at Amerikano. Pagkaraang sumiklab ang Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano sa panulukan ng Sociego at Silencio, Sta. Mesa, Maynila noong 4 Pebrero 1899, naglabanan ang dalawang puwersa sa tulay na ito, 5 Pebrero 1899.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Tulay ng San Juan 10.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"2009","lat":14.60159,"address":"San Juan River Bridge, San Juan, Metro Manila","lon":121.02029},"Q43304785":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan"},"photo":{"credit":"Nikond80 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Marker church and convent of San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan","date":"2006","lon":120.97911,"lat":14.58484,"address":"Rizal Park, Padre Burgos Avenue cor. Maria Y. Orosa Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q37948341":{"date":"1955","locPhoto":null,"name":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>In memory of Olivia Salamanca, M.D., pioneer woman physician of the Philippines. Born in San Roque, Cavite on 1 July 1889; appointed government scholar in 1905; studied in Drexel Institute, Philadelphia. Died on 11 July 1913. A devoted and competent practitioner, she was a credit to the medical profession and an inspiration to her fellow women.</p>","title":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.58319,"address":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca, Taft Avenue cor. T.M. Kalaw Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98389},"Q22296143":{"lon":121.01261,"lat":14.63789,"address":"Santuario de San Pedro Bautista, 69 San Pedro Bautista Street, Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"1936","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Francisco del Monte historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Francisco del Monte","inscription":"<p>The site was donated to the Franciscans on February 17, 1590, by Governor Santiago de Vera in the name of King Philip II. Chapels were built of thatch and bamboo in 1590, of wood in 1593, and of volcanic tuff in 1599. The last was badly damaged in the Chinese uprising of 1639. Present church built from 1696 to 1699, through the generosity of Tomas de Endaya. To this site retired for prayer and recollection several Franciscans who sufferred martyrdom in Japan in the XVII Century and others who lead missionary expeditions to Japan, China and Cambodia. The Escuela Serafica or Probation School for Filipino applicants to the Franciscan order was opened here July 16, 1931.</p>"}}},"name":"Church of San Francisco del Monte","locPhoto":null},"Q31440586":{"address":"Punta Cruz Watchtower, Maribojoc, Bohol","lat":9.73506,"lon":123.79026,"name":"Bantayan ng Punta Cruz","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Punta Cruz Watchtower historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Recoletos sa Patronato ni San Vicente Ferrer laban sa pagsalakay ng mga piratang moro, 1796. Yari sa korales na may hugis tatsulok as unang palapag at heksagonal sa ikalawang palapag. Naligtas sa pagkasira noong digmaang Filipino-Amerikano at ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig nang sunugin ng mga puwersang Hapones ang bayan ng Maribojoc, 1944. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang militar noong panahon ng mga Espanyol at bantayog sa kahusayan ng mga lokal na artisano. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>","title":"Bantayan ng Punta Cruz","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2009"},"Q24071475":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Dagupan","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Augustinians had charge of the spiritual administration of Dagupan from 1590 to 1713, and the Dominicans from 1713 to the close of the nineteenth century. An early church and a convent were burned in 1660 when Andres Malong's men razed the town. The Rev. Pedro Rama, O.P., rebuilt this church in 1816. In 1895 the Rev. Vicente Iztegui, O.P. rebuilt the facade that the earthquake of March 16, 1892 had destroyed.</p>","title":"Church of Dagupan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Dagupan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1939","lat":16.04248,"address":"Dagupan Church, Dagupan, Pangasinan","lon":120.33517},"Q25068837":{"lon":120.94012,"address":"Imus Arsenal, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42967,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Imus Arsenal 03.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, noong 1896, itinatag ng Tsinong panday na si Jose Ignacio Paua, na naging Heneral noong Himagsikang Pilipino laban sa Espanya at Labanang Pilipino - Amerikano, ang isang Arsenal sa utos ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo. Dito ginawa at kinumpuni ang mga baril at lantaka ng mga manghihimagsik sa tulong ng iba pa niyang kapwa Tsino at Rebolusyonaryo.</p>","title":"Arsenal ng Imus"}}},"name":"Arsenal ng Imus","locPhoto":null,"date":"1990"},"Q41214132":{"date":"1951","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site of the first parachute landing in the Philippines executed by the 511th Parachute Infantry Regiment, 11th Airborne Division, 8th Army, USA, under Lt. Gen. Robert Eichelberger, with Maj. John P. M. Swing, CG., 3 February 1945.</p>","title":"Tagaytay Ridge Landing","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"TagaytayRidge HistoricalMarker TagaytayCity.jpg"}}},"name":"Tagaytay Ridge Landing","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96197,"address":"Tagaytay Rotonda, Tagaytay, Cavite","lat":14.11533},"Q28919992":{"lat":7.09397,"address":"Davao City","lon":125.50026,"name":"Ohta Kyozaburo","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ohta Kyozaburo","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Hyogo, Japan, Pebrero 1876. Nagtatag, Ohta Development Company. Ang unang taniman ng abaka ng mga Hapon sa Pilipinas, 3 Mayo 1907. Nagtatag ng iba pang mga kumpanya tulad ng Mintal Plantation Company, Riverside Plantation Company, Talomo River Plantation Company at Guianga Plantation Company. Tumulong sa paglago ng negosyong Hapones sa Davao. Namatay sa Kyoto, Japan, 31 Oktubre 1917.</p>","subtitle":"(1876–1917)"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Ohta Kyozaburo historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"2003"},"Q44820670":{"lon":120.47696,"lat":17.92722,"address":"Juan Luna Shrine, Rizal Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Bahay ni Luna historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bahay ni Luna","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Bahay ni Luna","date":"1977"},"Q24816583":{"date":"1955-06-24","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo 1859–1946","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Taal 24 Hunyo 1859; nag-aral sa Kolehiyo ng Santa Catalina; Asawa ni Felipe Agoncillo at siya niyang matapat na katulong sa kanyang gawaing makabayan; ipinagbili ang kanyang mga hiyas upang magugol ng asawa sa misyon nito sa ibang bansa sa kapakanan ng pagsasarili ng Pilipinas. Sa panahon ng kanilang pagkapatapon sa Hong Kong, ay tinahi niya ang unang bandilang Pilipino na buong pagmamalaking iwinagayway ni Heneral Emelio Aguinaldo sa Kawit noong 12 Hunyo 1898 sa pagpapahayag ng Pagsasarili ng Pilipinas. Namatay sa Taal 30 Mayo 1946.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the museum.","name":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo 1859–1946","locPhoto":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Marcela Agoncillo Historical Landmark entrance.jpg"},"lon":120.91815,"address":"Marcela Mariño and Felipe Agoncillo Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.87843},"Q29017572":{"address":"Cagayan de Oro","lat":8.47617,"lon":124.6417,"date":"2015-01-13","name":"Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Cagayan de Misamis","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"10 Enero 1899","title":"Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Cagayan de Misamis","inscription":"<p>Itinaas ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Casa Real ng Cagayan de Misamis (ngayo'y Cagayan de Oro) bilang sagisag ng pagkilala sa Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo, 10 Enero 1899. Tinawag ni Gobernador Jose Roa y Casas ng lalawigan ng Misamis ang pagdiriwang na yaon bilang \"La Fiesta Nacional\" sa kanyang liham kay Hen. Aguinaldo, 26 Enero 1899. Tanda ito ng masiglang pagdiriwang ng mamamayan sa kalayaan ng Pilipinas.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q24702458":{"date":"1978-01-15","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the facade of Tayabas municipal  hall.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Pransiskano noong 1578, naging kabisera ng lalawigan noong 1605 na dati ay nasa Kalilayan (ngayo'y Unisan). Inilipat sa Lucena, ika-10 ng Marso, 1901. Noong ika-23 ng Oktubre, 1841, sa pamumuno ni Apolinario de la Cruz, isang labanan ang namagitan sa kanyang mga tauhan at sa pangkat ng mga Kastila sa baryo Isabang. Ang mga manghihimagsik ay nagwagi sa labanang iyon at napatay ang gobernador ng Kastila. Isa pang labanan ang naganap noong ika-1 ng Nobyembre sa Alitao kung saan nadakip si Hermano Puli at binitay sa karatig na bulwagang bayan ng Tayabas noong ika-4 ng Nobyembre. Siya ay ipinagbunyi bilang unang bayani ng lalawigan ng Tayabas at hari ng mga Tagalog.</p>","title":"Tayabas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Tayabas Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"name":"Tayabas","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tayabasjf0310 07.JPG"},"lon":121.59256,"lat":14.02517,"address":"Tayabas, Quezon"},"Q24709070":{"lat":13.82818,"address":"San Juan, Batangas","lon":121.39486,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng San Juan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Juan Church (Batangas) historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng San Juan","inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa pawid at kawayan sa Pinagbayanan, 1843. Nahiwalay sa Rosario, 1848. Ipinagawa ang simbahang bato ni Padre Damaso Mojica, unang kura paroko sa tulong ng mga Principales ng bayan sa pamumuno ni Gobernadorsilyong si Felipe Salud, 1845. Lumubog sa tubig, 1883. INilipat sa kasalukuyang pook, 1890: at pinasinayaan ang ngayo'y simbahang bato, sa tangkilik ni Padre Celestino Yoldi, Rekoletos, 1894. Pansamantalang pinamahalaan ng mga paring Kaputsino, 1904. Pinalitan ng San Juan de Bocboc ng Bolboc sa pamamagitan ng batas bilang 2390, 1914. Naging San Juan de Nepomuceno ng mga unang taon ng 1920.</p>"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1990"},"Q28937921":{"lon":124.8409,"address":"Koronadal, South Cotabato","lat":6.498,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"City Government of Cotabato","file":"Seventeen Martyrs of Koronadal historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Pook na Pinaglibingan ng Labimpitong Pilipinong Martir sa Koronadal","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pook na Pinaglibingan ng Labimpitong Pilipinong Martir sa Koronadal","date":"2013"},"Q28933167":{"lat":8.47579,"address":"Cagayan de Oro","lon":124.6419,"name":"Labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bago magbukang-liwayway noong Abril 7, 1900, ang lakas panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pamumuno ni Heneral Nicolas Capistrano ay nagsagawa ng isang biglaang pagsalakay sa ika-40 rehimiyento na binubuo ng mga boluntaryo ng Estados Unidos sa pamumuno ni Medyor James Case. Sa pagtatanggol sa kanilang minamahal na bansa. Ilang daang magigiting na Pilipinong manghihimagsik ang namatay sa labanang ito. </p><p> </p><p> Ang panandang pangkasaysayang ito ay buong pusong iniaalay ng sambayanang Pilipino sa magigiting na tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan ng Cagayan de Misamis sa paggunita sa ikasandaang taon ng makasaysayang labanang ito.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2000-04-07"},"Q37659579":{"lon":121.07423,"address":"Taguig Church, Taguig, Metro Manila","lat":14.52673,"date":"1987-07-25","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall just to the right of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Tagig","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Agustino ang parokya sa pamamatnubay ng patronang si Sta. Ana at ipinatayo ng unang kura paroko P. Diego Alvarez, ang unang simbahang bato noong 1587. Nasira ng lindol, 1645, at muling ipinatayo ni P. Andres Diaz, 1848. Nasirang muli ng lindol, 1882, at muling ipinatayong yari sa bato ni P. Giullermo Diaz, 1886–1896. Ipinaayos ni Rt. Rev. Msgr. Augurio I. Juta, 1980–1985, at ni Msgr. Emmanuel V. Sunga, 1985–1987. Inihandog sa Panginoon ng Kagalang-Galang Obispo Bruno Torpigliani, Apostoliko Nunsiyo sa Pilipinas, sa pagdiriwang ng ika-400 taong pagkatatag ng parokya, Hulyo 25, 1987.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Simbahan ng Taguig.JPG","credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Simbahan ng Tagig","locPhoto":{"file":"Taguig Church main entrance.jpg","credit":"Ronaldbunag {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}},"Q28942505":{"lat":7.38406,"address":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun, Parang, Maguindanao","lon":124.25707,"date":"2014-04-02","name":"Salipada K. Pendatun (1921–1985)","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Salipada K. Pendatun (1921–1985)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Pikit, Cotabato, 3 Disyembre 1912. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas at pumasa sa Philippine Bar, 1938. Hinirang bilang kasapi ng Lupong Panlalawigan ng Cotabato, 1938; nahalal, 1940. Nakomisyon bilang 3rd Lieutenant, Philippine Army Reserve Force at napabilang sa USAFFE bago sumiklab ang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Kasama si Datu Udtog Matalam, nagtatag ng isang puwersang gerilya laban sa mga Hapon sa Cotabato. Hinirang bilang Gobernador ng Cotabato pagkatapos ng digmaan. Nahalal bilang senador, 1946-1949; tagapayo, administrasyong Quirino, 1950-1953; kinatawan ng lalawigan ng Cotabato sa Kongreso, 1958-1961; 1962-1965; 1966-1969; 1970-1972; Speaker Pro Tempore, 1962-1967; kinatawan ng Maguindanao sa Regular Batasang Pambansa at Speaker Pro Tempore, 1984-1985. Yumao, 27 Enero 1985.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q50377948":{"lat":14.3366,"address":"Gen. M. Capinpin Street, Biñan, Laguna","lon":121.08353,"date":"1958","name":"Rizal in Biñan","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>In this town of Biñan in 1871, Dr. Jose Rizal received his first formal schooling under Maestro Justiniano Cruz, who later advised him to study in a higher school in Manila.﻿</p>","title":"Rizal in Biñan"}}}},"Q51921881":{"lon":121.17639,"lat":14.58757,"address":"Antipolo Cathedral, Antipolo, Rizal","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The statue of Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was brought from Mexico to Manila by Governor Juan Niño de Tavora in 1626 and at his death in 1632 was turned over to the Jesuits for the Church of Antipolo. Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was proclaimed Patroness of the galleons. The statue crossed the Pacific, and returned, eight times on board the galleons of Acapulco: in 1641, 1643, 1645–46 on the San Luis; 1648–1649 on the Encarnacion; in 1650 on the San Diego; in 1851–1853 on the San Javier; in 1659–1662 on the San Jose and in 1746–1748 on the Nuestra Señora del Pilar. The statue of Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was canonically crowned on November 26, 1926, by the Most Rev. Michael J. O’Doherty, Archbishop of Manila, on the Luneta, Manila, in the presence of at least one hundred thousand people.</p>","title":"Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"OLOfGoodVoyage HistoricalMarker AntipoloCity.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the southern corner of the cathedral facade.","name":"Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje","locPhoto":{"credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}","file":"Antipolo Shrine (Antipolo, Rizal).jpg"},"date":"1937"},"Q24736360":{"lon":120.91758,"lat":13.87761,"address":"Calle Ramon Diokno, Taal, Batangas","date":"1991-01-22","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Ananias Diokno historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"title":"Ananias Diokno","inscription":"<p>Kilala sa taguring Heneral ng Karagatan. Ipinanganak sa Taal, Batangas, Enero 22, 1860. Naging kalihim ng Digma sa pamahalaang pangkagawaran ng Batangas, 1898: Namumunong Heneral ng hukbong ekspedisyunaryo ng Panay; matagumpay na nakipaglaban sa balwarte ng mga Kastila sa Aklan, Antique, Capiz at Lungsod ng Iloilo: Gobernador pampulitiko-militar ng Capiz. Lumahok sa pakikipaglaban ng mga gerilya noong Digmaang Pilipino at Amerikano sa Capiz, 1898. Nakipaglaban at nadakip ng mga Amerikano sa may bundok Makawiwili, Aklan, 1901. Namatay sa Arayat, Pampanga, Nobyembre 2, 1922.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Ananias Diokno","locPhoto":null},"Q29018419":{"address":"University of Eastern Philippines, Catarman, Northern Samar","lat":12.50977,"lon":124.66689,"date":"2014","locPhoto":null,"name":"University of Eastern Philippines","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang paaralang panlalawigan sa pangalang Catarman Farm School, 1918. Naging paaralang bayan dahil sa insular aid ng Pamunuang Pambansa at tinawag na Catarman Agricultural School, 1919; Kalaunan, Catarman Agricultural High School. Tumulong sa mga karatig na pamayanang pang-agrikultura. Nagsilbing lugar para sa pagsasanay-militar ng puwersang gerilya at pansamantalang himpilan ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Pinangalanang Catarman National Agricultural High School, 1951. Naging Samar Institute of Technology, 1956. Itinalaga bilang unibersidad at tinawag na University of Eastern Philippines, 1964.</p>","title":"University of Eastern Philippines","subtitle":null}}}},"Q22236932":{"lon":120.9785,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Plaza Nuestra Señora de Guia Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.57816,"date":"1984","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1877–1919)","inscription":"<p>Ama ng pag-aaral ng beriberi sa mga sanggol sa Pilipinas. Ipinanganak sa Ermita, Maynila, Enero 8, 1877. Nagtapos ng A.B. sa Ateneo Municipal, 1894, at Doktor sa Medicina sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1902. Sumulat para sa Republica Filipina, La Independencia at La Patria. Kagawad ng patnugutan, Manila at Revista Filipina de Medicina y Farmacia. Kagawad, Colegio Medico-Farmaceutico, Asamblea de Medicos y Farmaceuticos de Filipinas at Sanggunian ng Kalusugan. Isa sa mga nagtatag ng Liga Nacional Filipina para la Proteccion de la Infancia at La Gota de Leche. Pinagkalooban ng mga medalyang pilak ng Louisiana Purchase Exposition at Panama Pacific International Exposition. Namatay, Enero 4, 1919.</p>","title":"Manuel S. Guerrero"},"photo":{"file":"Manuel S. Guerrero (1877 - 1919).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Manuel S. Guerrero","locPhoto":null},"Q24849237":{"date":"2007","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Known as the Faro de Punta de Malabrigo, designed by Guillermo Brockman as cylindrical brick tower with metal staircase, adjacent pavilion and machine room, 1891. Built by the Chinese conractor Jose Garcia, 1896. An outstanding work of architecture from the Spanish colonial period, it has served as beacon to sea vessels at Verde Island Passage. Declared as National Historical Landmark, 27 November 2006.</p>","title":"Malabrigo Lighthouse","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Malabrigo Lighthouse","lon":121.26247,"lat":13.59882,"address":"Malabrigo Point Lighthouse, Lobo, Batangas"},"Q46574680":{"address":"Patnongon, Antique","lat":10.91353,"lon":121.99369,"date":"2008-02-25","locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Lumang Simbahan at Kumbento ng Patnongon","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Ang Lumang Simbahan at Kumbento ng Patnongon","subtitle":null}}}},"Q45206250":{"lon":120.97537,"lat":14.43802,"address":"Bacoor, Cavite","date":"2017-12-01","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a pedestal just to the west of the statue of the saint.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"San Ezekiel Moreno historical marker (Bacoor).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Paring Agustino Rekoleto at santo. Isinilang sa La Rioja, Espanya, 9 Abril 1848. Dumating sa Maynila, 10 Pebrero 1870. Naordenahang pari sa Katedral ng Maynila, 2 Hunyo 1871. Kabilang sa mga nagtatag ng bayan ng Puerto Princesa bilang unang misyonero, kapelyan ng mga militar at ng colonya penal, 4 Marso 1872. Mula 1873 hanggang 1885, naging kura paroko ng Calapan (Mindoro), Las Piñas, Santo Tomas (Batangas), Sta. Cruz (Maynila) at tagapamahala ng Hacienda ng Imus. Yumao sa Espanya sa sakit na kanser, 19 Agosto 1906. Idineklarang santo ni Papa Juan Pablo II dahil sa ipinakitang kabanalan, kapuri-puring halimbawa, at taospusong pagsilbi sa mga kapuspalad at mga maysakit sa Pilipinas, Espanya at Colombia, 11 Oktubre 1992. Itinuturing na santo at patron ng mga may kanser.</p>","title":"San Ezekiel Moreno","subtitle":"1848–1906"}}},"name":"San Ezekiel Moreno","locPhoto":{"file":"Saint Ezekiel Moreno y Diaz Park (Bacoor) - 3.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"Q28933113":{"lon":123.82117,"lat":8.41615,"address":"Aloran, Misamis Occidental","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Banisilon, Aloran, Misamis Occidental, 5 Mayo 1898. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, 1921. Gobernador ng Misamis Occidental, 1929-1931; kinatawan sa Lehislatura ng Pilipinas, 1931-1935; Kombensyon Konstitusyonal, 1934-1935; Pambansang Asambleya, 1935-1938. Naihalal muli sa asambleya ngunit tumanggi sa posisyon upang umanib sa kilusang gerilya at hukbong Amerikano sa Australia noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Dinakip ng mga Hapon at ipiniit sa Fort Santiago at Bilibid. Dinala sa Manila Chinese Cemetery kung saan siya at ang iba pang kasama ay pinugutan ng ulo at itinapon ang kanilang mga bangkay sa isang hukay lamang sa loob ng sementeryo, 30 Agosto 1944. Natagpuan ang mga labi, 1946. Inilipat ang mga labi at binigyan ng marangal na libing sa Cementerio Del Norte sa Maynila, 9 Marso 1947.</p>","title":"Jose F. Ozamiz","subtitle":"(1898–1944)"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Jose F. Ozamiz","locPhoto":null,"date":"2014"},"Q40999278":{"lon":120.97466,"lat":14.59291,"address":"Sto. Tomas Street cor. Solana Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"USTFoundationSite HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas","inscription":""}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas","date":"2002"},"Q24831810":{"lat":13.94006,"address":"Lipa, Batangas","lon":121.16278,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Fidel A. Reyes","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Fidel Reyes Monument, Lipa City.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Fidel A. Reyes","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa lungsod ng Lipa, Batangas, noong Mayo 3, 1878. Nagtapos ng A.B., Colegio de San Juan de Letran, 1895 at B.S. Phar. Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1902. Patnugot ng La Vanguardia at El Renacimiento. Nagbunyag ng mga katiwalian ng pamahalaang Amerikano sa kanyang editorial na “Aves de Rapina”, na pumukaw sa pambansang kamalayan. Kinatawan, Asambleya ng Pilipinas, 1912, at unang Pilipinong direktor , Kawanihan ng Pangangalakal at Industriya, 1918–1929. Nagkaloob ng lote sa lungsod ng Lipa para sa kaunaunahang SOS Children's Village sa Pilipinas. Namatay Setyembre 10, 1967.</p>","subtitle":"(1878–1967)"}}},"date":"1984-05-03"},"Q40999993":{"date":"2006","locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos Marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos"}}},"lat":14.58861,"address":"Recoletos Street cor. Muralla Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97871},"Q50413489":{"date":"2007-09-22","name":"Ang Pagsuko ng mga Puwersang Hapones sa Negros Oriental","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Ang Pagsuko ng mga Puwersang Hapones sa Negros Oriental","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Dumaguete South Road, Zamboanguita, Negros Oriental","lat":9.11136,"lon":123.20291},"Q28877396":{"name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Replica of the house constructed in Talisay by Rizal. He lived here from March 1893 to 31 July 1896 while in exile at Dapitan.</p>","subtitle":"1861–1896 National Hero of the Philippines"},"photo":{"file":"Jose Rizal historical marker in Rizal Shrine Dapitan.jpg","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"date":"1962","address":"Jose Rizal Memorial Protected Landscape, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lat":8.66805,"lon":123.41665},"Q46573020":{"lon":122.43162,"address":"New Washington, Aklan","lat":11.65106,"date":"2007","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1928–2005)","inscription":"","title":"Jaime Cardinal Sin"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jaime Cardinal Sin"},"Q41082313":{"lat":14.59402,"address":"Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97618,"date":"1968-12-08","locPhoto":null,"name":"Pintong Isabela II","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pintong Isabela II","inscription":""},"photo":{"file":"Pintong Isabela II historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q22341197":{"lat":14.38101,"address":"Pakil Municipal Hall, Pakil, Laguna","lon":121.47871,"name":"Ang Bayan ng Pakil","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pakil,Lagunajf6670 20.JPG"},"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical marker of Pakil.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang unang pamayanan ni San Pedro Bautista, O.F.M., 1588. Naging baryo ng Paete, 1602; Naging bayan, 1676 at hinirang na unang kapitan si Diego Jorge. Ipinatayo ang casa tribunal at unang paaralang bayan, 1800. Ibinalik sa pagiging baryo ng Paete, Oktubre 12, 1903 at inilipat sa pagiging baryo ng Pangil, Nobyembre 25, 1903. Mula ng mapaanib ang bayang ito sa Pangil, apat na taga-Pakil ang naging Presidente Municipal. Naging ganap na bayan, Oktubre 1, 1927 sa Bisa ng Utos Pampangasiwaan bilang 77, Setyembre 9, 1927, na sinusugan ng Utos Pampangasiwaan bilang 91. Disyembre 5, 1927. Nang panahon ng pananakop ng mga Hapon, ang mamamayan ng bayang ito ay buong giting na nakipaglaban. Lumaya, Abril 5, 1945.</p>","title":"Ang Bayan ng Pakil","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the left side of the main entrance of the municipal hall.","date":"1988"},"Q24814491":{"date":"1991-01-22","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Escuela Pia historical marker 2.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isang paaralang pinangasiwaan ng simbahan at ipinangalan sa orden ng Escuela Pia, isang kongregasyong na itinatag ni San Jose ng Calasanz noong ika-17 daantaon. Itinatag ng mga paring agustino noong 1839, ang kumbento ng mga ito ang nagsilbing paaralan para sa mahihirap at iniwang kabataan ng Taal. Ang kasalukuyang gusali at ipinatayo ni P. Aniceto Aparicio, 1885. Naging paaralang sentral noong panahon pananakop ng mga Amerikano. Ang restorasyon ng lumang gusali, na isa sa mga pinakamatandang institusyong edukasyonal sa Pilipinas, ay sinumulan ng Taal Arts and Culture Movement, Inc. sa pakikipag-ugnayan sa pambansang suriang pangkasaysayan. Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga kautusang bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang paaralang ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Escuela Pia","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the building.","locPhoto":{"file":"Taal,Batangasjf2457 08.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Escuela Pia","lon":120.92372,"address":"Escuela Pia, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.8805},"Q28927495":{"date":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Pagdalaw ni Valenzuela sa Dapitan","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Visit of Pio Valenzuela historical marker.jpg","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Pagdalaw ni Valenzuela sa Dapitan","lon":123.41693,"lat":8.66735,"address":"Jose Rizal Memorial Protected Landscape, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte"},"Q44807646":{"lon":120.53027,"lat":14.67589,"address":"Capitol Drive, Balanga, Bataan","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"The Fall of Bataan historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"9 April 1942","inscription":"<p>[The fall of Bataan] sealed in blood the permanent ties of friendship and cooperation between the Philippines and the United States. This marker is dedicated, 9 April 1952, to the memory of the gallant Filipino and Americans soldiers as well as civilians, who fought and died side by side in the defense of Democracy.</p>","title":"The Fall of Bataan"}}},"name":"The Fall of Bataan","locPhoto":null,"date":"1952-04-09"},"Q28927601":{"date":"2014-10-28","name":"Mga Guho ng Kuta ng Tukuran","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Kinatatayuan ng pamayanan ni Sultan Untung na nakubkob ng puwersang Espanyol, 1887. Tinayuan ng Kuta ng Alfonso XIII, 1890; natapos, 1891. Pook ng rebelyon laban sa Espanya, Setyembre 1896 at Oktubre 1898, at pook-pinagbitayan sa mga rebeldeng sundalong Pilipino sa Mindanao, Enero 1897. Tinayuan ng pamayanang Muslim matapos iwan ng mga Espanyol, 1899. Naging garison ng hukbong Amerikano, 1900-1912, at ng Philippine Constabulary, 1902-1903. Sentro ng Tukuran-Lintogup Telephone Line ng U.S. SIGNAL Corps, ang pangunahing linya ng komunikasyon sa Mindanao, 1 Enero 1901. Himpilan ng distritong militar, 1912-1918, at distritong munisipal ng Tukuran, 1918-1921. Tuluyang inabandona dulot ng patuloy na pagsalakay ng mga Moro, 1921. Naging Barangay Militar, Tukuran, Zamboanga del Sur.</p>","title":"Mga Guho ng Kuta ng Tukuran"}}},"lat":7.84445,"address":"Tukuran, Zamboanga del Sur","lon":123.5849},"Q43302185":{"date":"1971","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Morong","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Hannachiever07 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Morong Historical Marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the left of the main entrance of the old Morong municipal hall.","locPhoto":{"file":"Morong Museum entrance (2).jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Morong","lon":121.23887,"lat":14.51285,"address":"Tupas Street, Morong, Rizal"},"Q43248095":{"lat":14.27399,"address":"Maragondon Church, Maragondon, Cavite","lon":120.73364,"locPhoto":{"file":"MaragondonChurchjf0031 06.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Maragondon","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Maragondon","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Maragondon Marker.JPG"}}},"date":"2007"},"Q43247430":{"lat":14.27283,"address":"Col. E. Riego de Dios Street, Maragondon, Cavite","lon":120.73695,"date":"1975","locPhoto":null,"name":"Emiliano Riego de Dios","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Emiliano Riego de Dios","subtitle":"(1864–1926)"},"photo":null}}},"Q28942696":{"lon":125.02763,"address":"Tacloban","lat":11.2073,"date":"1979","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Built by the Japanese Imperial Forces during World War II as part of the fortification against the Allied Liberation Forces lead by Gen. Douglas MacArthur on D-Day, 20 October 1944. The United States Marines captured and used it as shelter from aerial bombardments by Japanese planes. As war relic, the Dio Island Resort has maintained and preserved it for posterity.</p>","title":"Japanese Pillbox Whitebeach, San Jose, Tacloban City"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Japanese Pillbox Whitebeach, San Jose, Tacloban City"},"Q38167195":{"date":"1937","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Juan del Monte","inscription":"<p>The Church and Convent were built in 1602–1604 by the Dominican Province of the Most Holy Rosary on a site donated by Captain Julian de Cuenca. Both buildings were burned during the Chinese uprising of 1639. The new Church and Convent, constructed in 1641, were set on fire in July 1763 during the British occupation of Manila. The present Church and Convent, constructed in 1774, were used by the insurgent forces of the revolution of 1898. This Sanctuary is the seat of the Cofraternity of Santisimo Cristo de San Juan del Monte approved by Pope Innocent X on March 4, 1648.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"San Juan del Monte Church in Metro Manila historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Church of San Juan del Monte","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.03054,"address":"Santuario del Santo Cristo, 183 F. Blumentritt Street, San Juan, Metro Manila","lat":14.59819},"Q37977096":{"date":"2014","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo, 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, ngunit muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang na rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>","subtitle":"(1861–1896)"},"photo":null}},"name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.96878,"address":"National Road, Basco, Batanes","lat":20.44932},"Q44504205":{"lat":16.41361,"address":"The Mansion, Baguio","lon":120.6204,"date":"2008","locPhoto":{"credit":"Francisco M. Pajares, Jr. {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Entrance to the Mansion House.jpg"},"name":"Mansion House","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mansion House","inscription":""},"photo":null},"ilo":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mansion House","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Irvin Parco Sto. Tomas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Mansion House NHI marker Ilokano.JPG"}},"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Mansion House"},"photo":{"file":"Mansion House NHI marker English.JPG","credit":"Irvin Parco Sto. Tomas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on the pillars of the main gate to the compound. The Tagalog marker is on the second pillar from the north, the English on the third pillar, and the Ilocano on the last pillar."},"Q25080050":{"date":"1986-10-02","name":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas","inscription":"<p>Dating kapilya sa baryo ng Imus. Itinatag ang Parokya ng Camarin de Piedra ng mga paring Rekoleto noong 1867. Ipinatayo ang simbahang bato sa patronato ng La Immaculada Concepcion at naging unang kura paroko si Padre Valentin Diaz. Nagsilbing luklukan ng pamahalaang sibil ng mga Kastila ang kumbento: naganap dito ang madugong labanan ng magapi ng hukbong Kastila ang mga rebolusyonaryo sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Placido Campos at kanyang kalihim Francisco Barzaga, Pebrero 25, 1897. Ipiniit rin dito ng mga Hapon ang mga mamamayan noong Disyembre 17, 1944 at 17 sa kanilang pinatay ang nalibing sa iisang hukay.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas historical marker.jpg"}}},"lat":14.32693,"address":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church of Dasmariñas, Dasmariñas, Cavite","lon":120.93583},"Q28933707":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Women’s Auxilary Service","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this site, May 18, 1943 was adopted the constitution and by-laws of the Women’s Auxiliary Service led by Josefa Borromeo Capistrano which assisted the Tenth Military District under Col. Wendell W. Fertic, army of the United States, in resisting the Japanese invaders. Dedicated to the courageous women of Misamis Occidental who volunteered and risked their lives for freedom.</p>","title":"Women’s Auxilary Service","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"date":null,"lat":8.14225,"address":"La Purisima Street corner Jose P. Rizal Avenue, Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","lon":123.84558},"Q39021856":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Gusaling Army and Navy Club","inscription":"<p>Dinisenyo ni William E. Parsons bilang bahagi ng balangkas ni Daniel Burnham para sa Lungsod ng Maynila. Pinasinayaan, 19 Abril 1911. Nagsilbing clubhouse ng Samahang Pang-Hukbong Katihan at Pandagat ng Maynila (Army and Navy Club of Maynila) mula 1911–1942 at 1946–1980. Matinding napinsala noong labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Muling isinaayos sa pagtutulungan ng U.S. Army Engineering Corps at U.S. Navy Construction Battallion (Seabees), 1945. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 26 Abril 1991. Muling isinaayos, 2014–2017. Pinasinayaan bilang Rizal Park Hotel ni Pangulong Rodrigo Roa Duterte, 26 Hulyo 2017.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null},"en":{"text":{"title":"Army and Navy Club Building","inscription":"<p>Designed by William E. Parsons as part of Daniel Burnham’s plan for the City of Manila. Inaugurated, 19 April 1911. Served as the clubhouse of the Army and Navy Club of Manila, 1911–1942 and 1946–1980. Sustained heavy damage during the battle for Manila, 1945. Reconstructed through the joint effort of the U.S. Army Engineering Corps and U.S. Navy Construction Battallion (Seabees), 1945. Declared a National Historical Landmark, 26 April 1991. Underwent rehabilitation, 2014–2017. Inaugurated as the Rizal Park Hotel by President Rodrigo Roa Duterte, 26 July 2017.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Army and Navy Club Building","locPhoto":null,"date":"2018","lon":120.97624,"address":"Rizal Park Hotel, South Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.57877},"Q43282120":{"lat":13.44835,"address":"house of Pedro Lardizabal, Governor D. Reyes Street cor. Magsaysay Drive, Boac, Marinduque","lon":121.83924,"date":"1973-02-23","name":"Maharlikang Tahanan ni Kapitan Piroco","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Maharlikang Tahanan ni Kapitan Piroco"}}},"locDesc":null},"Q44814882":{"name":"Servando Castro","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1946)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang noong Oktubre 23, 1861 sa Batac, Ilocos Norte. Nag-aral ng pagpapari at nagturo sa Seminaryo ng Vigan. Naglingkod ng 12 taon sa Diyosesis ng Nueva Segovia. Sumapi sa Iglesia Filipina Independiente at naging isa sa mga lumagda sa Doctrina y Reglas Constitucionales. Pansimbahang Gobernador ng Laguna, Obispo ng Rehiyon ng Ilocos, Obispo Maximo Emeritus at Decano de los Obispos. Sumulat para sa La Vanguardia. Kinatawan ng Ilocos Norte sa 1934 Konstitusyunal Kumbensiyon at kagawad ng Komite sa Tungkulin ng Mamamayan. Namatay noong Disyembre 6, 1946.</p>","title":"Servando Castro"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1983-12-06","lat":18.05225,"address":"Sabas Street cor. Asuncion Street, Batac, Ilocos Norte","lon":120.56547},"Q30129474":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"José Rizal (Carson, California) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Philippine National Hero. Born on 19 June 1861. Doctor, poet, writer, educator, linguist, inventor.</p><p>Authored novels Noli Me Tangere (1887) and El Filibusterismo (1891) which bared colonial oppression of the Filipinos. He advocated nonviolent struggle for freedom but was charged with inciting dissent.</p><p>The living soul of the 1896 Philippine revolution, he was executed on 30 December 1896.</p><p>His martyrdom inspired a sense of nationhood that eventually led to the proclamation of the Philippine Independence in 1898.</p><p>Installed in commemoration of Jose Rizal’s 150<sup>th</sup> birth anniversary.</p>","title":"Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jose Rizal","date":"2012-09-29","lon":-118.26048,"address":"801 E. Carson Street, Carson, Los Angeles County, California, United States of America","lat":33.83206},"Q38348379":{"lon":120.98105,"lat":14.5734,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Pedro Gil Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1989","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1892–1948)","title":"Manuel Acuña Roxas","inscription":"<p>Orador. estadista, ekonomista, at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Capiz (ngayo’y Roxas City), Capiz, Enero 1, 1892. Nagtapos ng sekondaryang edukasyon, Manila High School, 1910; Batsilyer sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1913. Gobernador, 1919, at kinatawan ng Capiz sa Lehislatura, 1922; delegado ng Kumbenston Konstitusyonal, 1935: Kalihim ng Pananalapi, 1938; Senador, 1941. Noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, naging Medyor, 1941; at Brigadyer Heneral, 1945, ng Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas. Senador, 1945–1946; Pangulo ng Pilipinas, 1946–1948. Namatay Abril 15, 1948.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Manuel Acuña Roxas (1892 - 1948) Roxas blvd marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Manuel Acuña Roxas","locPhoto":null},"Q41972059":{"lon":120.97708,"lat":14.58234,"address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard cor. Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Rizal's execution site historical marker (Tagalog).jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Pook ng Pinagbarilan kay Rizal"}},"en":{"text":{"title":"Rizal’s Execution Site","inscription":"<p>Jose Rizal y Mercado, Filipino physician, propagandist, writer, and patriot was executed within these hallowed grounds at exactly 7:03 in the morning of December 30, 1896 by an eight-man squad of Filipino riflemen from the 70th Infantry Regiment, the ‘Magallanes’, of the Spanish colonial army.</p><p>Those who witnessed Rizal’s public execution included Lt. Luis Taviel de Andrade, his legal defender during his trial for alleged treason against Spain, and the two Jesuit priests, Fr. Jose Villaclara, S.J. and Fr. Estanislao March, S.J. who accompanied Rizal during his final walk before his execution.</p><p>Rizal’s martyrdom fanned the flames of the Filipino Revolution of 1896 and inspired the Filipinos in their resolute and epic fight for freedom.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Rizal's execution site historical marker at Rizal Park, Manila.jpg","credit":"celine marie castañeda (Wikipedia Takes Manila participant) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Rizal’s Execution Site","locPhoto":null,"date":"1996"},"Q43363516":{"lon":121.23859,"lat":14.51273,"address":"Tomas Claudio Street cor. Tupas Street, Morong, Rizal","date":"1992-05-07","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1892–1918)","title":"Tomas Claudio","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Hannachiever07 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tomas Claudio (1892-1918) historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Tomas Claudio"},"Q23987469":{"lon":120.98852,"lat":14.58093,"address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the park’s entrance.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Completed shortly previous to the cholera epidemic of 1820. Nine of the niches were donated by the City of Manila in grateful acknowledgment of the services of the Dominicans to the victoms of cholera. The mausoleum of Governor General Ramon Solano y Lladeral is inside the mortuary chapel. The remains of the Filipino leader, Dr. José Rizal y Mercado, were interred here from December 30, 1896 to December 29, 1912.</p>","title":"Paco Cemetery"},"photo":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IJVPacoCemetery1.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Entrance of Paco Park.jpg"},"name":"Paco Cemetery","date":"1938"},"Q34125673":{"lon":121.07949,"lat":14.53353,"address":"Felix Y. Manalo National Historical Landmark, Felix Y. Manalo Street, Taguig, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Felix Y. Manalo birthplace historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Felix Y. Manalo","inscription":"<p>Dito sa Bo. Calsada, Tipas, Rizal isinilang si Felix Y Manalo, 10 Mayo 1886. Nagtatag at unang tagapamahalang pangkalahatan ng mga kongregasyon ng Iglesia ni Cristo sa Pilipinas. Unang ipinangaral ang Iglesia ni Cristo sa Punta, Sta. Ana, Maynila, at opisyal na ipinarehistro bilang isang samahang pangrelihiyon, 27 Hulyo 1914. Naglathala ng babasahing Pasugo na naglalaman ng mga doktrina ng Iglesia ni Cristo na hango sa Bibliya, 1939. Nagtayo ng mga simbahan ng Iglesia ni Cristo sa iba’t ibang panig ng Pilipinas at buong mundo. Yumao, 12 Abril 1963. Ipinahayag ang pook na kanyang sinilangan bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, Enero 1986.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Felix Y. Manalo","date":"2007-07-27"},"Q30127147":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"José Rizal","locDesc":null,"details":{"fr":{"text":{"title":"José Rizal","inscription":"<p>[Rizal] vivait dans cette maison quand il publia son roman “El Filibusterismo” en 1891.</p>","subtitle":"1861–1896 Héros National des Philippines"},"photo":{"file":"José Rizal gedenkplaat Henegouwenstraat Gent.png","credit":"Paul Drieghe {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"1959","address":"Henegouwenstraat 9, Ghent, Arrondissement of Ghent, East Flanders, Flemish Region, Belgium","lat":51.05221,"lon":3.72602},"Q37776237":{"lon":120.98507,"lat":14.56459,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. President Quirino Avenue, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1994-03-01","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, Nobyembre 16, 1890. Nagtapos ng elementarya sa Aringay, La Union at sekondarya sa Manila High School, 1911. Nagkamit ng Titulo sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1915. Nagsimulang maglingkod sa bayan bilang guro sa Caparian, Agoo, La Union sa gulang na 16. Nahirang na pribadong kalihim ng Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa ilalim ng panunungkulan ng Gobernador Heneral Frank Murphy at Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor. Nahalal na kinatawan ng Ilocos Sur, 1919; senador 1922, 1931, 1941; delegado sa Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal, 1934; at pangalawang pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1946. Naging pangulo sa pagkamatay ni Pangulong Manuel A. Roxas, 1948; nahalal na pangulo, 1949. Namatay, Pebrero 29, 1956. Ang kanyang panunungkula’y kinatampukan ng muling pagpapayabong sa ekonomiya ng bansa na sinira ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at pagpapanumbalik ng kapayapaan at muling pananalig ng mamamayan sa pamahalaan.</p>","title":"Elpidio R. Quirino","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Elpidio R. Quirino"},"Q44453303":{"lat":15.34898,"address":"Capas National Shrine, Capas, Tarlac","lon":120.54524,"date":"2002","name":"Capas Concentration Camp","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Capas Concentration Camp","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"CapasNationalShrinevjf4286 15.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q28944715":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Labangan sa Borongan (1899 Himagsikang Pilipino-Amerikano)","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Ang Labangan sa Borongan (1899 Himagsikang Pilipino-Amerikano)","inscription":"<p>Dito nagwagi ang mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino ng Samar sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Ramon Serrano matapos nilang salakayin ang mga sundalong Amerikanong nakabase dito, 16 Marso 1900. Ang mga sumunod na matagumpay na labanan ay naganap sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Andres Lobrio noong 10 Hulyo, 13 Hulyo at 16 Hulyo, 1901.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2012","address":"Borongan, Eastern Samar","lat":11.6078,"lon":125.43306},"Q34131366":{"date":"2002","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the museum.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Gusali ng Elks Club historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dinisenyo ni William E. Parsons noong 1907 para sa Manila Lodge of The Elks, isang samahang makabayan, pangkapatiran at pangkawanggawa ng mga Amerikanong mangangalakal na itinatag noong 1902. Ipinatayo, 1910. Pinasinayaan, 1911. Bahagi ng Balangkas Burnham–Anderson para sa Maynila at isang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Amerikano noong panahng iyon. Naging Museum of Philippine Art; pagkaraan, punong tanggapan ng Manila Overseas Press Club; at sa kasalukuyan, Museo Pambata ng Maynila.</p>","title":"Gusali ng Elks Club","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MuseoPambatajf0260 23.JPG"},"name":"Gusali ng Elks Club","lon":120.97718,"address":"Elks Club Building, Roxas Boulevard cor. South Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.57911},"Q37782699":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tejeros Convention House.jpg"},"name":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy","locDesc":"The marker is at the base of the statue of Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy located at the left side of the facade of the Tejeros Convention house.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1869–1964)","inscription":"<p>Bayani at unang pangulo ng Pilipinas. Isinilang sa Kawit, Cavite, 22 Marso 1869. Naging Kapitan Munisipal ng Kawit at kasapi ng Katipunan sa pangalang Magdalo, 1895. Naging Pangulo ng pamahalaang rebolusyonaryo sa Tejeros, 22 Marso 1897; at Republika ng Biyak-na-Bato, 2 Nobyembre 1897. Nadestiyero sa Hong Kong, 27 Disyembre 1897. Dito niya itinatag ang Hong Kong Junta at ipinagawa ang bandila ng Pilipinas. Bmalik sa Pilipinas pang ipagpatuloy ang laban para sa kalayaan, 19 Mayo 1898. Itinatag ang pamahalaang diktatoryal, 24 Mayo 1898. Inatasan si Julian Felipe na kumatha ng \"Marcha Filipina Magdalo\" na kalauna'y naging pambansang awit, 4 Hunyo 1898. Ipinahayag ang kalayaan ng Pilipinas sa Espanya sa Kawit, Cavite, 12 Hunyo 1898. Itinatag ang pamahalaang rebolusyonanryo ng Pilipinas, 23 Hunyo 1898. Pinulong ang kongreso ng Malolos sa simbahan ng Barasoain, Bulacan na magbabalangkas ng saligang batas, 15 Setyembre 1898. Hinirang bilang pangul kasabay ng pagtatatag ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 23 Enero 1899. Pinamunuan ang digmaang Filipino laban sa mga Amerikano, 1899-1901. Nadakip sa Palanan, Isabela, 23 Marso 1901. Yumao, 6 Pebrero 1964.</p>","title":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy"},"photo":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Emilio Aguinaldo marker at Site of Tejeros Convention.jpg"}}},"date":"2011","address":"General Trias Drive, Rosario, Cavite","lat":14.40109,"lon":120.86078},"Q28913903":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Provisional Capitol","inscription":"<p>Constructed, 1910, and enlarged, 1936. This edifice, owned by Mr. and Mrs. Walter S. Price, sheltered Gen. Douglas Macarthur, who escaped injury, 20 October 1944, when Japanese bomb penetrated the roof over his room. Served as provisional Capitol 20–23 October 1944, upon the reconstitution of the Commonwealth of the Philippines, for President Sergio Osmeña.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Provisional Capitol historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Provisional Capitol","date":"1950","lon":125.00426,"address":"Price Mansion, Tacloban","lat":11.24392},"Q41962281":{"lon":120.97732,"lat":14.58243,"address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard cor. Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","date":true,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this spot, on February 17, 1872, Fathers Jose G. Burgos, Mariano C. Gomes and Jacinto R. Zamora, were executed by strangulation for alleged complicity with the military uprising in Cavite on January 20, 1872.</p>","title":null,"subtitle":null},"date":"1998","photo":{"file":"Gomburza execution site historical marker (English).jpg","credit":"Titopao {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"es":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gomburza execution 2.jpg"},"date":"1953","text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Supuestos complicados en motin militar de Cavite, 20 Enero 1872, Padre Jose A. Burgos, Padre Mariano Gomez, Padre Jacinto Zamora Martires de la libertad de Filipinas, ejecutados en garrote vil en este lugar, 17 Febrero 1872.</p>","title":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Gomburza execution site"},"Q47092331":{"date":"2009","locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the bust of Macapagal which is located to the left of the main entrance of the capitol building.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Diosdado Macapagal historical marker (Pampanga Provincial Capitol).jpg"},"text":{"title":"Diosdado Macapagal","inscription":"","subtitle":"(1910–1997)"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"08586jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 35.jpg"},"name":"Diosdado Macapagal","lon":120.68735,"lat":15.02408,"address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga"},"Q24841847":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Kevin Michael Aguinaldo {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tanauan Church.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang pangangasiwang pansimbahan ng bayan ay tinanggap ng Agustino noong Mayo 5, 1584. Si P. Antonio Roxas ang naging unang kura paroko. Natapos ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy at nasa may lawa ng Bombon bago ang taong 1690. Ipinatayo ang simbahang bato, 1732. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinalalagyan nito nang ang buong bayan ay lumubog bunga ng pagsabog ng Bulkang Taal, 1754. Muling ipinagawa ni P. Jose Diaz, 1881, ganap na nasira, 1944. Muling ipinagawa ni Monsignor Mariño, 1948.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Tanauan","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Simbahan ng Tanauan","locPhoto":null,"date":"1991-01-21","lon":121.15331,"lat":14.086,"address":"St.John The Evangelist Parish Church, Tanauan, Batangas"},"Q42919921":{"lon":121.043,"lat":12.35939,"address":"San Jose, Occidental Mindoro","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Pagdaong sa Mindoro","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Pagdaong sa Mindoro","locPhoto":null,"date":"2010"},"Q24034676":{"lat":17.36678,"address":"Our Lady of the Assumption Church, Santa Maria, Ilocos Sur","lon":120.48309,"date":"1982","locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Sta. Maria","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Simbahan ng Sta. Maria.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Sta. Maria","inscription":"<p>Orihinal na itinayo ng mga paring Agustino bilang kapilya ng Narvacan. Naging isang parokya noong 1769 na ang patrona ay Nuestra Senora de la Asuncion. Muling ginawa at nilagyan ng tore noong 1810. Naging pansamantalang tuluyan ng mga misyonerong nagtutungo sa Abra. Binago noong 1863 at ang dalusdos ay pinaligiran ng malalaking bato. Muling ipingawa ni Padre Lorenzo Rodriguez ang simbahang bato.\nSa Bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974 at bilang 1515, 11 Hunyo, 1978, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palantandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","subtitle":null}}}},"Q46518566":{"name":"Church of Cagsaua","locPhoto":{"credit":"Wijo08 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cagsawa Church Ruins.jpg"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the southwestern corner of the ruined church tower.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Church of Cagsaua.JPG"},"text":{"title":"Church of Cagsaua","inscription":"<p>The spiritual administration of Cagsaua from 1587 to 1595 was under the parish of Camalig. An early church was burned, 25 July 1636, by the Dutch who ransacked the towns bordering Legaspi Bay. This Church built after 1724 by Fray Francisco Blanco, O. F. M., was buried by rocks and lava during the eruption of Mayon Volcano, 1 February 1814. The authorities of Cagsaua meeting at Ligao, 6 July 1814, decided to incorporate their town as part of Daraga. The first centenary of the destruction of the church was commemorated, 1 February 1914, with a huge pilgrimage to the ruins where high mass was celebrated.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1954","lat":13.16601,"address":"Cagsawa Ruins, Pan-Philippine Highway, Daraga, Albay","lon":123.70104},"Q23886432":{"date":"1938","name":"Church of Nagcarlang","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Nagcarlang","inscription":"<p>The first Church, which was of light materials, was built by Rev. Tomas de Miranda, O.F.M., who was assigned to this town in 1583 as resident priest. The second Church, of brick and stone, was built in 1752, but was partly destroyed by fire in 1781. A choirloft was added to the reconstructed Church in 1845 by Rev. Vicente Velloc, who built the Nagcarlang Cemeteyr and its underground crypt. Rev. Tomas de Miranda was pioneer in the successful cultivation of wheat in the uplands of Nagcarlang.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NagcarlanChurchjf4012 01.JPG"}}},"lat":14.13656,"address":"Nagcarlan Church, Nagcarlan, Laguna","lon":121.41738},"Q50384010":{"lat":14.56768,"address":"2020 M. H. del Pilar Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98511,"date":"1990-05-26","name":"Felipe Encarnacion Agoncillo at Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Agoncillo marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1859–1941) (1859–1946)","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ang unang Pilipinong diplomatiko at ang tumahi ng bandila ng Pilipinas na buong pagmamalaking iwinagayway ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo sa Kawit, Cavite noong Hunyo 12, 1898 sa pagpapahayag ng pagsasarili ng Pilipinas, ay maligaya at masayang nanirahan kapiling ang kanilang mga ulirang anak na sina Lorenza, Gregoria, Eugenia, Marcela at Maria.</p>","title":"Felipe Encarnacion Agoncillo at Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo"}}}},"Q28858156":{"lon":120.99945,"lat":14.5808,"address":"Plaza Dilao, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the southwest of the Takayama monument.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Takayama Marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1552–1615)","inscription":"<p>Pinuno ng unang pangkat ng mga maharlikang Hapon na Kristiyano na ipinatapon sa Pilipinas noong 1614, nang ipinagbawal ng Hapon ang Kristiyanismo. Mahigit sa 100 kagawad ng maharlikang angkan ng Hapon na naging Kristiyano, kabilang ang Lord Juan Tokuan Naito, at ang mga kagawad ng unang Kongregasyong Katoliko ng kababaihan sa Hapon sa pangunguna ni Priyora Julia Naito, ay malugod na tinanggap sa Maynila ng magigiliw na pilipino na kanilang nakasama sa ilalim ng isang bigkis ng kapatirang Kristiyano. Ang mga Kristiyanong Hapon ay nanatili sa Pilipinas hanggang sa sila ay lubusang mapabilang sa madlang Pilipino. </p><p> </p><p> Ang Liwasang Dilao na kinatatayuan ng bantayog na ito ay gumugunita sa bayan ng Dilao (ngayo'y Paco), ang unang purok ng Hapon sa Maynila.</p>","title":"Lord Justo Ukon Takayama"}}},"name":"Lord Justo Ukon Takayama","locPhoto":{"file":"Justo Takayama monument and historical marker at Plaza Dilao.jpg","credit":"noel Gonong (Wikipedia Takes Manila participant) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":"1992"},"Q36987290":{"address":"Plaza Moriones, Moriones Street, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.61,"lon":120.96686,"date":"1992","locPhoto":null,"name":"Domingo Franco y Tuason","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1856–1897)","inscription":"","title":"Domingo Franco y Tuason"},"photo":{"file":"Domingo Franco y Tuason historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}}},"Q24763827":{"date":"1973","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Balayan, Batangas, noong 25 Octubre 1861. Abogado at Hukom pamayapa. Nagtatag ng masonerya sa kanyang lalawigan. Naglingkod bilang kanang kamay ng Heneral Miguel Malvar; naging katulong sa pagtatatag ng lalawigan ng Batangas noong panahon ng himagsikan. Nahirang na kinatawan ng Lepanto sa Kongreso ng Malolos. Nakaisang dibdib si Matilde Martinez; namatay noong 1901. Ang bahay na ito ay naaging tananan niya at naging tagpuan din nina dr. Jose Rizal, Mariano Ponce, at iba pang mga bayani.</p>","title":"Leon Apacible","subtitle":"(1861–1901)"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Leon Apacible historical marker.jpg"}}},"name":"Leon Apacible","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.91975,"lat":13.87944,"address":"Leon Apacible Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas"},"Q28861668":{"lon":120.9908,"address":"Arch of the Centuries, España Boulevard, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.60838,"date":"1960","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the left post of the arch looking from España Boulevard.","details":{"es":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Rizal arch of the centuries.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Jose Rizal, Alumno de la Real y Pontificia Universidad de Santo Tomas de Manila, Filipinas, 1877–1882.</p>"}}},"name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":{"file":"Arch of the Centuries- University of Santo Tomas.jpg","credit":"Ms.popsie21 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"Q22342220":{"lon":121.3644,"address":"Pila Church, Pila, Laguna","lat":14.23396,"date":"1939","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the columns immediately to the right of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Church of Pila historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Rev. Juan de Florencia, O.F.M. was the first priest to minister to this town in 1578.The first Church and the first Convent were completed 1616. The town was transferred from Pagalangan to the present site in 1800 to avoid frequent floods. The present Church was built at the beginning of the 19th century and the Convent was completed in 1849, both having been seriously damaged by the earthquakes of 1880. A rest-house for the sick Franciscan Missionaries was maintained in this town from 1618 to 1673. The Franciscans established here in 1606 a printing press under the printers Tomas Pinpin and Domingo Loag.</p>","title":"Church of Pila"}}},"name":"Church of Pila","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"PilaChurchjf3816 03.JPG"}},"Q22284212":{"address":"Lipa Cathedral, Lipa, Batangas","lat":13.94106,"lon":121.16368,"date":"1939","name":"Cathedral of Lipa","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: RaMmpage18; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cathedral of Lipa historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The parish of Lipa was administered by the Augustinians from 1605 to the end of the nineteenth century. Lipa, which was located formerly on the shore of Bombon Lake, was destroyed by the eruption of Taal Volcano in 1754, but was reconstructed on the present site. This Church was built under the supervision of the Rev. Benito Varas, O.S.A., parish priest from 1865 to 1894. The Diocese of Lipa was created by Pope Pius X on April 10, 1910. The Augustinians encouraged the extensive cultivation of cacao and coffee.</p>","title":"Cathedral of Lipa","subtitle":null}}}},"Q28927536":{"date":"1989","name":"Site Where Rizal Landed","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Dito Lumunsad si Rizal historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"en":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Site Where Rizal Landed","inscription":"<p>On this beach of Sta. Cruz, Jose Rizal landed at 7:00 o’clock PM on July 17, 1892 to begin the life an exile in Dapitan. With Captain Delgras and three artillery men, they walked through Sta. Cruz street with a “Farol de Combate” to the Casa Real where he was presented to Don Ricardo Carnicero, Spanish military governor of the district.</p>"},"tl":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa dalampasigang ito ng Sta. Cruz, lumunsad si Jose Rizal noong ika-7 ng gabi, ika-17 ng Hulyo, 1892 upang simulan ang buhay-tapon sa Dapitan. Kasama ni Kapitan Delgras ang tatlong kawal ng artilyerya ay naglakad sina Rizal sa daang patungo sa Casa Real. Dito siya ipinakilala kay Don Ricardo Carnicero, ang Kastilang Gobernador Militar ng purok.</p>","title":"Dito Lumunsad si Rizal"}}},"lat":8.65627,"address":"Sunset Boulevard, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lon":123.4192},"Q24189287":{"date":"1939","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cathedral of Naga historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Erected of Padi-an when the Diocese of Nueva Caceres was created by a Papal bull of 14 August 1595. Destroyed by fire, 1768. Construction of present cathedral in Spanish-Romanesque style began by Bishop Bernardo de la Concepcion, 1808. Finished and blessed by Mons. Tomas Ladron de Guevara, 1843. Damaged by typhoon, October, 1856; restored by the Very Reverend Fray Francisco Gainza, 1862-1879. Damaged by earthquake, 1887; repaired by Obras Publicas under the direction of Bishop Arsenio Campo and engineer Ricardo Ayuso,1890.</p>","title":"Cathedral of Naga","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Cathedral of Naga","lon":123.18718,"lat":13.62801,"address":"Naga Cathedral, Naga, Camarines Sur"},"Q24705272":{"date":"2008","name":"Gala–Rodriguez House","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Gala-Rodriguez House.jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute 14 May 2008</p>","title":"Gala–Rodriguez House","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Gala–Rodriguez House, Rizal Street cor. Gomez Street, Sariaya, Quezon","lat":13.96194,"lon":121.525},"Q44354771":{"date":"1973-12-17","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Pinangalanang Tulay Tomas Mascardo bilang pagkilala sa kanyang mga nagawa nang siya'y naging heneral ng 1896 Himagsikan at gobernador ng lalawigan ng Kabite (1910-1912)</p>","title":"Tulay Tomas Mascardo"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Tulay Tomas Mascardo","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.94291,"lat":14.42393,"address":"Tomás Mascardo Bridge, Emilio Aguinaldo Highway, Imus, Cavite"},"Q40318367":{"date":"1984","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Padre Jose Burgos in Cabildo.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Padre Jose A. Burgos","inscription":""}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Padre Jose A. Burgos","lon":120.97387,"lat":14.592,"address":"Cabildo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q37713611":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cape Engano Lighthouse Facade.jpg"},"name":"Parola ng Cape Engaño","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the lighthouse facing the southern entrance to the compound.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Cape Engano Lighthouse Historical Marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Parola ng Cape Engaño","inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Inhenyero Magin Pers y Pers ayon sa plano ng mga parola sa Cape Bojeador, Faro de Punta Capones at Faro de la Isla de Cabra na may tore at mga pabelyon, 1 Hunyo 1887. Ipinatayo, 21 Setyembre 1888. Natapos, 31 Disyembre 1892. Isa sa mga natatanging halimbawa ng arkitektura at nalalabing parolang itinayo noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>"}}},"date":"2009","lat":18.57977,"address":"Cape Engaño Lighthouse, Santa Ana, Cagayan","lon":122.1377},"Q38348252":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose P. Laurel (1891 - 1959) Roxas blvd.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1891–1959)","title":"Jose P. Laurel","inscription":""}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jose P. Laurel","date":null,"lon":120.98128,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Pedro Gil Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.57292},"Q38250202":{"lon":120.9723,"address":"457 Urbiztondo Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59829,"date":"1967-10-29","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna 1866-1899.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna","inscription":"","subtitle":"1866–1899"}}},"name":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna","locPhoto":null},"Q28933344":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, Mayo 14, 1900, ang unang kumpanya ng lakas panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pangunguna ni Kapitan Vicente Roa y Racines at mga kabalyeriya sa pamumuno ni Sarhento Uldarico Akut kasama ang mga macheteros, ay madugong nakipaglaban sa mga sundalong Amerikano ng ika-40 rehimyento ng boluntaryong impanterya ng Estados Unidos na pinangunahan ni Kapitan Walter B. Elliot. Si Kapitan Roa, kasama ang iba pang makabayang Pilipino ay buong kabayanihang namatay sa labanang ito. </p><p> </p><p> Sa mga dakilang tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan ng dating lalawigan ng Misamis, lalung-lalo na yaong mga namatay sa labana sa burol Agusan, ang panandang pangkasaysayang ito ay iniaalay ng sambayanang Pilipino bilang paggunita sa ikasandaang taon ng makasaysayang labanang ito.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Burol Agusan"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Labanan sa Burol Agusan","locPhoto":null,"date":"2000-05-14","lon":124.73852,"lat":8.48813,"address":"Cagayan de Oro"},"Q41328550":{"lat":14.27549,"address":"Old Laguna Provincial Capitol Building, Pedro Guevarra Avenue, Santa Cruz, Laguna","lon":121.41722,"name":"Juan Cailles","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Monument to Juan Cailles in Laguna Provincial Capital, Philippines.jpg"},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1871–1951)","title":"Juan Cailles","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, Rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Nasugbu, Batangas, 10 Nobyembre 1871. Nagkamit ng Teacher's Diploma, Paaralang Normal ng mga Heswita, 1890. Nagturo sa baryo Amaya, Tanza, Cavite hanggang sa pagsiklab ng Himagsikang Filipino, 1896. Umanib sa hukbo ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo at naging brigadyer heneral, 1897. Isa sa mga lumagda sa pagpapahayag ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas, 12 Hunyo 1898. Itinalaga sa Laguna, 1899. Tinalo ang mga Amerikano sa Labanan ng Mabitac, 17 Setyembre 1900. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 24 Hunyo 1901. Hinirang na Gobernador Sibil, 1902-1910 at nahalal na Gobernador ng Laguna, 1915-1925; naging kinatawan ng Lalawigan ng Mountain Province, 1926-1931; muling nahalal na Gobernador ng Laguna, 1932-1938; pangalawang tagapangulo ng Board of Pensions for Veterans, 1940. Inspektor Heneral ng Philippine Veterans Administration, 1941. Yumao 28 Hunyo 1951.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Juan Cailles historical marker, Laguna, Philippines.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the pedestal of the monument of Juan Cailles.","date":"2013"},"Q42931575":{"lon":122.09186,"address":"Torrijos, Marinduque","lat":13.35847,"date":"2000-09-13","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Labanan sa Pulang Lupa","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"name":"Ang Labanan sa Pulang Lupa","locPhoto":null},"Q22236841":{"date":"1983","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Leon Ma. Guerrero (1915–1982).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1915–1982)","inscription":"<p>Diplomatiko, manunulat, mamamahayag, abogado, at makabayan. Ipinanganak noong Marso 24, 1915 sa Ermita, Maynila. Nagtapos ng A.B., summa cum laude, Ateneo de Manila, 1935; at LL.B., summa cum laude, Philippine Law School, 1939. Pangalawang Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Suliraning Panlabas, 1954. Embahador sa Great Britain, Denmark, Sweden, Norway, Finland, Germany, Spain, India, Nepal, Afghanistan, Mexico, Guatemala, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, Honduras, Panama, El Salvador, Ecuador, Venezuela, Columbia, Cuba at Yugoslavia, 1954–1980. May-akda ng nagwaging talambuhay ni Rizal, The First Filipino. Nagsalin sa Ingles ng Noli Me Tangere at El Filibusterismo. Tumanggap ng gawad, Doctor of Humanities, honoris causa, Lyceum of the Philippines, 1971, at Gawad Mabini, 1982. Namatay noong Hunyo 24, 1982.</p>","title":"Leon Ma. Guerrero"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Leon Ma. Guerrero","lon":120.97864,"lat":14.57828,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Plaza Nuestra Señora de Guia Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q24715649":{"name":"Natalio Enriquez House","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Sariaya,Mansion,TownCenterjf0265 15.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Natalio Enriquez House","inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute 14 May 2008</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2008-05-14","address":"Gen. Luna Street cor. Rizal Street, Sariaya, Quezon","lat":13.96331,"lon":121.52454},"Q41743750":{"address":"Meycauayan Church, Marcos Ira Street, Meycauayan, Bulacan","lat":14.73481,"lon":120.95705,"locPhoto":{"file":"MeycauayanChurchBulacan 08.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Church of Meycauayan","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall on the westernmost portion of the church facade.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Meycauayan","inscription":"<p>The first Church was destroyed by a typhoon in 1588. The construction of the present Church was started shortly after 1668, when the town was moved from Lagolo to the present site. Rev. Francisco Gascueña, O.F.M., who built the belfry in 1800, preached the Gospel in China for six years, and on being exiled from that kingdom out of opposition to his religious teachings returned to Meycauayan. He served this parish for 31 years and died here on November 18, 1831. The Convent was built from 1731 to 1759. Both Convent and Church were seriously damaged by the typhoon of 1882.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Meycauayanchurchjf1238 06.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"1939"},"Q23848781":{"lat":14.29734,"address":"Lumban Church, Lumban, Laguna","lon":121.45922,"name":"Church of Lumbang","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker of St. Sebastian Church in Lumban, Laguna.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lumbang was for a time the center of all missionary activities in Laguna. Rev. Juan de Plasencia, O.F.M., ministered here in 1578. The original Church, of wood and thatch, was destroyed by fire, being replaced by the first stone Church to be built in Laguna, completed here in 1600. A solemn Eucharistic procession was held here on October 9, 1600. The Church was seriously damed by the earthquakes of 1880. A rest-house for sick Franciscan missionaries was maintained here from 1606 to 1618. Rev. Juan de Santa Maria, O.F.M., conducted here in 1606 a regional school, where 400 boys were taught liturgical hymns and the use of musical instruments.</p>","title":"Church of Lumbang","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1939"},"Q25070568":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a small obelisk at the western portion of the park.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Bundok Nagpatong Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"Maragondon, Kabite","title":"Bundok Nagpatong","inscription":"<p>Noong Mayo 10, 1897, sa pook na itong tinatawag na Nagpatong, malapit sa Bundok Buntis, Maragondon, ang Supremo Andres Bonifacio at ang kanyang kapatid na si Procopio ay binaril alinsunod sa pasiya ng hukumang militar ng Pamahalaang Mapanghimagsik.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Andres Bonifacio Mount Nagpatong Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Bundok Nagpatong","date":"1953","lon":120.7176,"lat":14.26271,"address":"Bonifacio Shrine and Eco-Tourism Park, Maragondon, Cavite"},"Q52153517":{"lon":124.74792,"lat":10.37305,"address":"Hilongos Church, R.V. Villaflores Street, Hilongos, Leyte","date":"1994-12-22","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Hilongos","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Hilongos"},"Q24702663":{"lon":122.08428,"address":"Maharlika Highway, Gumaca, Quezon","lat":13.93525,"date":"1982","locDesc":"The marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of St. Didacus of Alcalá.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":null,"title":"Ika-400 Taong Pagdiriwang ng Pagiging Kristiyano ng Bayan ng Gumaca"},"photo":{"file":"Marker San Diego de Alcala Park Gumaca, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Diego de Alcala Park Gumaca, Quezon.JPG"},"name":"Ika-400 Taong Pagdiriwang ng Pagiging Kristiyano ng Bayan ng Gumaca"},"Q23835528":{"lat":14.59248,"address":"Ayuntamiento de Manila, Cabildo, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97331,"name":"Casas Consistoriales","locPhoto":{"file":"Casas Consistoriales historical marker vicinity.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall between the northernmost and the second-to-the-northernmost main doors of the building.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(Ayuntamiento)","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong tahanan ng Cabildo at iba pang pinuno ng pamahalaan ng lungsod ng Maynila. Inilagay ang panukulang bato, 1735; natapos, 1738. Nasira ng lindol, 1863; muling ipinatayo, 1879. Naging luklukan ng pamahalaang kolonyal na Kastila at Amerikano at ng unang Asamblea ng Pilipinas. Sa Salón de Marmol ng gusaling ito pinasinayaan si Sergio Osmeña bilang ispiker noong Oktubre 16, 1907, katungkulang kanyang hinawakan hanggang 1922. Nasira nang bombahin ng hukbong Hapon at Amerikano noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig.</p>","title":"Casas Consistoriales"},"photo":{"file":"Casas Consistoriales historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"date":"1989"},"Q51452915":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Jrr irang soulfinder {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Maria Panganiban historical marker in Jose Panganiban, Camarines Norte.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","subtitle":"(1863–1890)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","date":"1985-02-01","lon":122.69172,"address":"Jose Panganiban, Camarines Norte","lat":14.29029},"Q21529486":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the wall adjoining to the left of the main gate of the house.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lichauco House","inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Commission of the Philippines 21 July 2010</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Lichauco Heritage House marker (cropped).jpg"}}},"name":"Lichauco House","locPhoto":{"file":"0246jfPedro Gil Street Plaza Calderon Santa Ana Manila Schools Landmarksfvf 12.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"date":"2010","lon":121.01108,"address":"Lichauco Heritage House, 2315 Pedro Gil Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58132},"Q36483228":{"lon":121.32257,"lat":14.07147,"address":"Fule-Malvar Mansion, Jose Rizal Avenue, San Pablo, Laguna","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mansiyong Fule-Malvar","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo sa istilong Romantic Classicism ng mag-asawang Eusebia Fule at Potenciano Malvar, 1915; Grand old man ng San Pablo; pinunong mediko, Digmaang Pilipino-Amerikano; Kinatawan, Asamblea ng Pilipinas, 1909-1912; Gobernador ng Laguna, 1912-1914; at kauna-unahang nahirang na punong lungsod ng San Pablo, 1940. Naging pansamantalang tuluyan ng mga kilalang panauhin ng San Pablo kagaya nina Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Sergio Osmeña, atbp. Ipinamana ng mag-asawang Malvar sa kanilang mga pamangkin na siyang nagbili ng mansiyong ito sa National Life Insurance Company, 1966. Nabili ng Philippine American Life Insurance Company, 1988, na siyang gumawa ng pagsasaayos, 1990.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Fule Malvar Mansion historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ian Lopez (Ianlopez1115)"}}},"name":"Mansiyong Fule-Malvar","locPhoto":null,"date":"1991-02-16"},"Q34999670":{"date":"2014","locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Alburquerque","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Alburquerque Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang bisita ng Baclayon sa ilalim ng patronato ni Santa Monica. Unang ipinatayo yari sa kahoy at kawayan sa kanlurang bahagi ng liwasan, 1842. Isang matibay at malawak na simbahan ang ipinatayo sa silangang bahagi, 1856. Humiwalay ang kinatatayuan sa bayan ng Baclayon at tinawag na Alburquerque, 1861. Pormal na pinasinayaan bilang parokya, 1869, at sumailalim sa pamamahala ng mga Rekoleto hanggang 1898. Sinimulan ni Padre Manuel Muro ang pagpapatayo ng simbahang bato, 1885. Ipinagawa ang itaas na bahagi ng pader at tore, dekada, 1920. Ipininta ni Ray Francia ang mga larawan sa kisame ng simbahan, 1932. Ang lagusang may nakahanay na mga arko ang nagdurugtong sa simbahan at kumbento na bukod-tangi sa Bohol.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Alburquerque","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Alburquerque Church, Alburquerque, Bohol","lat":9.61102,"lon":123.95751},"Q30138745":{"name":"Battle of Pinaglabanan","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pinaglabanan HistoricalMarker SanJuanCity.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naganap ang makasaysayang labanan ng mga Pilipino at Kastila noong 30 Agosto 1896. Dito unang sumalakay ang mga Katipunero sa pamumuno ni Andres Bonifacio at Emilio Jacinto. Sa labanang ito, na kinasawian ng 153 Katipunero, ipinakilala ng mga Pilipino na handa silang mag-alay ng kanilang buhay alang-alang sa kalayaan ng Inang Bayan.</p>","title":"Battle of Pinaglabanan","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1969-08-29","lat":14.60753,"address":"N. Domingo Street corner Pinaglabanan Road, San Juan, Metro Manila","lon":121.02681},"Q47141910":{"name":"Pampanga Provincial Jail","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"SF (62) Pampanga Jail NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Pampanga Provincial Jail","inscription":"","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2009","lat":15.02342,"address":"Pampanga Provincial Jail, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.68599},"Q37785797":{"lon":120.60177,"lat":14.93833,"address":"San Agustin Church, Lubao, Pampanga","date":"1957","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC Lubao 19.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church of Lubao","inscription":"<p>Founded 1572 in Barrio Santa Catalina. Moved to this site thirty years later due to yearly floods. Architect Fr. Antonio Herrera, Augustinian, constructed this church 1614–1630 out of locally-made brick and sand mixed in egg albumen contributed by the people of Lubao. Occupied 1898 by the revolutionists. Used as hospital 1899 by American forces. Destroyed 1942 by Japanese shelling. Repaired 1949-1952, under the direction of Fr. Melencio Garcia and other priests.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC Lubao 3.jpg"},"name":"Church of Lubao"},"Q52027139":{"lat":14.56064,"address":"Pasig World War II Memorial Monument, Caruncho Avenue, Pasig, Metro Manila","lon":121.0783,"date":"1954-08-29","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"01430jfBarangays Bridges River Avenues Center Buildings Pasig Cityfvf 09.jpg"},"name":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog","inscription":"<p>Ang bantayog na ito ay sa karangalan ng mga anak ng Pasig na nangamatay nang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig upang tayong nangabubuhay ay makakuhang-uliran sa kanila. Ang mga kagamitan at salaping ginugol dito ay buhat sa mga butihing mamamayan ng Pasig at mga kalapit-bayan. Ang namanihala sa pagbabangon ay ang Pasig Civic League. Pinasinayaan noong ika-29 ng Agosto, 1954.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q46540162":{"lat":13.58815,"address":"Batalay Shrine, Bato, Catanduanes","lon":124.31532,"date":"1973-04-27","locPhoto":null,"name":"Dambana sa Batalay","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Dambana sa Batalay"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q37727427":{"lat":15.75859,"address":"San Luis Street, Baler, Aurora","lon":121.56256,"locPhoto":{"file":"Aurorahousejf.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Bayan ng Baler","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the guest entrance of Aurora Quezon's replica house.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Baler Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Lumang pamayanan sa barrio Sabang, bago dumating ang mga Espanyol. Itinatag bilang misyon ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1609. Nasira ng malalaking alon, 27 Disyembre 1735. Lumikas pansamantala ang mga mamamayan sa burol ng Ermita bago lumipat sa kasalukuyang pook. Naging kabisera ng distrit ng El Principe (ngayo'y Aurora), 1856. Pook na sinilangan ni Manuel Luis Quezon, 19 Agosto 1878. Sumiklab ang himagsikan, Iktubre 1897. Naganap sa simbahan ang pagkubkob ng mga rebolusyonaryo sa puwersang Espanyol, 27 Hunyo 1898 - 2 Hunyo 1899, na kinilala bilang mga kaibigan ng bisa ng dekreto ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo, 20 Hunyo 1899. Naging bahagi ng Tayabas (ngayo'y Quezon), 12 Hunyo 1902. Naging kabisera ng sub-province ng Aurora, 1951, at ng lalawigan ng Aurora, 1979.</p>","title":"Bayan ng Baler"}}},"date":null},"Q28923408":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"The Raising of the Philippine Flag in Mindanao","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"The Raising of the Philippine Flag in Mindanao","locPhoto":null,"date":null,"lon":125.54342,"lat":8.94768,"address":"Butuan"},"Q44816101":{"date":"1980","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang tagapayo ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo noong 1898. May-akda ng Pagpapahayag ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas (ika-12 ng Hunyo 1898), at masigasig na makabayan at tagapagpalaganap. Siya ay ipinanganak sa Biñan, Laguna noong ika-7 Disyembre 1830 kina Gregorio Enriquez Bautista at Silvestra Altamira. Nagtapos siya ng panimulang pag-aaral sa Biñan at ng pag-aaral sa batas sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas noong 1865.</p><p>Nagsanay siya sa pagkamanananggol sa Maynila at naging kilala sa pagkakaloob ng walang bayad na paglilingkod sa mahihirap na may usapin. Isang masigasig na kagawad ng La Liga Filipina, Cuerpo de Compromisarios, at La Propaganda. Siya ay dinakip ng mga maykapangyarihang Kastila at ipiniit sa Kutang Santiago nang magsiklab ang himagsikan noong 1896. Siya ay pinalaya pagkaraang ipagtanggol niya nang buong ningning ang kanyang sarili.</p><p>Siya ay inihalal na Ikalawang Pangulo ng Kongresong Panghimagsikan sa Tarlak noong ika-14 ng Hulyo 1899. Itinalaga siya bilang hukom ng Hukumang Unang Dulugan sa Pangasinan. Siya ay namatay sa Maynila noong ika-4 ng Disyembre 1903.</p>","title":"Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista","subtitle":"(1830–1903)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista","lon":121.0844,"lat":14.33864,"address":"Biñan Cultural Center, A. Bonifacio Street, Biñan, Laguna"},"Q24702493":{"date":"1988-09-20","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Casa Comunidad de Tayabas historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Kilalang Casa Tribunal na ipinatayong yari sa mahihinang kagamitan ni Gobernadorsilyo Francisco Lopez, 1776; nagsilbing bulwagang pambayan at bahay tuluyan ng mga manlalakbay. Muling ipinatayong yari sa bato ni Gobernadorsilyo Diego Enriquez, 1831; pinasinayaan at pinanganlang casa de Comunidad, 1835; natapos at pinalamutian ng mga magagandang dekorasyon at mamahaling kasangkapan ni Gobernador de La O, 1855 at nasunog, 1877. Binalak na muling ipatayo bilang ayuntamiento,1890, ngunit hinidi naisakatuparan sa kakulangan ng pundo. Ginawang paaralang sentral noong panahon ng mga Amerikano at muling nasunog noong panahon ng pagpapalaya, 1945, sa mga naiwang pader sinimulan ng pambansang suriang pangkasaysayan ang huling pagpapaayos ng dati'y isa sa pinakamagandang tribula sa buong kapuluan.</p><p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang gusaling ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan.</p>","title":"Casa de Comunidad de Tayabas"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Casa de Comunidad de Tayabas","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.59183,"lat":14.02578,"address":"Casa Comunidad of Tayabas, Gen. Antonio Luna Street cor. J.P. Rizal Street, Tayabas, Quezon"},"Q25069958":{"lat":14.43023,"address":"Bridge of Isabel II, Imus, Cavite","lon":120.94022,"name":"Bridge of Isabel II","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ImusCavitejf0723 07.JPG"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed at the upper portion of a commemorative structure on the balcony on the southbound side of the bridge.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Bridge of Isabel II","inscription":"<p>This bridge was constructed shortly before 1857 by the lay Brother Matias Carbonell, A.R. (1806–1861), overseer of the Hacienda de Imus. A silver medal was awarded the builder by Don Ramon Montero, Governor General of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Bridge of Isabel II historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1939"},"Q31764159":{"lon":123.86522,"lat":9.62623,"address":"Dauis Church, Dauis, Bohol","date":"2009","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Dauis Church Complex historical marker.jpg","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Binubuo ng simbahan, kumbento, bantayan at kampanaryo na pawang yari sa korales. Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang visita ng Baclayon ay naging parokya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de Asuncion, 1697. Ipinatayo ni Padre Joseph Nepomuceno, S.J. ang kumbento na naging opisyal na tirahan ng mga Heswita mula sa Loboc, 1753-1768. Isinailalim sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Ipinatayo ni Padre Santiago del Corazon de Jesus, O.A.R., and kampanaryo, 1774. Pinatibay ang bakuran bilang depensa sa pagsalakay ng mga piratang Moro, 1885. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Julio Saldaña, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1863-1879. Tinapos ni Padre Natalio del Mar na may pintadong obra ni Ray Francia at Canuto Avila, 1919-1923. Pinasinayaan ni Monsignor Juan Gorordo ng Cebu, 23 Agosto 1923. Naging kanlungan ng mga madre ng Holy Spirit ng Tagbilaran ang kumbento noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Itinalaga bilang Shrine of Our Lady of Assumption, 15 Agosto 2004. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang Neo-Gothic at Neo-Classic. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>","title":"Dauis Church Complex"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dauis Church Complex"},"Q43305624":{"lat":14.73248,"address":"J. P. Rizal Street cor. A. Bonifacio Street, Rodriguez, Rizal","lon":121.14521,"name":"Licerio I. Geronimo","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"SanMaeojf5812 07.JPG"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal where the statue of Licerio Gerónimo stands.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Licerio I. Geronimo","inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Labanan ng San Mateo. Ipinanganak Agosto 27, 1855, Sampaloc, Maynila. Puno, Kapulungang Katipunan ng Wawa, Montalban, tagapagtatag, Katipunan sa San Mateo at Marikina. Napaurong ang mga Kastila na sumalakay sa puwersa ni Heneral Aguinaldo sa Bundok Puray. Nahirang na medyor heneral ng dibisyon nakatalaga sa San Mateo, 1898; komandante heneral ng Ikatlong Sona Militar ng lalawigan ng Maynila, 1899. Buong tapang na nakipaglaban kasama ang kanyang mga Tiradores de la Muerte sa Labanan ng San Mateo kung saan napatay niya si Heneral Henry Lawton at iba pang opsiyal na Amerikano. Sinundan ito ng mga pagsalakay sa iba’t-ibang himpilan ng mga Amerikano sa Bulakan, Rizal at mga karatig bayan ng Maynila. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 1901. Nagtrabaho sa Konstabularyo ng Pilipinas bilang 4th class inspector, Hunyo 1, 1902. Naging 3rd lieutenant at inspector, Disyembre 23, 1902. Namatay, Enero 16, 1924.</p>","subtitle":"(1855–1924)"},"photo":{"file":"SanMaeojf5812 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"1992"},"Q28933375":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa Burol ng Makahambus","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Burol ng Makahambus","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, Hunyo 4, 1900, ang hukbong panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pangunguna ni Tenyente Cruz Taal na nasa ilalim ng pamumuno ni Kol. Apolinar Velez y Ramos ay nagwagi sa kanilang madugong pakikipaglaban sa mga sundalong Amerikano na kabilang sa ika-40 impanteryang pinamumunuan ni Kapitan Thomas Miller at ng dagdag na pangkat na pinangungunahan ni Kapitan Walter B. Elliot. Ang pagkatalong ito ng mga Amerikano sa labanan sa Makahambus ay bunga ng mahusay na pamamaraan at disiplina sa sarili ng mga nagtantanggol na mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino. Umani ang mga Pilipino ng paghanga mula sa mga Amerikano, dahil sa kanilang ginawang pakikitungo sa mga bihag ng digma.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2000-06-07","lat":8.37887,"address":"Macahambus Cave, Cagayan de Oro","lon":124.60974},"Q34998485":{"date":"2006","name":"Ang Sandugo","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Ang Sandugo historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa look ng Hinawanan, Loay, naganap ang sandugo sa pagitan nina Miguel Lopez de Legazpi at Datu Sikatuna ng Bohol sa loob ng barkong San Pedro ng Espanya, 25 Marso 1565. Isinagawa sa pamamagitan ng pag-inom ng alak na inihalo sa dugo mula sa hiwa sa dibdib ng dalawang pinuno. Naging simula ng pagkakaibigan ng mga Espnayol at mga Boholano at Kristiyanisasyon ng Pulo.</p>","title":"Ang Sandugo","subtitle":null}}},"lat":9.60579,"address":"Loay, Bohol","lon":123.99882},"Q22340995":{"date":"1960","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"José Rizal historical marker in Calamba Church baptistry.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896","inscription":"<p>Si José Rizal ay bininyagan ni P. Rufino Collantes sa pabinyagang ito ng Simbahan ng Calamba, noong ika-22 ng Hunyo ng 1861, at naging inaama sa binyag si P. Pedro Casanas.</p>","title":"Jose Rizal"}}},"name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16747,"lat":14.21375,"address":"Calamba Church, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna"},"Q28878079":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical marker of Andres Bonifacio in Davao City.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"title":"Andres Bonifacio","inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Andres Bonifacio","date":"2013","lon":125.49732,"lat":7.01871,"address":"Davao City"},"Q41141358":{"date":"1956","locPhoto":{"file":"Cuenca Ancestral House.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the northern main door of the house.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cuenca Ancestral House Historical Marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"Bakoor, Kabite","inscription":"<p>Sa tahanang ito ng mag-asawang Juan Cuenca at Candida Chaves inilipat ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo ang Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo buhat sa bayan ng Kabite noong ika-15 ng Hulyo, 1898, upang malapit sa mga kalaban sa Maynila. Nanatili rito hanggang sa malipat sa Malolos, Bulakan noong ika-10 ng Setyembre 1898 noong ika-23 ng Enero 1899 ay itinatag doon ang Unang Republika Pilipina.</p>","title":"Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo"}}},"lat":14.45962,"address":"Cuenca Ancestral House, Bacoor, Cavite","lon":120.94281},"Q23677499":{"date":"2010-12-02","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)","inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa panulukan ng Calle Jakosalem at Cuenco sa Lungsod ng Cebu bilang pangatlong sangay ng B.P.I. sa labas ng Maynila, 1924. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang gusali na ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni Juan M. Arellano, 1941. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga puwersang Hapones noong panahon ng digmaan, 1942–1945. Ipinaayos, 1947. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 24 Setyembre 1991.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Marker history Bank of the Philippine Islands Cebu Main.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)","lon":123.90243,"lat":10.29353,"address":"BPI Cebu Main branch, Cebu City"},"Q31770524":{"lat":9.95945,"address":"Dagohoy Monument, Danao, Bohol","lon":124.18406,"name":"In Memory of Francisco Dagohoy","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Filipino patriot, who established an independent government for the island of Bohol during the long and successful rebellion, 1744–1829, on this site, between Inabangan and Talibon.</p>","title":"In Memory of Francisco Dagohoy","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Dagohoy Monument marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"date":"1955"},"Q24054361":{"lon":120.98967,"lat":14.59943,"address":"Saint Rita College, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>This Beaterio dates from 1719. The religious habit was given to the first two Religious Sisters Dionisia and Cecilia Talampas Constancia by the Rev. Diego de San Jose, O.R.S.A., on July 16, 1725. The Beaterio became a teaching institution in June, 1907. The congregations of Madres Recoletas in Labrea, Brazil, and Catequistas Agustinas de Cristo Rey in Kweitehfu, China, are affiliated with it by decrees of the Holy See.</p>","title":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall of St. Rita College facing the street and near the vehicular entrance to San Sebastian Church.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09587jfBeaterio Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas Quiapo Manilafvf 05.jpg"},"name":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas","date":"1939"},"Q31766805":{"date":"2009","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Dauis","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang visita ng Baclayon; Naging parokya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de Asuncion, 1697. Ipinamahal sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Julio Saldaña, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1863-1879. Ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Natalio del Mar, 1919-1923. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia at Canuto Avila ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan. Pinasinayaan ni Monsignor Juan Gorordo ng Cebu, 23 Agosto 1923. Itinalaga bilang Shrine of Our Lady of Assumption, 15 Agosto 2004. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang Neo-Gothic at Neo-Classic. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Dauis church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Dauis","lon":123.86509,"lat":9.62549,"address":"Dauis Church, Dauis, Bohol"},"Q37324123":{"date":"1936","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"San Fernando de Dilao Church, Paco historical marker (English) (cropped).jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first chapel built in 1599–1601, and damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1603, was repaired by Archdean Francisco Gomez Arellano. The chapel gave way to a church built in 1809–1914 under the supervision of Bernardo de la Concepcion Perdigon, O.F.M., afterward Bishop of Nueva Caceres. The church was damaged by the earthquakes of 1852 and 1881, and destroyed by fire on February 5, 1899. The present church was solemnly blessed on April 29, 1934.</p>","title":"Church of Dilao–Paco"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church.","name":"Church of Dilao–Paco","locPhoto":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IJVPacoChurch3.jpg"},"lon":120.99492,"lat":14.57933,"address":"Paco Church, 1521 Paz Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q45161681":{"lon":123.90367,"lat":10.29797,"address":"Colon Street cor. Mabini Street, Cebu City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Joannerfabregas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Colon Street Historical Marker.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Daang Colon","inscription":"<p>Ang daang Colon, kilala rin bilang Parian, ang pinakamatandang daan sa Pilipinas. Ipinatayo ng mga Kastila na dumating sa Cebu noong 1565 lulan ng plotang binubuo ng mga sasakyang-dagat na San Pedro, San Pablo at San Juan sa pamumuno ni Miguel Lopez de Legazpi.</p>"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Daang Colon","locPhoto":null,"date":"1961-10-16"},"Q22341168":{"lat":14.17875,"address":"Los Baños Church, Palis Street, Los Baños, Laguna","lon":121.22186,"date":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Los Baños","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Hospital Chapel dedicated to Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception used in the absence of a Church from 1613 to 1727. Destroyed by fire, chapel was replaced by a Church structure made of bamboo and nipa. Church of stone on its present site erected about 1790 under the direction of Fr. Domingo Mateo, construction of belfry, sacristy, and tile roofing supervised by Fr. Manuel Amat, 1852; Convent and tower destroyed by earthquake, 1863; Repairs made during the administration of Frs. Manuel Rodriguez and Gilberto Martin, 1880.</p>","title":"Church of Los Baños","subtitle":null}}}},"Q51221948":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Sa mga Bayani ng Lungsod ng Maynila","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"SaMgaBayaniNgLungsodNgMaynila HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"}}},"name":"Sa mga Bayani ng Lungsod ng Maynila","locPhoto":null,"date":"1993-02-03","lon":120.9819,"lat":14.58801,"address":"Manila City Hall, Taft Avenue cor. Antonio Villegas Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q30130018":{"lon":150.79218,"address":"Rizal Park, Anthony Drive, Rosemeadow, City of Campbelltown, Sydney, City of Sydney, Australia","lat":-34.10127,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Philippine National Hero. Born on 19 June 1861. Doctor, poet, writer, educator, linguist, inventor.</p><p>Authored novels Noli Me Tangere (1887) and El Filibusterismo (1891) which bared colonial oppression of the Filipinos. He advocated nonviolent struggle for freedom but was charged with inciting dissent.</p><p>The living soul of the 1896 Philippine revolution, he was executed on 30 December 1896.</p><p>His martyrdom inspired a sense of nationhood that eventually led to the proclamation of the Philippine Independence in 1898.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Jose Rizal","date":"2012-10-26"},"Q38446821":{"name":"Ramon Magsaysay","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"text":{"tl":{"subtitle":"(1907–1957)","inscription":"<p>Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas</p>","title":"Ramon Magsaysay"},"en":{"inscription":"<p>President of the Republic of the Philippines (1953–1957)</p>","title":"Ramon Magsaysay","subtitle":"(1907–1957)"}},"photo":{"file":"Ramon Magsaysay (1907 - 1957) Roxas blvd.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"date":"2007","lat":14.57171,"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Dr. J. Quintos Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98191},"Q37621078":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the southern end of the northbound side of Soriano Bridge along the Manila–Cavite Road.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"Nobeleta, Kabite","title":"Labanan sa Kalero","inscription":"<p>Sa tulay na ito naganap ang isang mahigpit na labanan noong ika-10 ng Nobyembre, 1896. Mahigit sa 400 na kawal ni Heneral Diego de Los Rios ng pamahalaang Kastila ang napatay ng mga magigiting na manghihimagsik ng sangguniang Magdiwang sa pamumuno ni Koronel Luciano San Miguel at sa tulong ng matibay na Tanggulang Blg. 2.</p><p>Nagtagumpay ang mga Magdiwang sa pamomook na ito.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"BattleofNoveletajf3101 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Labanan sa Kalero","locPhoto":{"file":"BattleofNoveletajf3112 02.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":"1983","lon":120.87907,"address":"Manila–Cavite Road, Noveleta, Cavite","lat":14.44147},"Q28855086":{"address":"Bernardino Jalandoni Museum, Silay, Negros Occidental","lat":10.80186,"lon":122.97731,"date":"1993","name":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"ClaireMRA {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 3 dated April 6, 1993 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","title":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House"}}}},"Q43325425":{"address":"United Nations Avenue cor. San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58339,"lon":120.98646,"date":"2017-08-07","name":"Punong Himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang unang pulisyang sibil ng Maynila sa bisa ng proklamasyon ni Gobernador William H. Taft, 5 Agosto 1901. Nagsilbing mga punong himpilan ang Escuela Municipal, Intramuros, 1901–1904; Bulwagang Lungsod ng Maynila, 1904–1946; Lumang Kulungan ng Bilibid, 1946–1949; at ang kasalukuyang himpilan mula 1949. Itinayo ang gusaling ito bilang South Police Station bago ang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; pinagkublian ng hukbong Hapones at naging lugar ng matinding labanan, 14–20 Pebrero 1945; at isinaayos sa pamamagitan ng Philippine Rehabilitation Act at itinalagang punong himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila, 1949.</p>","title":"Punong Himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila","subtitle":null},"photo":null}}},"Q25160366":{"date":"2010","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo","inscription":"<p>Dating Casa Real na yari sa kahoy at bato noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Naging kapitolyo nang itinatag ang Pamahalaang Sibil ng lalawigan ng Iloilo, 11 Abril 1901. Martin T. Delgado, Rebolusyonaryo, Unang Gobernador, 1901-1904. Ginamit ng mga pwersang Hapones noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1942-1945. Isinaayos ang ilang bahagi ng gusali, mga taong 1960's. Muling ipinaayos matapos masunog ang gusali, 4 Nobyembre 1998. Naging sentro sa pagtataguyod ng lalawigan ng Iloilo, 1901-2001.</p>"}}},"name":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.569,"lat":10.70183,"address":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo, City Proper, Iloilo City"},"Q30087446":{"lat":14.60462,"address":"Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan, Metro Manila","lon":121.03054,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"El Deposito historical marker in Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan City.jpg"},"name":"“El Deposito”","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"“El Deposito”","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito itinayo ng mga Kastila ang tinggalan ng tubig na may lawak na dalawang ektarya at may lalim na dalawandaang talampakan. Dito naganap ang labanan noong ika-30 ng Agosto, 1886. Ginamit hanggang noong panahon ng Amerikano nang itayo ang tinggalan ng tubig sa San Juan at ang salaan ng tubig sa Balara na pinamahalaan ng dating Metropolitan Water District.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"El Deposito NHCP historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main steps of the Pinaglabanan Shrine.","date":"1972-08-30"},"Q29018396":{"name":"Lumang Simbahan ng Palapag","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Lumang Simbahan ng Palapag","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita bilang Misyon ng Cabo de Espiritu Santo sa Hilagang Samar sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion, 1605. Ipinatayo ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy at nipa. Dito nagsimula ang himagsikan ni Agustin Sumuroy na lumaganap sa ibang bahagi ng Samar at Leyte, 1 Hunyo 1649. Tinapos ni Ignacio Alcina, S.J. ang simbahang may hugis krus, kumbento at kuta na yari sa korales at bato bilang tanggulan sa mga pirata, 1663. Dito tumuloy ang mga Heswita, Pransiskano, at Dominikano na lulan ng galyong \"Concepcion\" na dumaong sa Palapag, 1666. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1768-1941. Huling ginamit nang matapos ang bagong simbahan, mga taong 1970. Ipinatayo sa harapan nito ang malaking krus bilang alaala sa ika-400 na taong pagkakatatag ng Kristyanismo sa Hilagang Samar, 1995.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Palapag Church Ruins historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"2010","lat":12.54536,"address":"Palapag Church, Palapag, Northern Samar","lon":125.11556},"Q24844845":{"lon":120.73597,"lat":13.9405,"address":"Balayan, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1863–1947)","title":"Sixto Castelo Lopez","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak, Abril 6, 1863 sa Balayan, Batangas kina Natalio Lopez at Maria Castelo. Nagsimulang mag-aral sa pampublikong paaralan ng Balayan, 1875; pagkaraan, Ateneo Municipal, Manila; pagkatapos ay sumailalim siya sa pagtuturo ni Dr. Cipriano Gonzales; San Juan de Letran, 1882; at sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, kung saan ay nagtapos siya ng sekundaryang edukasyon noong 1884. Tagahanga at kaibigan ni Dr. Jose Rizal. Naging kalihim ni Ambassador Plenipontentiary Felipe Agoncillo. Isa sa ilang Pilipino na di sumumpa ng katapatan sa Estados Unidos. Kusang ipinatapon ang sarili sa Estados UNidos sa loob ng 25 taon. Ginugol ang nalalabing buhay sa kanyang bukid sa Balayan namatay, Marso 3, 1947.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Sixto Castelo Lopez","date":"1993-03-13"},"Q28923203":{"date":"1981","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Hen. Paulino Santos","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Camiling, Tarlac, noong Hunyo 22, 1890 kina Remigio Santos at Rosa Torres. Nagtapos bilang balidiktoryan sa Akademya Militar ng Pilipinas noong 1914. Itinalaga bilang pangatlonng tenyente ng Konstabularya ng Pilipinas. </p><p> Bilang komandanteng panlalawigan at gobernador, napaunlad niya ang edukasyon, agrikultura at komunikasyon sa Lanao. </p><p> Naging Direktor ng mga Bilangguan; Nagtatag ng Davao Penal Colony at nagsagawa ng madaliang paglilipat ng New Bilibid Prison sa Muntinlupa. </p><p> Naging unang puno ng Estado Mayor ng Hukbong Pilipino. Patnugot ng National Land Settlement Adminsitration. Sa kanyang masigasig at mabisang panunungkulan, anim na pamayanan ang itinatag sa South Cotabato. </p><p> Namatay sa Kiangan, Mt. Province noong Agosto 29, 1945. Bilang parangal sa kanya, ang bayan ng Buayan (Dati'y Dadiangas) at pinangalanang Heneral Santos na pagkaraan ay ginawang lungsod.</p>","subtitle":"(1890–1945)"},"photo":{"credit":"Thecl2499 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Monument of Gen. Paulino Santos.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Hen. Paulino Santos","lon":125.17171,"lat":6.11178,"address":"General Santos"},"Q28913899":{"date":"2004","locPhoto":null,"name":"Leyte Landing","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Paglunsad sa Leyte historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"title":"Paglunsad sa Leyte","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito sa Palo, Leyte, nagbalik sa Pilipinas si Heneral Douglas MacArthur noong 20 Oktubre 1944 at personal na nanguna sa mabilisang pagtataboy sa hukbong Hapones na nasa Pilipinas and pangulong Sergio Osmeña at ilang kagawad ng nagdestiyepong pamahalaan ay dumating kasama ni Hen. MacArthur at kumilos para sa muling pagtatatag, pagpapanumbalik, at pangangasiwa sa pamahalaang Komonwelt ng Pilipinas. Ipinahayag ng Pambansang Tandang Pangkasaysayan, 2004.</p>","subtitle":null}},"en":{"photo":{"file":"Leyte landing historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Leyte Landing","inscription":"<p>On this spot, Palo, Leyte, General Douglas MacArthur returned to the Philippines on 20 October 1944 and personally led the swift drive against the Japanese forces in the Philippines. President Sergio Osmeña and some members of the government-in-exile arrived with General MacArthur and proceeded to reorganize, restore, and administer the government of the Commonwealth of the Philippines. Declared a National Historical Landmark, 2004.</p>"}}},"lat":11.17213,"address":"MacArthur Landing Memorial National Park, Palo, Leyte","lon":125.01217},"Q43264019":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Nagsilbing pangunahing daungan ng bayan ng Boac mula noong ika-19 na dantaon. Ginamit na pantalan ng mga bapor na naghahatid ng mga pasahero, kargada, at lokal na produkto ng Marinduque papuntang Maynila at mga karatig pook. Ginamit na daungan ng mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino, 1896 at 1898. Itinayo ang kongkretong daungan noong ika-20 dantaon.</p>","title":"Puwerto ng Laylay, Boac"},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Puwerto ng Laylay, Boac","date":"2015-06-04","lon":121.81892,"lat":13.43554,"address":"Circumferential Road, Boac, Marinduque"},"Q41326209":{"lon":121.45621,"address":"Gen. Taino Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna","lat":14.27385,"date":"1982","locDesc":"The historical marker is located in front on the Benitez House along Gen. Taino Street.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Conrado Benitez y Francia","subtitle":"(1889–1971)"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Conrado Benitez historical marker in Pagsanjan, Laguna.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LagunaAjf9944 21.JPG"},"name":"Conrado Benitez y Francia"},"Q24763481":{"lon":120.91964,"lat":13.87953,"address":"Leon Apacible Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Bahay ni Apacible historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Bahay ni Apacible","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng resolusyon noong Hunyo 29, 1976 ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan na binigyan ng karapatan ng Seksyon 4 ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 ang gusaling ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Bahay ni Apacible","locPhoto":null,"date":"1977-10-25"},"Q43354402":{"date":"1940","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Philippine Commission’s First Session in Baguio","inscription":"<p>This is the site of the building where the Philippine Commission held its first session in Baguio from April 22 to June 11, 1904, inclusive, officially initiating use of Baguio as the Philippines’ summer capital. The Commission was composed of Governor General Luke E. Wright, President, and Commissioners Henry C. Ide, Dean C. Worcester, T. H. Pardo de Tavera, Benito Legarda, Jose R. de Luzuriaga, James F. Smith and W. Cameron Forbes. In this session, 74 acts and 273 Resolutions were approved.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Philippine Commission session site in Baguio historical marker 01.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Philippine Commission’s First Session in Baguio","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.5988,"address":"Governor Pack Road, Baguio","lat":16.41054},"Q47037925":{"address":"San Fernando railway station, San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.02682,"lon":120.68666,"name":"Himpilang Daang-bakal ng San Fernando","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Himpilang Daang-bakal ng San Fernando","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Sftrainjf66.JPG"}}},"date":"2004"},"Q46867382":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1873–1898)","inscription":"","title":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","date":"2001","lon":123.64123,"lat":10.10487,"address":"Carcar, Cebu"},"Q36172984":{"date":"1960","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal 1903 Daang San Fernando, Maynila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1903 Daang San Fernando, Maynila","inscription":"<p>Si Teodora Alonzo, ina ni Rizal, ay namatay noong ika-16 ng Agosto ng 1911 sa isang bahay na nakatayo sa pook na ito (ngayo'y Blg. 476-478) at ari ni Gng. Luisa Lichauco.</p>","title":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal","lon":120.97236,"lat":14.59888,"address":"San Fernando Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q36151172":{"address":"Church Among the Palms, Jose R. Velasco Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","lat":14.16757,"lon":121.24037,"name":"Church Among the Palms","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church among the palms historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church Among the Palms","inscription":"<p>Sinimulang ipangaral ng Iglesia Presbiteriana ang Protestantismo sa College of Agriculture at School of Forestry sa Los Baños, Laguna (ngayo'y University of the Philippines Los Baños), at tinawag na Los Baños College Church, 1911. Kinilala bilang nagsasariling kongregasyon ng Manila Presbytery, 1914. Pinasinayaan ang simbahan, Marso 1917; Rev. Charles R. Hamilton, unang pastor. Sinimulang tawaging Church Among the Palms, mga taong 1928. Sumapi sa United Evangelical Church, 1929, at nang lumaon sa United Church of Christ in the Philippines, 1948. Inilipat sa mga Pilipino ang pamamahala ng simbahan mula 1961.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2014"},"Q43633671":{"lat":15.13866,"address":"Rizal Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","lon":120.97096,"name":"Simon Tecson","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simon Tecson","subtitle":"(1861–1903)"},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simon Tecson historical marker in San Miguel, Bulacan.jpg"}}},"date":"2009"},"Q26111317":{"lon":121.13232,"lat":14.57102,"address":"Taytay Church, Taytay, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Taytay historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Taytay","inscription":"<p>Dating yari sa mahihinang kagamitan na ipinatayo ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano malapit sa baybayin ng Laguna de Bay, 1579. Nahiwalay bilang Visita ng Santa Ana de Sapa, 1583. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang pook ni P. Pedro Chirino, S.J., 1591 at bininyagan ang bayan ng pangalang San Juan del Monte. Ipinagawa ang unang simbahang bato sa labas ng Maynila. Muling ipinagawa ang pangalawang simbahang bato na higit na malaki ni P. Juan de Salazar, 1630. Nasira ang bubungan ng malakas na bagyo, 1632; ipinaayos sa pamamahala ng mga sekular, 1768; at sa mga Agustinong-Rekoletos, 1864. Muling nasunog noong Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano, 1899; pinalaki para matugunan ang lumalaking populasyon noong mga unang taon nang 1970's.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the extreme left of the main entrance of the church.","name":"Simbahan ng Taytay","locPhoto":{"file":"Taytay Church historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":"1992"},"Q46993548":{"address":"President Diosdado P. Macapagal Library and Museum, Lubao, Pampanga","lat":14.93936,"lon":120.60034,"date":"1990","name":"Diosdado P. Macapagal","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jf6931Diosdado Macapagal Library Museum Lubao Pampangafvf 22.JPG"},"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Diosdado P. Macapagal"},"photo":{"file":"Jf6931Diosdado Macapagal Library Museum Lubao Pampangafvf 22.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal holding the bust of Macapagal."},"Q44488084":{"address":"Jaro Cathedral, Jaro, Iloilo City","lat":10.72375,"lon":122.55649,"date":"1976","name":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1874 sa utos ng Kgg. Mariano Cuartero, O. P., unang Obispo ng Jaro; napinsala ng lindol noong Enero, 1948 at ipinaayos sa utos ng Kgg. Jose Ma. Cuenco, unang Arsobispo ng Jaro, 1956. Dito bininyagan si Graciano Lopez Jaena, makabayan at mananalumpati, noong Disyembre 20, 1856.</p>","title":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo","subtitle":null}}}},"Q46865828":{"address":"Matilda L. Bradford Memorial Church, 85 Osmeña Boulevard, Cebu City","lat":10.30584,"lon":123.89481,"name":"Bradford Memorial Church","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Bradford Memorial Church","inscription":"","subtitle":"1913"}}},"date":"2013"},"Q43227562":{"lon":121.07691,"lat":14.64007,"address":"Ateneo School of Humanities, University Road, Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2017","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"1916–1977","title":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J.","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J. historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J."},"Q28149890":{"lat":14.40925,"address":"Research Institute for Tropical Medicine, Alabang, Muntinlupa, Metro Manila","lon":121.03726,"name":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Binuo sa panahon ni Haring Carlos IV noong 1 Setyembre 1803. Ang espedisyong pinamunuan ng doktor na si Francisco de Balmis ang nagpasimula ng bakuna laban sa bulutong sa mga kolonya ng Espanya. Naglayag ang Espedisyong Balmis mulang La Coruña, Espanya noong 30 Nobyembre 1803 at dumating sa Filipinas kasama ang dalawampu't limang batang Mehikanong taglay ang bakuna noong 15 Abril 1805. Bilang pagtanaw ng utang-na-loob sa dulot na pansagip laban sa salot ng bulutong, isang bantayog ni Haring Carlos ang ipinatayo at inihandog ng Lungsod ng Maynila sa Intramuros noong 1824.</p>","title":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis historical marker 1.jpg"}}},"date":"2004"},"Q41735715":{"lon":120.34734,"lat":15.92568,"address":"Malong Street, San Carlos, Pangasinan","date":"1988","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"SaintDominicdeGuzmanParishChurchjf278.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lunsod ng San Carlos","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Lunsod ng San Carlos"},"Q44353315":{"date":"2008","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1847–1912)","title":"Roman Ongpin","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BinondoManilajf0288 01.JPG"}}},"name":"Roman Ongpin","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97485,"lat":14.59974,"address":"Don Roman Ongpin Monument, Ongpin Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q43375893":{"date":true,"name":"First Shot in Filipino–American War","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"First Shot in Filipino-American War Marker.jpg"},"date":"1941","text":{"inscription":"<p>Here, at 9:00 o’clock in the evening of February 4th, 1899, Private William Grayson of the First Nebraska Volunteers fired the shot that started the Filipino–American War.</p>","title":"First Shot in Filipino–American War","subtitle":null}},"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Unang Putok sa Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito noong ganap na 9:00 sa gabi ng 4 Pebrero 1899 nagpaputok si Private William Grayson ng First Nebraska Volunteers, putok na nagpasiklab sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano.</p>","title":"Unang Putok sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano","subtitle":null},"date":"2004"}},"lat":14.60407,"address":"Silencio Street cor. Sociego Street, Santa Mesa, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":121.01535},"Q35096899":{"lon":123.96282,"address":"Tubigon Church, Tubigon, Bohol","lat":9.95045,"date":"2015","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Tubigon","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Tubigon"},"Q42889907":{"address":"Santiago Apostol Church, Gov. Padilla Road cor. P. Vergel de Dios Street, Plaridel, Bulacan","lat":14.88585,"lon":120.85978,"date":"1961","name":"Simbahan ng Quingua","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"PlaridelChurchjf8188 32.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":"(Plaridel, Bulacan)","title":"Simbahan ng Quingua","inscription":""}}}},"Q28865725":{"date":"2003","locPhoto":null,"name":"Henson-Hizon House","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Henson-Hizon House","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"lat":15.0262,"address":"Henson-Hizon House, V. Tiomico Street, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.69013},"Q28874593":{"lon":4.34736,"lat":50.8433,"address":"42 Rue Philippe de Champagne, Brussels, Brussels-Capital Region, Belgium","locDesc":null,"details":{"fr":{"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Heros National des Philippines</p><p>Habitait dan cette maison lorsqu’il ecrivit son roman ‘El Filibusterismo’ en 1890–1891</p>","subtitle":"1861–1896"},"photo":{"credit":"Michel wal {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker in Brussels, Belgium.jpg"}}},"name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":null,"date":"2007"},"Q40314230":{"lat":14.58743,"address":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia, Santa Lucia Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97481,"name":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Santa Lucia Barracks historical marker in Intramuros, Manila.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"text":{"subtitle":"(Santa Lucia Barracks)","title":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia","inscription":""}}},"date":"1990-08-04"},"Q37784067":{"lat":18.51211,"address":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse, Burgos, Ilocos Sur","lon":120.59758,"name":"Ang Parola ng Cape Bojeador","locPhoto":{"file":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse, Burgos, Ilocos Norte.JPG","credit":"Ma. Isabel Sheila Solidum {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the entrance of the first floor pavilion of the lighthouse complex.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Popodiaz {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse Historical Marker (cropped).jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Inhenyero Magin Pers y Pers, 1887. Isinaayos at natapos ng Servicio de Faros sa ilalim ni Inhenyero Guillermo Brockman, 1890. Itinayo bilang Faro de Primera Orden na may tore at mga pabelyon sa burol na Vigia de Nagparitan ng bayan ng Burgos. Nagsilbing gabay-tanglaw sa mga sasakyang pandagat mula 1892 hanggang sa kasalukuyan. Natatanging halimbawa ng parola at arkitektura ng ikalabinsiyam na dantaon. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandang Pangkasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Agosto 2004, at Pambansang Yamang Pangkalinangan ng Pambansang Museo, 20 Hunyo 2005.</p>","title":"Ang Parola ng Cape Bojeador"}}},"date":"2005"},"Q41337041":{"address":"Santa Ana Church, Pedro Gil Street cor. New Panaderos Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.5821,"lon":121.01362,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"0819jfSanta Ana Church Main Right Facade Statue Exterior Patio Manilafvf 14.jpg"},"name":"Church of Santa Ana","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the western wall at the base of the church’s bell tower.","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>First Franciscan Mission established outside Manila, in 1578. Present Church built under the supervision of Vicente Ingles, O.F.M. Cornerstone laid on September 12, 1720, by Francisco De la Cuesta, Archbishop of Manila and acting Governor of the Philippines.</p>","title":"Church of Santa Ana","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church of Santa Ana (Manila) historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1936"},"Q22340926":{"lat":14.21373,"address":"Rizal Shrine, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna","lon":121.16669,"date":"1951","name":"Birthplace of Jose Rizal","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Calambajf2779 13.JPG"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main door of the house.","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Restored by Executive Order No. 145 of President Elpidio Quirino with funds mainly contributed by school children of the Philippines. Inaugurated, 1950. Architect: Juan F. Nakpil.</p>","title":"Birthplace of Jose Rizal","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Birthplace of José Rizal historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q51901440":{"lat":13.77206,"address":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse, Calatagan, Batangas","lon":120.65303,"date":"2018","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse Facade.jpg"},"name":"Parola ng Cape Santiago","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main door of the lighthouse building.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kilala bilang Faro de Cabo Santiago. Unang siniyasat at ipinanukala ni Margin Pers y Pers, 1887. Itinayo ng Aldecoa y Cia na yari sa ladrilyo batay sa disenyo ni Guillermo Brockman, 1890. Nagsilbing gabay ng mga naglalayag sa daungan ng Maynila</p>","title":"Parola ng Cape Santiago","subtitle":null}}}},"Q28923507":{"lat":9.79104,"address":"Surigao, Surigao del Norte","lon":125.49334,"name":"Pook ng Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao","locPhoto":{"file":"Surigao City Hall and Flagpole.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the flagpole in front of the Surigao City Hall.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa Casa Real ng bayan ng Surigao, ang kabisera ng lalawigan ng Surigao (dating Caraga), si Alejandro \"Jantoy\" Gonzalez, pangulo ng Panlalawigang Hunta ng Surigao, at ang iba pang mga pinuno ng Ikatlong Distrito ng Mindanao, ay opisal na itinaas sa kauna-unahang pagkakataon, noong umaga ng Disyembre 26, 1898, ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao. Ay opisyal na itinaas sa kauna unahang pagkakataon noong umaga ng Disyembre 26, 1898 ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao.</p>","title":"Pook ng Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao"}}},"date":"2000"},"Q24817337":{"date":"1985-12-08","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Taal, Batangas, 13 Mayo 1852. Tinawag na Aling Eriang at itinuring na isang bayani ng himagsikan noong 1896, dahil sa kanyang tulong na moral at materyal sa mga manghihimagsik. Ang kanyang bahay ay nagsilbing punong himpilan noong panahon ng himagsikan. Ipinagkaloob niya ang kanyang karapatan sa sasakyang pandagat na \"Bulusan\" na ginawang sasakyang pandigma ng mga manghihimagsik. Namatay 28 Setyembre 1929.</p>","title":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio","subtitle":"(1852–1929)"},"photo":{"file":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"name":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.92104,"lat":13.88022,"address":"Casa Villavicencio, 33 Calle Gliceria Marella, Taal, Batangas"},"Q24033367":{"date":"1950","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker at the Church of Paoay.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Church of Paoay","inscription":"<p>Parish founded by Augustinian missionaries, 1593. Cornerstone of Church laid, 1704; of convent, 1707; of tower, 1793. Used before completion and kept in repair by the people under the joint auspices of the Church and the townb officials. Inauguration ceremonies, 28 February 1896. Church damaged by earthquake, 1706 and 1927. Tower used as observation post by Katipuneros during the Revolution, by Guerrilleros during the Japanese occupation.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Church of Paoay","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.52112,"lat":18.06161,"address":"Paoay Church, Paoay, Ilocos Norte"},"Q44755886":{"date":"2014-08-08","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a pedestal in front of the Eusebio Villanueva Building.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sentro ng komersyo sa Iloilo na nagbigay daan sa pagbubukas ng daungang nagpaunlad ng pandaigdigang kalakalan at industriya ng asukal noong ika-19 dantaon. Napanatili ang arkitektura ng mga gusaling itinayo noong ika-20 dantaon. Ipinahayag na Pook Pamana ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas sa bisa ng Kapasyahan ng Lupon Bilang 3, 16 Hunyo 2014.</p>","title":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Calle Real, Iloilo City 2.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana","lon":122.57048,"lat":10.69461,"address":"Iloilo City Central Business District, J. M. Basa Street cor. Aldeguer Street, City Proper, Iloilo City"},"Q40176820":{"lat":14.44532,"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","lon":120.90689,"date":"1998","name":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1869–1964)","inscription":"<p>First President of the Republic of the Philippines, 1899–1901, and leader of the Filipino People in the revolution against Spanish rule, 1896–1898 and the Filipino–American War, 1899–1901. Born March 22, 1869, Kawit, Cavite. Became Municipal Captain of Kawit. Inducted into Masonry and initiated into the Katipunan under his chosen name, Magdalo, 1895. Led in the capture of Kawit, Imus, Bacoor and other towns in Cavite during the outbreak of the Philippine Revolution in 1896. His military victories provided prestige which led to his election, in absentia, as president of the First Revolutionary Government during the Tejeros Convention on March 22, 1897. Went to self-exile in Hongkong in accordance with the Pact of Biak-na-Bato and forged an alliance with the United States of America to overthrow Spanish rule in the Philippines. Returned from Hongkong, May 19, 1898 and resumed the struggle for freedom. Proclaimed Philippine independence on June 12, 1898 at Kawit. On this occasion the Philippine national flag made in Hongkong by Dona Marcela de Agoncillo was officially unfurled and the Marcha Nacional which became the Philippine National Anthem was played publicly for the first time. Convened the Revolutionary Congress in Malolos, Bulacan, September 15, 1898. Led the Filipino forces during the Filipino–American War and was captured in Palanan, Isabela on March 23, 1901.</p><p>Died at the Veterans Memorial Hospital, Quezon City, February 6, 1964.</p>","title":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy"}}}},"Q52144885":{"date":"1995-04-08","name":"La Casa de Doña Ana","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ipinatayo ng mag-asawang Pedro Nepomuceno y Villaseñor at Ana Maria Herrera y de la Concepcion ang isang malaking bahay na bato sa estilong neo-classical ilang taon makaraan ang kanilang kasal noong 1842. Nag-iisang yari sa ganitong estilo sa buong bayan ng Lucban ang bahay ay paboritong tuluyan ng mga kilalang panauhin mula sa Maynila at mga karatig bayan. Lalong kilala sa tawag na La Casa de Doña Ana bilang parangal sa butihing maybahay ng nagtatag ng Hospicio de Pobres de Lucban. Isang institusyong kanyang itinaguyod sa pamamagitan ng kanyang personal na pagkalinga sa mahihirap at mga maysakit. Binili ng mag-asawang Marcelo Dealo at Eduviges Veloso, 1946. Muling ipinagawa ng mga tagapagmanang sina Antonio at Milada Dealo-Valde, 1994 at pinanganlang La Doña Ana.</p>","title":"La Casa de Doña Ana","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"address":"La Doña Ana, Quezon Avenue, Lucban, Quezon","lat":14.11405,"lon":121.55541},"Q23886139":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Mabitac","inscription":"<p>This town dates from 1613. The earthquake of 1880 seriously damaged the present Church. Repairs here made by Rev. Antonio de la Fuente. The earthquake of August 20, 1927, left it unserviceable. The image of Nuestra Senora de la Candelaria, honored in the Church, is famed throughout Laguna. Cristobal de Mercado gave it to the Church of Paco, Manila in 1600. In 1615 it was removed to Siniloan; but that same year the founders of Mabitac fought succesfully for its permanent possession by this parish.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Mabitac","date":"1939","lon":121.42623,"lat":14.42529,"address":"Nuestra Señora de Candelaria Parish Church, Mabitac, Laguna"},"Q37309666":{"lon":120.90312,"address":"Bonifacio Shrine, Pangil Road, Indang, Cavite","lat":14.20002,"date":"1963","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1897)","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Limbon, Indang, nagsagupa ang mga pangkat ni Andres Bonifacio at ng Pamahalaan noong ika-28 ng Abril 1897. Ipinadakip ng Pangulong Aguinaldo si Bonifacio dahil sa himaton ni Pio del Pilar na nagbabangon ng ibang pamahalaang mapanghimagsik ang Supremo. Sa sagupaan ay napatay si Ciriaco at nasugatan si Andres.</p>","title":"Ang Pagdakip kay Bonifacio"}}},"name":"Ang Pagdakip kay Bonifacio","locPhoto":null},"Q28927475":{"lat":8.66691,"address":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lon":123.4164,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Where Rizal Left for Manila historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Sa dalampasigang ito noong dapithapon ng Hulyo 31, 1896, ang pambansang bayani ng Pilipinas at dangal ng lahing Malayo ay umalis patungong Maynila kasama ang kanyang pamilya at mga kaibigan, na nagbigay wakas sa mahigit na apat na mabungang taon ng pagkakatapon niya sa Dapitan.</p>"}}},"date":"1998"},"Q23821323":{"date":"1939","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Liliw Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church of Lilio","inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of this town belonged to Nagcarlang up to 1605. The Church and the Convent of Lilio were seriously damaged by the earthquakes of 1880. The reconstructed Church and the Convent were partially burned on April 6, 1898.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Church of Lilio","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.43578,"lat":14.13005,"address":"Liliw Church, Liliw, Laguna"},"Q23805082":{"lat":14.24531,"address":"Cavinti Church, Cavinti, Laguna","lon":121.50741,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Cavinti","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Cavinti historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church of Cavinti","inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of Cavinti belonged to Lumbang until 1619. The first stone Church and convent were built about 1621, but both were seriously damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1939. The present Church was partially, and the convent totally, destroyed by the earthquakes of 1824; both were rebuilt before 1851. The tower collapsed during the earthquakes of 1880, and the walls were badly cracked during the earthquakes of 1880 and 1937.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1938"},"Q43282847":{"lat":13.44856,"address":"Boac Cathedral, Boac, Marinduque","lon":121.84185,"date":"1972","locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Boac","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Boac","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q36597581":{"date":"1939","locDesc":"The historical marker is located just to the left of the main door of the church.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Tondo","inscription":"<p>The first Catholic minister of Tondo was the Rev. Alonso de Alvarado, O.S.A. Tondo was the residence of Lakan-Dula who was baptized by the Rev. Martin de Rada, O.S.A. In the early days its ecclesiastical jurisdiction extended up to Pasig, Cainta and Taytay. Tondo was an active center of Catholic activities among the Chinese. The former convent was demolished in 1662 by Governor Sabiniano Manrique de Lara as a military precaution against the expected attack on Manila by Kue-Sing. The present church was built by the Rev. Manuel Diez, O.S.A., and the Rev. Casimiro Herrero, O.S.A., in the second half of the 19th century. Since the early days the traditional fluvial procession of Sto. Niño has attracted thousands of visitors to Tondo.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ChurchofTondojf1245 01.JPG"}}},"name":"Church of Tondo","locPhoto":{"file":"Tondo Church main door.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":120.96711,"lat":14.60779,"address":"Tondo Church, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q46515773":{"lon":124.01551,"lat":10.31081,"address":"Mactan Shrine, Punta Engaño Road, Lapu-Lapu","date":"1941","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the back side of the pedestal inside an open building on the eastern side of the Mactan Shrine.","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this spot Ferdinand Magellan died on April 27, 1521, wounded in an encounter with the soldiers of Lapulapu, Chief of Mactan Island. One of Magellan’s ships, the Victoria, under the command of Juan Sebastian Elcano, sailed from Cebu on May 1, 1521, and anchored at San Lucar de Barrameda on September 6, 1522, thus completing the first circumnavigation of the earth.</p>","title":"Ferdinand Magellan’s Death","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Lapu-lapuShrine05.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Lapu-lapuShrine05.jpg"},"name":"Ferdinand Magellan’s Death"},"Q24702677":{"lon":121.73264,"address":"Mauban, Quezon","lat":14.18808,"date":"2009","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the statue of Manuel Enverga.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Manuel S. Enverga historical marker (cropped).jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1909–1981)","inscription":"<p>Makabayan at lingkod-bayan. Isinilang sa Mauban, Quezon, 1 Enero 1909. Nagtapos ng Abogasya sa Philippine Law School, 1938. Master of Laws sa Universidad ng Sto. Tomas, 1948. Ginawaran ng Doctor of Laws ng Universidad Central de Madrid, 1950. Nagtatag ng Luzonian Colleges, ngayo’y Manuel S. Enverga University Foundation, 11 Pebrero 1947. Nahalal na kinatawan ng unang distrito ng Quezon, 1953–1969. Nagpanukala ng pagtatatag ng Philippine Coconut administration, 1954. Naging tagapangulo ng house committee on education, 1958–1961, house committee on foreign affairs, 1961–1969. Napiling outstanding congressman ng mga pahayagan sa Pilipinas bilang pangunahing tagapagmungkahi ng panukalang-batas para sa pagbubukas ng kalakalan sa pagitan ng Pilipinas at ng mga bansang komunista, 1966. Yumao, 14 Hunyo 1981.</p>","title":"Manuel S. Enverga"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Enverga Statue.jpg","credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Manuel S. Enverga"},"Q40317563":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NatPressClub HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"National Press Club","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"National Press Club","locPhoto":null,"date":"2006","lon":120.97733,"address":"Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59485},"Q24247737":{"date":"1988","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1869–1930)","inscription":"<p>Hurista, makabayan at matapat na lingkod bayan. Isinilang sa Molo; (dating Parian), Iloilo noong Abril 16, 1869. Nagkamit na titulong Batsilyer sa Sining, sobresaliente, Ateneo Municipal de Manila, 1884; titulo de agrimensor y perito tasador de tierras, 1886; at lisensiyado sa hurispundensiya, 1891, sobresaliente, Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Naging Nanunungkulang Piskal ng Audiencia de Manila, 1894–1895; Sekretaryo Heneral ng Republika ng Malolos, 1898; kasapi sa komite na bumalangkas ng Konstitusyon ng Malolos, katulong na mahistrado ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman, 1899; Solisitor Heneral ng pamahalaang sibil, 1900; unang Pilipinong Abogado Heneral, 1905 at Kalihim ng Katarungan at Pananalapi, 1908. Propesor ng batas sibil sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1916–1930[.] Namatay noong Marso 9, 1930.</p>","title":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano"},"photo":{"file":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano","lon":120.98737,"lat":14.59891,"address":"Nazarene Catholic School, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q46790914":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Casa Gorordo","inscription":"<p>The house was built in the mid-19th century by Alejandro Reynes y Rosales and bought by Juan Isidro de Gorordo, a Spanish merchant, in 1863. Four generations of the Gorordo Family lived in this house, including Juan Gorordo, first Filipino Bishop of Cebu 1910–1932. Acquired in 1980 by the Ramon Aboitiz Foundation, Inc. It was restored and later opened as a public museum. Casa Gorordo has been declared a National Historical Landmark by virtue of National Historical Institute Board Resolution No. 4 dated September 24, 1991.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Casa Gorordo","locPhoto":null,"date":"1998-08-21","lon":123.90488,"lat":10.29997,"address":"Casa Gorordo, Lopez Jaena Street cor. Ballesteros Street, Cebu City"},"Q24049388":{"name":"El Renacimiento","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"El Renacimiento historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1901","title":"El Renacimiento","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito itinatag ni Martin Ocampo ang makabayang pahayagang <u>El Renacimiento</u> na ang unang bilang ay lumabas noong Setyembre 3, 1901. Naging patnugot sina Rafael Palma (1901–1903), Fernando Ma. Guerrero (1903–1907), at Teodoro M. Kalaw (1907–1909). Natalo sa usaping libelo at ang mga kasangkapan ng pahayagan ay ipinagbili upang mabayaran ng ₱60,000 danyos ang Kalihim-Panloob Dean C. Worcester. Ito ang ikinamatay ng pahayagan.</p>"}}},"date":"1973","lat":14.59671,"address":"Gunao Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.9852},"Q51924068":{"name":"Juan M. Sumulong","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Juan M. Sumulong (1874-1942).jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Antipolo, Rizal noong ika-27 ng Disyembre 1874.</p><p>Kalihim sa Morong ng mga naghihimagsik laban sa Kastila, manunulat at manananggol. Naipanalo ang usapin ng <i>El Renacimiento</i> sa sakdal na libelo ng mga Amerikanong militar. Itinatag ang Lalawigan ng Rizal dahil sa pagkakapagtibay sa kanyang panukala na ang dating lalawigan ng Morong at ang ilang bayan ng Maynila ay pagsamahin at gawing isang lalawigan. Hukom sa Pagtatala ng Lupa (1908); Kagawad ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas (1909–1913); nahalal na Senador, 1925–1931 at 1934–1935, at Kagawad ng Komisyon sa Kalayaan, 1930–1931. Utak ng oposisyon na ang patakaran ay ang pagsasabi ng totoo, at pagtatapat sa bayan.</p><p>Namatay noong ika-9 ng Enero, 1942.</p>","title":"Juan M. Sumulong","subtitle":"(1874–1942)"}}},"date":"1974-12-27","lat":14.58719,"address":"Antipolo Plaza, M. L. Quezon Street, Antipolo, Rizal","lon":121.17592},"Q28937549":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ni Arsobispo Gerard Mongeau, OMI, DD, sa Kidapawan, 1960. Fr. William McGrath, OMI, unang rector. Inilipat sa Rebuken, Sultan Kudarat, Maguindanao, 1963. Binasbasan ni Rufino J. Cardinal Santos, 1964. Kilala rin bilang Nuling Seminary. Makaraan ang \"missionary era\" nagpatuloy na tumulong upang makapagpatapos ng mga lokal na pari na maglilingkod sa Archdiocese of Cotabato, Diocese of Kidapawan at sa iba pang panig ng mundo. Naging instrumento sa pagpapalaganap ng Kristiyanismo at pagkakawanggawa sa mga maralita sa Mindanao.</p>","title":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary","subtitle":"Archdiocese of Cotabato"}}},"name":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary","locPhoto":null,"date":"2010","lon":124.27848,"address":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary, Cotabato City","lat":7.25867},"Q41758337":{"date":"1983-04-13","name":"Paciano Rizal","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Paciano Rizal historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1851–1930","inscription":"<p>Nakatatandang kapatid ni Jose Rizal. Ipinanganak sa Calamba, Laguna, noong Marso 9, 1851. Nangilak ng abuloy para sa kilusan sa pagpapalaganap laban sa Espanya at nangilak ng suskrisyon para sa Diariong Tagalog. Nakumisyong heneral ng Hukbong Mapanghimagsik. Inihalal na Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa Pamahalaang Pangkagawaran ng Gitnang Luson sa Bundok Puray, Montalban, at itinalagang Punong Militar ng mga manghihimagsik sa Laguna. Lumahok sa Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano at nadakip ng mga kaaway noong 1900. Namatay sa bahay na ito noong Abril 13, 1930.</p>","title":"Paciano Rizal"}}},"lat":14.1817,"address":"General Paciano Rizal Shrine, Villegas Street cor. Juan Luna Street, Los Baños, Laguna","lon":121.22399},"Q40501131":{"address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58082,"lon":120.97761,"date":"2011-12-30","locPhoto":null,"name":"Rizal Fountain","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating nasa tahanan ni Pastor Karl Ullmer sa Wilhelmsfeld, Alemanya kung saan nanirahan si Jose Rizal nang tapusin niya ang mga huling kabanata ng nobelang Noli me Tangere, 1886. Ipinagkaloob ng pamahalaan ng Alemanya sa Pilipinas bilang tanda ng makasaysayang relasyon ng dalawang bansa at inilagay sa Rizal Park, 30 Disyembre 1964. Isinaayos, 1994. Muling isinaayos bilang bahagi ng ika-150 taong pagdiriwang ng kapanganakan ni Rizal, 2011.</p>","title":"Rizal Fountain"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Rizal fountain.jpg"}}}},"Q52030144":{"lat":14.56624,"address":"Nuestra Señora de Gracia Church, 7440 Bernardino Street, Makati, Metro Manila","lon":121.0431,"name":"Church and Monastery of Guadalupe","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"02516jfChurch and Monastery of Guadalupe Makati Cityfvf 01.jpg"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right side of the church facade.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The foundations of this Church and Monastery of the Augustinian Order were laid in 1601 and construction work was finished in 1629. Nuestra Señora de Guadalupe was chosen titular patroness in 1603. After the Chinese uprising of 1639 this sanctuary served as a seat of devotion for the Chinese. The buildings withstood the earthquakes of 1645, 1658, 1754 and 1863; the masonry roof of the church collapsed in the earthquakes of 1880 and the structure was rebuilt in 1882 by Rev. Jose Corujedo, O.S.A. Site of an orphan asylum and trade school administered by the Augustinian Order for the benefit of the children of the victims of the cholera of 1882. Both church and monastery were gutted by fire in February, 1899, during the early skirmishes between Americans and Filipinos.</p>","title":"Church and Monastery of Guadalupe"},"photo":{"credit":"Ronaldbunag {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Our Lady of Grace Church in Makati. Marker.JPG"}}},"date":"1937"},"Q41212768":{"date":"1972","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the San Francisco Church in Naga City.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng San Francisco","inscription":"<p>Kauna-unahang simbahan sa Naga at isa sa pinakamatanda sa Kabikulan na itinayo noong 1578. Naging tirahan ng misyonaryong Pransiskano. Pinalaki noong 1883; nasira noong 1915 at nanatiling hindi ginagamit hanggang sa maitayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan noong 1957. Sa pook ding ito sumuko sa mga Pilipino ang huling gobernador ng Ambos Camarines noong 18 Setyembre 1898.</p>"}}},"name":"Simbahan ng San Francisco","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.18617,"lat":13.62442,"address":"Saint Francis of Assisi Parish Church, Peñafrancia Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur"},"Q46995411":{"address":"F. Tirona Street, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42925,"lon":120.93704,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Heneral Licerio Topacio y Cuenca","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Licerio Topacio historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1839–1925)","inscription":"","title":"Heneral Licerio Topacio y Cuenca"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1991-11-16"},"Q47141810":{"date":"2009","locPhoto":null,"name":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. “Ninoy”","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. “Ninoy”","subtitle":"(1932–1983)"},"photo":{"file":"Ninoy HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"lat":15.0243,"address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.68657},"Q38406106":{"lon":120.99229,"lat":14.56112,"address":"Pablo Ocampo Street cor. Adriatico Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1991-06-11","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of Pablo Ocampo facing Pablo Ocampo Street.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pablo Ocampo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1853–1925)","inscription":"","title":"Pablo Ocampo"}}},"name":"Pablo Ocampo","locPhoto":{"credit":"Theodore Uy {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pablo Ocampo-B.JPG"}},"Q23854678":{"date":"2003","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the building’s entrance.","details":{"de":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nationalheld der Philippinen, war Arzt und Dichter. Als Reformer und Kritiker der Kolonialregierung Spanien stand Rizal für den gewaltlosen Widerstand und vollendete in diesem Haus seinen stark autobiographisch geprägten Roman, Noli me tangere.</p>","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"José Rizal historical marker in Berlin.jpg"}}},"name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","locPhoto":{"file":"Building where Jose Rizal marker in Berlin is located 03.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":13.38659,"lat":52.5138,"address":"Jägerstraße 71 cor. Glinkastraße, Mitte, Berlin, Germany"},"Q35008459":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Loon Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita, 1753. Inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Augustinian Recollects, 1768. Nasunog ang unang simbahan maliban ang harapan, 1850's. Kasama ang harapan ng dating gusali, muling ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni Domingo Escondrillas, 1855-1864. Ginamit ng mga pwersang Amerikano bilang garison sa kanilang kampanya laban sa mga Filipinong gerilya, 1901. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia, Cebuanong pintor, ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan, 1938. Pangunahing patron ang Nuestra Señora de la Luz o Birhen sa Kasilak at pangalawang patron si St. Joseph the Worker. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2010.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Loon","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Simbahan ng Loon","locPhoto":null,"date":"2010","lon":123.79285,"address":"Loon Church, Loon, Bohol","lat":9.79863},"Q35000752":{"name":"Simbahan ng Baclayon","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito pormal na itinayo nina Padre Juan de Torres at Padre Gabriel Sanchez, mga paring Heswita, ang unang misyon ng Kristiyanismo sa Bohol, Nobyembre 17, 1596. Ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy ay parangal sa Birheng Immaculada Concepcion. Naging ganap na parokya, 1717. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa korales, 1727. Pinamahalaan ng mga Agustinong Recolectos, 1768. Idinagdag ang pilak na tabernakulo sa pangunahing dambana, 1810; ginawa ang binyagan at sakristiya, 1852. Nagsagawa ng mga ilang pagbabago at pagsasaayos ngunit ang orihinal na arkitekturang Neo-Klasiko sa paggamit ng arkong Romano at templo ay napanatili hanggang sa kasalukuyan. </p><p> Sa bisa ng kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng mga kautusan bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 at bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan noong Hulyo 27, 1994.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Baclayon","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Baclayon Church Marker Baclayon, Bohol.JPG"}}},"date":"1995","lat":9.62243,"address":"Baclayon Church, Baclayon, Bohol","lon":123.91215},"Q24837637":{"lon":121.09922,"address":"Tanauan, Batangas","lat":14.10089,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Patriot, statesman, lawyer, political writer, educator. Son of Inocencio Mabini and Dionisia Maranan. Rose from poverty. Joined the revolution becoming chief adviser of General Emilio Aguinaldo. Struck with paralysis, January 1896. Imprisoned by the Spaniards, following October; by the Americans, 1899. Exiled to Guam, January 15, 1901; returned February 26, 1903; Died in Manila, May 13, 1903.</p>","title":"On This Site was Born 23 July 1864 Apolinario Mabini","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Apolinario Mabini Birthplace historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"On This Site was Born 23 July 1864 Apolinario Mabini","date":"1952"},"Q52145038":{"date":"1977","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1815–1841)","inscription":"","title":"Apolinario de la Cruz"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Apolinario de la Cruz","lon":121.54566,"lat":14.14415,"address":"Hermano Pule Shrine, Lucban–Luisiana Road, Lucban, Quezon"},"Q26709080":{"lat":49.47027,"address":"José-Rizal-Straße 17, Wilhelmsfeld, Rhein-Neckar, Karlsruhe Government Region, Baden-Württemberg, Germany","lon":8.75882,"name":"José Rizal","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"de":{"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896 Nationalheld der Philippinen","inscription":"<p>[Rizal] verfasste den letzten Teil seines Romans “Noli Me Tangere” in diesem Haus, während er Gast von Pfarrer Ullmer war 1886</p>","title":"José Rizal"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"José Rizal historical marker in Wilhelmsfeld.jpg"}}},"date":"1960-01-04"},"Q24835341":{"address":"Casa de Segunda, Jose P. Rizal Street, Lipa, Batangas","lat":13.93897,"lon":121.16179,"date":"1996-10-20","locPhoto":null,"name":"Luz–Katigbak Ancestral House","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Luz–Katigbak Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This is a heritage house pursuant to the Board Resolution No. 4, series of 1996 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Luz katigbak House historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP), a government agency"}}}},"Q37330895":{"lat":14.57929,"address":"Paco Church, 1521 Paz Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.99492,"name":"Simbahan ng San Fernando de Dilao ng Paco","locPhoto":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IJVPacoChurch3.jpg"},"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"IJVPacoChurch2 (cropped).jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang unang simbahan na yari sa bato ay ipinatayo ni Fray Juan de Garrovillas, OFM, sa patronahe ng La Purificacion de Nuestra Señora, 1599–1601. Sumailalim sa ilang serye ng pagtatayong-muli bunga ng ilang malalaking pangyayari: ang pag-aalsa ng mga Intsik noong 1603, ang pagsalakay ng mga Ingles noong 1762, ang lindol noong 1852 at 1881, ang bagyo noong 1892 at ang sunog noong 1899. Inilipat sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring Belga ng Congregatio Immaculatie Cordis Mariae, 1900. Ang kasalukuyang simbahan na ipinatayo ni P. Godofredo Aldenhuijsen, CICM, ay binasbasan noong Abril 29, 1934. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at muling ipinagawa ng mga taga-parokya noong 1948. Hinalinhan ng mga paring sekular na Filipino noong 1984. Katulong ang mga taga-parokya, patuloy nilang isinasagawa ang pagpapaayos at pagpapaganda sa kasalukuyang simbahan ayon sa mga espesipikasyon ng Ikalawang Konseho ng Vatican. </p><p> Binasbasan ng Kanyang Kabunyian Jaime Cardinal L. Sin noong Agosto 22, 1999. Bilang pagtatampok sa ikaapat na raan ng pagkakatayo ng unang simbahang bato ng Dilao-Paco.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng San Fernando de Dilao ng Paco","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church.","date":"1999-08-22"},"Q43267842":{"name":"Pilar Hidalgo Lim","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Pilar Hidalgo Lim","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1982-05-24","lat":13.44684,"address":"Boac Municipal Hall, Boac, Marinduque","lon":121.84169},"Q41757852":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago","inscription":"","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago","date":"2013","lon":120.96996,"address":"Rizal Shrine, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59441},"Q43301970":{"lon":121.92214,"lat":14.00278,"address":"Iskong Bantay, Iskong Bantay Street cor. Angeles Street, Atimonan, Quezon","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Iskong Bantay","inscription":"<p>The only observation and defense tower existing of the seven built around 1752 in Atimonan, Quezon (Tayabas), to guard the sea coast against pirates. Repaired, 1948–1951 by the Municipality of Atimonan, naming it in memory of Francisco Tandas, popularly called Iskong Bantay, chief defender of the town in the raid of 1872.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Iskong Bantay","date":"1952"},"Q41995081":{"lat":14.79633,"address":"Birthplace of General Gregorio del Pilar Historical Landmark, Camino Real Street, Bulakan, Bulacan","lon":120.8755,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gregoriojf.JPG"},"name":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal for the statue of del Pilar.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar","inscription":"<p>Site in the town of Bulacan where General Gregorio H. del Pilar was born November 14, 1875. Fifth child of Ferrnando H. del Pilar and Felipa Sempio. Intrepid, valiant and youngest Filipino General. Figured most prominently in the defense of Kakaron, Attack of Paombong, Liberation of Bulacan, and in the Battle of Tirad Pass where he died “a soldier and a gentleman,” December 2, 1899.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1948"},"Q46542087":{"lat":12.75175,"address":"Bulusan, Sorsogon","lon":124.13698,"date":"2015-02-07","name":"Mga Moog ng Bulusan","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mga Moog ng Bulusan","inscription":""}}}},"Q50562154":{"lon":123.30823,"lat":9.30554,"address":"Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Jose Rizal sa Dumaguete","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"name":"Jose Rizal sa Dumaguete","locPhoto":null,"date":"2012-02-07"},"Q48123589":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Insular Life","inscription":"<p>Unang kumpanyang Filipino sa pagseseguro sa Pilipinas, itinatag bilang Insular Life Assurance Co., Ltd. sa Maynila, 25 Nobyembre 1910. Antonio Ma. Barretto, unang pangulo. Unang opisina, Lack & Davis Bldg., Echague, Santa Cruz, Maynila. Nagkaroon ng sariling gusali, Plaza Moraga, Binondo, 1931. Nagbukas ng sangay, Honolulu, 1934, Lungsod ng Cebu, unang tanggapang pangdistrito nito, 1938. Sinakop ang Filipinas Life Assurance Co., 1943. Nagpatuloy ang operasyon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1941–1945. Sinakop ang Occidental Life Insurance Co. of California sa Pilipinas, 1954. Unang nagbigay ng segurong pang-industriyal, 1958. Lumipat ang opisina sa Makati, 1963; sa Muntinlupa, 2001.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Insular Life historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a wall to the right of the main entrance of Insular Life Corporate Centre.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Insular Life historical marker vicinity - 2.jpg"},"name":"Insular Life","date":"2010-11-25","lon":121.03838,"lat":14.41909,"address":"Insular Life Corporate Centre, Insular Life Drive, Alabang, Muntinlupa, Metro Manila"},"Q23848774":{"lon":121.4815,"lat":14.36449,"address":"Paete Church, Paete, Laguna","date":"1939","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the extreme right of the church's entrance.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"xtintina {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Paete historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Paete was founded in 1580 by the Rev. Juan de Plasencia. Its stone Church and its Convent, built in 1646, were ruined before 1717. The Rev. Francisco de la Fuente, O.F.M., constructed a stronger Church in 1717, which was later destroyed by the earthquake of 1880. The Church which the Rev. Pedro Galiano, O.F.M., built in 1884, was destroyed by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>","title":"Church of Paete"}}},"name":"Church of Paete","locPhoto":{"file":"Paete church,laguna.jpg","credit":"Leoviernes1 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}},"Q24012063":{"date":"2014-02-28","locPhoto":{"file":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 08 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 15 Hulyo 2013.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the church.","lat":14.48121,"address":"Las Piñas Church, P. Diego Cera Avenue, Las Piñas, Metro Manila","lon":120.98155},"Q43304094":{"lon":120.97865,"lat":14.58532,"address":"Padre Burgos Avenue cor. General Luna Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":"The historical markers are located on opposite sides of the pedestal for the statue of Juan Luna.","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Juan Luna y Novicio","subtitle":"(1857–1899)"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"JuanLunajf0501 03.JPG"}},"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"JuanLunajf0501 02.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1857–1899)","title":"Juan Luna y Novicio","inscription":""}}},"name":"Juan Luna y Novicio","locPhoto":{"file":"Juan Luna Monument.jpg","credit":"Nikond80 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":"1985-12-14"},"Q43302115":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña.jpg"}}},"name":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña","locPhoto":null,"date":"1970-04-16","lon":121.09193,"lat":14.6342,"address":"P. Zamora Street, Marikina, Metro Manila"},"Q31440656":{"lon":124.03158,"address":"Loboc Church, Loboc, Bohol","lat":9.63656,"date":"1999","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of San Pedro Apostol","inscription":"<p>In May 1597, Fr. Juan de Torres, S.J., established the mission of Loboc, which was canonically established as a parish dedicated to San Pedro Apostol[.] In 1602, the present church, built on foundations of the early church which was destroyed by the fire, was started in 1670 and completed in 1734. The convent annexed to the church in a three-storey structure, was the central residence of the Jesuit Missions. In 1768, the Recollects were assigned the former missions in Bohol; they built the octagonal bell tower separate from the main church structure. Sometime in 1858, Fray Aquilino Bon, O.A.R., built the portico in front of the church façade and the octagional mortuary chapel at the gospel flank of the church.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Loboc Church historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of San Pedro Apostol"},"Q50384107":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Engracia Cruz Reyes (1892–1975) historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Engracia Cruz Reyes","subtitle":"(1892–1975)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Engracia Cruz Reyes","date":"1992-07-12","lon":120.9839,"address":"Plaza Rajah Sulayman, Roxas Boulevard cor. San Andres Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.56866},"Q31440620":{"lon":123.88035,"lat":9.62714,"address":"Tagbilaran, Bohol","date":"1941","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>About the middle of March 1565, Captain General Miguel Lopez de Legaspi’s fleet anchored along this shore. Shortly thereafter, Legaspi manifesting trust and confidence in the islanders, entered into a blood compact with Datu Sikatuna for the purpose of insuring friendly relations between the Spaniards and the natives. A few drops of blood drawn from a small incision in the arm of each of the two chiefs were placed in separate cups containing wine, and in the presence of the followers of both, each chief drank the potion containing the blood of the other. Thus, during this period of colonization, a bond was sealed in accordance with native practice, the first treaty of friendship and alliance between Spaniards and Filipinos.</p>","title":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi"}}},"name":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi","locPhoto":null},"Q29018520":{"date":"1987","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating parokya ng mga Heswita sa ilalim ng Obispado ng Cebu noong 1591 at ng tahanan ng Dagami noong 1656. Ipinatayong may matibay na pundasyon ng mga Heswita at inialay kay San Miguel de Archangel. Inilipat sa mga Agustino, 1768, at sa mga Pransiskano, 1795; ngunit pinamusesyonan noong 1804. Ipinaayos at ipinagawa ang tore at kumbentong bato at kubales kasama ang sementeryo at kapilya ni Padre Domingo de Madrid, 1845, sinira ng bagyo, 1880. Pinalitan ang bubungan ng yerong galbanisado ni Padre Vicente Gutierrez, 1894-1896. Naging punong himpilang pangmisyon, sentro ng pagtuturo ng \"Doctrina Christiana, at kuta - panahon ng Kastila; bulwagang pulungan at dulaan — nang pananakop ng Hapon; at pook likasan — noong Liberasyon.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Basey"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Basey","lon":125.07034,"lat":11.2811,"address":"Basey Church, Basey, Samar"},"Q43302397":{"lon":121.23772,"lat":14.51427,"address":"Morong Church, Morong, Rizal","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Morong","inscription":"<p>The Town dates from 1578. A resident Priest was assigned to it in 1586. A fire in 1612 destroyed the town and its first church. Shortly afterwards, the present Church was constructed. Its frontispiece and the belfry were built by Bartolome Palatino, of Paete, between 1850 and 1853.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MorongChurchjf0263 21.JPG"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Church of Morong","locPhoto":null,"date":"1939"},"Q28858149":{"date":"2009","name":"Carlos P. Garcia House","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Carlos P. Garcia House","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Carlos P. Garcia House historical marker.JPG"}}},"lat":9.6414,"address":"Carlos P. Garcia Heritage House, Tagbilaran, Bohol","lon":123.8581},"Q24033382":{"name":"Cathedral of Vigan","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Built in 1641, this church became a cathedral when the seat of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia was transferred from Lal-lo, Cagayan, to Vigan, 1758. Occupied by the revolutionists under Col. Juan Villamor, 1896, and by the American forces under Lt. Col. James Parker, 1899. A chapel of wood and thatch erected on this site, 1574, by order of Juan de Salcedo, the conquistador and founder of Villa Fernandina, after which Vigan was first called, was damaged by earthquake in 1619 and 1627, and by fire in 1739.</p>","title":"Cathedral of Vigan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Cathedral of Vigan.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1949","lat":17.575,"address":"Vigan Cathedral, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","lon":120.38855},"Q23974922":{"name":"Manila Metropolitan Theater","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"MMManilajf2189 02.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Manila Metropolitan Theater","inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang isang Pambansang Tanghalan ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto Juan Arellano. Pinasinayaan noong 1931. Naging tanghalan ng mga artistang Pilipino at banyaga. Nagpalabas ng mga opera, pageant, at dulang Kastila at Ingles na isinalin sa Tagalog para sa mga Filipino noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Nasira nang bahagya noong 1945. Ang gumuhong gusali ay naging tirahan ng mga squatter at pinangalanang Besa Boxing Arena. Ibinalik sa dating maringal na anyo noong 1978 ng Komisyon ng Kalakhang Maynila.</p>"}}},"date":"1988","lat":14.59422,"address":"Manila Metropolitan Theater, Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98032},"Q24033363":{"lon":120.6445,"lat":18.1558,"address":"Sarrat Church, Sarrat, Ilocos Norte","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Catholic Church of Sarrat","inscription":"<p>Formerly named Church of San Miguel in commemoration of the arrival at Sarrat of the first missionaries on the feast of San Miguel, 29 September 1725; Now named Sarrat by the Philippine legislature in 1916, restored the original name of the town, Sarrat. First convent constructed 1769 served as temporary church; Destroyed by fire 16 March 1816; Church and tower were constructed 1779; Another convent was built under the supervision of Father Vicente Berragro and finished May 1817; Burned again 18 October 1882; A third convent was built and completed June 1896.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Catholic Church of Sarrat","date":"1959"},"Q31997939":{"date":"2015","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Labanan sa Zapote historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Zapote","inscription":"<p>Sa lugar na ito lumaban ang mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino sa dalawang labanan upang mabawi ang Cavite sa mga Espanyol at pigilan ang tuluyang pagsakop ng mga Amerikano: una, sa pangunguna ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo laban sa mga Espanyol, 17 Pebrero 1897, na pinagwagian ng mga Pilipino ngunit ikinasawi ni Hen. Edilberto Evangelista; at ang huli, sa pangunguna nina Hen. Artemio Ricarte at Mariano Noriel laban sa mga Amerikano, 13 Hunyo 1899.</p><p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 11 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 9 Setyembre 2013.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the middle of the southeastern side of the bridge.","name":"Labanan sa Zapote","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zapote Bridge looking southward.jpg"},"lon":120.96636,"address":"Zapote Bridge, Aguinaldo Highway, Bacoor, Cavite","lat":14.46395},"Q44508069":{"date":"1991","locPhoto":null,"name":"Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Paaralang San Roque. Ipinatayo sa istilong Gabaldon na may limang dorikong kulumna noong 1911. Pinangalanang Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas, Agosto 11, 1972. Bilang parangal at pagkilala sa ama ng batas na nagtatadhana sa pagiging Lungsod ng Cavite o Batas Komonwelt bilang 546, Setyembre 7, 1940. Pinaayos, 1988.</p>","title":"Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"lat":14.48099,"address":"Manuel S. Rojas Elementary School, Dra. Salamanca Street, Cavite City, Cavite","lon":120.90131},"Q44989612":{"date":"2007","name":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Balanga, Bataan","lat":14.67582,"lon":120.5299},"Q52144871":{"lon":121.55475,"lat":14.11433,"address":"Lucban Municipal Hall, Quezon Avenue cor. Lucban–Sampaloc Road, Lucban, Quezon","date":"1978-05-14","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the northwestern corner of the municipal hall.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LucbanMunicipalHalljf8677 14.JPG"},"text":{"title":"Lucban","inscription":"","subtitle":"(1578–1978)"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LucbanMunicipalHalljf8677 15.JPG"},"name":"Lucban"},"Q24033369":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Guho ng Simbahang Katoliko ng Dingras","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Bakas ng isang magandang simbahang sinira ng lindol at apoy, 1913. May bubong na yero, malaki at matibay na pader. Ang simbahan na may habang 90 hakbang at lapad na 20 hakbang ay isa sa pinakamalaki sa Pilipinas. Nagsimulang visita ng Batac, ginawang parokya ng mga Agustino at inialay sa patrong San Jose; Si Padre Bartolome Conrado ang unang kura, 1598. Ibinalik sa pagkavisita, 1603. Naging parokyang muli bilang sentro ng misyon, 1605. Nasira ng lindol, 1619; Muling ipinagawa bagong nasunog, 1838 at nasira ng kidlat, 1853. Huling ipinatayo ni Padre Ricardo Deza sa paggawa ng 2 polistas buhat sa bawat isa ng 58 cabecerias sa halagang $28, 649.31 piso ng Mehiko, sa tulong ni Alkalde Mayor Camilo Millan, 1879-1893.</p>","title":"Guho ng Simbahang Katoliko ng Dingras"},"photo":{"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"DingrasChurchMarker1.JPG"}}},"date":"1987","address":"Dingras Church, Dingras, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.10274,"lon":120.69871},"Q43267173":{"lon":121.86897,"lat":13.56019,"address":"Mogpog, Marinduque","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"Datum Origin of the Luzon Datum of 1911","title":"Station Balanacan","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Station Balanacan","date":"2011-08-09"},"Q24813571":{"lon":121.1042,"lat":13.8795,"address":"Saint Joseph the Patriarch Church, San Jose, Batangas","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Jose, Batangas Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The foundation of this town, known formerly as Malaquing Tubig, dates from 1765. The church was built by the famous botanist, The Rev. Manuel Blanco, O.S.A., in 1812. The stone bridge over Malaquing Tubig was constructed by the Rev. Bruno Laredo, O.S.A.</p>","title":"Church of San Jose","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Church of San Jose","locPhoto":null,"date":"1939"},"Q28927514":{"date":"2011-07-17","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Sakahan ni Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Binili at nilinang ni Rizal ang sakahan na dating pag-aari ni Calixto Carreon na naging pasyente niya habang nasa Dapitan. Inatasan ang kapatid na si Trinidad Rizal na pangasiwaan ang pangangalaga nito, at lumaon namang inilipat kay Fernando Eguia, mag-aaral ni Rizal at naging katiwala sa sakahan. Ipinagbili ni Trinidad kay Crisostomo Eguia Sr. Saksi ang ibang mga kapatid ni Rizal sa kasunduang panatilihan ang sakahan sa pangalan ni Jose Rizal, 1949.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Rizal Farm historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the Jose Rizal monument.","locPhoto":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Sakahan ni Rizal 1.jpg"},"name":"Sakahan ni Jose Rizal","lon":123.29666,"lat":8.50128,"address":"Jose Rizal Farm, Katipunan, Zamboanga del Norte"},"Q36011972":{"lon":120.98363,"lat":14.56834,"address":"423 San Andres Street cor. Roxas Boulevard, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"The Aristocrat.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula sa isang lumang sasakyang ginamit ni Engracia Cruz-Reyes o Aling Asiang bilang tindahan ng meryenda na lumilibot sa Luneta at iba pang kalapit pook sa Maynila, Hulyo 1936. Dito itinatag ang unang gusaling kinilalang The Admiral Dewey at kinalauna’y pinangalanang The Aristocrat, 1939. Isa sa mga tanyag na kainang nagtampok ng mga lutuing Pilipino.</p>","title":"The Aristocrat","subtitle":null}}},"name":"The Aristocrat","locPhoto":null,"date":"2013-07-04"},"Q43302082":{"date":"1987-11-30","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Museo at Aklatan ng Boac","inscription":""}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Museo at Aklatan ng Boac","lon":121.84006,"lat":13.44767,"address":"Mercader Street cor. 1 de Noviembre Street, Boac, Marinduque"},"Q46123869":{"address":"Magdalena, Laguna","lat":14.19995,"lon":121.4296,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Emilio Jacinto","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Emilio Jacinto","subtitle":"1875–1899"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2017-12-14"},"Q41760038":{"lon":121.28475,"lat":14.49849,"address":"Tanay Church, M. H. Del Pilar Street, Tanay, Rizal","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall at the eastern corner of the church facade.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Tanay","inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of Tanay belonged to Pililla up to 1606 when the first church was built. The town moved to San Antonio in 1620 but was transferred to this site in 1640. The present Church was completed in 1783.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Church of Tanay historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"IJVTanayChurch4.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Church of Tanay","date":"1939"},"Q28919950":{"lat":8.47626,"address":"Casa del Chino Ygua, Cagayan de Oro","lon":124.64412,"name":"Casa del Chino Ygua","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Casa del Chino Ygua Marker.JPG","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(Balay nga Bato)","title":"Casa del Chino Ygua","inscription":"<p>Ipinagawa noong 1882 na yari sa ladrilyong inangkat sa Timog Tsina ni Sia Ygua noong Enero 10, 1899. Nagtipun-tipon sa harapan ng bahay na ito ang mga kalahok sa maringal na parada sa Cagayan de Misamis bilang pagkilala sa pamahalaang rebolusyonaryo ni Heneral Aguinaldo. Sinakop at inokupahan ng ika-40 rehimiyento ng mga boluntaryo ng Estados Unidos. Nilusob ng batalyong Mindanao sa pamumuno ni Heneral Nicolas Capistrano na nagtangkang palayain ang Cagayan de Misamis noong Abril 7, 1900. Maraming Pilipinong manghihimagsik ang napatay sa bahay na ito noong labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis at inilibong sa likod bahay nito.</p>"}}},"date":"2000"},"Q45312720":{"date":"1964-06-27","locPhoto":null,"name":"Ladislao Diwa","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ladislao Diwa","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"lat":14.47926,"address":"Ladislao Diwa Shrine, Cabuco Street cor. de Guzman Street, Cavite City, Cavite","lon":120.89264},"Q24817348":{"address":"Goco Ancestral House, Calle Hermenegildo del Castillo cor. Calle Gliceria Marella, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.88013,"lon":120.92106,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Goco Ancestral House","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This heritage house of the Goco family is registered with the National Historical institute, pursuant to NHI Board Resolution No. 03, S. 2000.</p>","title":"Goco Ancestral House","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Goco Ancestral House historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"2001"},"Q38818766":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"OurLadyofGuidancejf0107 01.JPG"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Ermita Church historical marker location.jpg"},"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia","date":"1971","lon":120.97981,"lat":14.5788,"address":"Ermita Church, M. H. del Pilar Street cor. A. Flores Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q52145135":{"address":"Pagbilao Church, Pan-Philippine Highway cor. General Lucban Street, Pagbilao, Quezon","lat":13.97203,"lon":121.68667,"name":"Simbahan ng Pagbilao","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Pagbilao","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"date":"1986-07-04"},"Q50383807":{"date":"1988-12-20","name":"Honoria Acosta Sison","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Honoria Acosta Sison"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"HonoriaAcostaSison HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"}}},"address":"Taft Avenue cor. Remedios Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.5723,"lon":120.99063},"Q50426643":{"lat":9.31123,"address":"Silliman University, Rizal Avenue, Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","lon":123.30892,"date":"1966","name":"Silliman University","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Originally an elementary school founded in 1901 by Dr. and Mrs. David S. Hibbard under the terms of a gift by philanthropist, Dr. Horace B. Silliman, it was converted into a college in 1910 and a university in 1938. Its buildings were occupied by the Japanese forces from 1942 to 1945. It was reopened after the Second World War. The first Filipino president, Dr. Leopoldo T. Ruiz, was elected in 1952.</p>","title":"Silliman University","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q24702488":{"date":"1937","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first Catholic Missionary of Pasig was Rev. Alonso de Alvarado, companion of Villalobos in his expedition in Moluccas. The first church was built in 1575. The present one was used by the British for military purposes in their campaign against the military forces of Simon de Anda y Salazar.</p>","title":"Church of Pasig"},"photo":{"file":"Church of Pasig historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ronaldbunag; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Church of Pasig","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.07707,"lat":14.56054,"address":"Pasig Cathedral, A. Luna Street cor. Caruncho Avenue, Pasig, Metro Manila"},"Q46868165":{"name":"Ang Dakong Balay","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(Don Florencio Noel House)","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Ang Dakong Balay"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2010-05-29","address":"Don Florencio Noel House, Santa Catalina Street, Carcar, Cebu","lat":10.10387,"lon":123.6418},"Q28942492":{"lat":7.38447,"address":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun, Parang, Maguindanao","lon":124.25709,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Formerly Camp Parang, renamed after Brig. Gen. Salipada K. Pendatun by House Bill no. 53 of the Regional Legislative Assembly of the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM) and the General Order no. 1472 of the Commanding General of the PNP dated October 25, 1991. Hero of the Second World War, founder of the Bolo Battalion in Cotabato Basin, later, Bukidnon-Cotabato Force, proponent of national unity, freedom and liberty. This camp is dedicated in his honor.</p>","title":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1991"},"Q28877481":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Caraga","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Padre Pablo Pastells, S.J. kaagapay si Padre Juan Terricabras, S.J. Yari sa kahoy, korales at bato, 1877. Natapos ang simbahan at naging parokya sa patronato ni San Juan Savador Del Mundo,1884. Nagsilbing sentro ng misyon ng mga Heswita sa pagtatag ng mga pueblo at pagpalaganap ng ebanghelyo sa silangang bahagi ng Mindanao noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Ipinamahala sa mga pari ng Foreign Mission of Quebec, 1939; Maryknoll Missioners, 1961; Diyosesis ng Tagum,1978; at Diyosesis ng Mati, 1984.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Olan214 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Salvador Del Mundo Church National Historical Site Marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Caraga","date":"2012","lon":126.56588,"lat":7.32754,"address":"Caraga Church, Caraga, Davao Oriental"},"Q29018562":{"lon":125.07496,"lat":9.90785,"address":"Limasawa Shrine, Limasawa, Southern Leyte","date":"1950","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Celebrated here on Easter Sunday, 31 March 1521, when Magellan landed on this island of Limasawa on his voyage around the world. Early in the morning, Magellan sent ashore priest Pedro de Valderrama with men to prepare a mass and to inform Rajah Kolambu, through an interpreter that he and his men would land to attend. The rajah showed consent by sending gifts. As Magellan and his men approached the shore, a salvo of six guns was fired as a sign of peace. Rajahs Kolambu and Si-Agu each embraced Magellan, flanked him and together with the sailors, they marched to the place of worship. During the mass the rajahs remained on their knees with clasped hands. At the elevation the ships fired all their artillery in response to musket signal from the shore.</p>","title":"First Mass in the Philippines","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"First Mass in the Philippines","locPhoto":null},"Q30133244":{"lat":41.95452,"address":"1332 West Irving Park Road, Chicago, Cook County, Illinois, United States of America","lon":-87.6634,"date":"1993","locPhoto":null,"name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","inscription":"<p>National hero of the Philippines arrived in Chicago, Illinois on May 11, 1888 at 8:14 a.m. He visited places of interest and left the city at 8:25 p.m.</p>","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null},"Q24185746":{"lat":16.04405,"address":"Manaoag Church, Manaoag, Pangasinan","lon":120.48847,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY 3.0}","file":"Manaoag Shrine Marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag","inscription":"<p>Administered since 1605 by the Dominicans, the first church of wood lasted a century. The second one, which was of stone, was built through the generosity of Gaspar de Gamboa and Agata Yangta, and inaugrated in 1720. In 1733 it was donated to the Dominican corporation, but was destroyed by the earthquake of 1892. The provisional church, built of wood, was burned during the insurrection of 1898. The reconstruction of the present church began in 1901 with the return of the Dominicans. The image of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag is famous throughout Pangasinan. It was preserved in Dagupan during the revolution, then taken back to the sanctuary by the people of Manaoag where it was solemnly crowned on April 21, 1926, in the presence of thousands of the faithful, by Mons. Guillermo Piano, Apostolic Delegate to the Philippines.</p>"}}},"date":"1937"},"Q46996468":{"lon":120.85523,"address":"Felipe G. Calderon Elementary School, San Agustin Street, Tanza, Cavite","lat":14.3988,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Felipe G. Calderon","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Felipe G. Calderon","locPhoto":null,"date":"1957-04-04"},"Q31440525":{"lat":9.75589,"address":"Balilihan Belfry, Balilihan, Bohol","lon":123.97368,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Balilihan Belfry","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Balilihan Belfry","inscription":"<p>Constructed of materials taken near Baclayon, 1844, by Recollect Fr. Antonio Cortes. Withstood the 1863 storm which destroyed the church, utilized as guard post by the Spanish, Filipino, American and Japanese forces.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Balilihan Belfry historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1953"},"Q47073005":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"08635jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 30.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"text":{"title":"Maximino H. Hizon","inscription":"","subtitle":"(1870–1901)"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the equestrian statue of Maximino Hizon.","name":"Maximino H. Hizon","locPhoto":{"file":"PampangaProvincialCapitoljf67.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"date":null,"lon":120.68721,"lat":15.02465,"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga"},"Q47087017":{"date":"1981-10-24","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Sementeryo sa Ilalim ng Lupa ng Nagcarlan","inscription":""}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Sementeryo sa Ilalim ng Lupa ng Nagcarlan","lon":121.41519,"address":"Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery, Nagcarlan–Rizal Road, Nagcarlan, Laguna","lat":14.13142},"Q23665949":{"date":"2013-12-03","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Andres Bonifacio Cebu City historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Andres Bonifacio","inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)"}}},"name":"Andres Bonifacio","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90494,"lat":10.29236,"address":"Cebu City"},"Q23927292":{"lon":123.90215,"address":"Minor Basilica of the Holy Child, Osmeña Boulevard, Cebu City","lat":10.29424,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the entrance to the convent which is located to the left of the main entrance of the basilica.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Nickrds09; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño","inscription":"<p>The Church and Convent erected by the Augustinian Fathers under the Rev. Andres Urdaneta in 1565 were the first established in the Philippines. Both were burned down on November 1, 1566. The second Church was likewise destroyed by fire in March of 1628, but rebuilt soon after (1628–1629) under the administration of the historian Rev. Juan de Medina, O.S.A. The present massive Church was designed and constructed during the Priorship of Rev. Juan Albarran O.S.A., (1735–1737). The Santo Niño, venerated in this Church since the time of Legaspi, is the center of intense devotion and religious pilgrimages through out the Visayas.</p>"}}},"name":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño","locPhoto":{"credit":"No machine-readable author provided. Magalhães assumed (based on copyright claims).","file":"Basilica Minore del Santo Niño entrances and historical marker.jpg"},"date":"1941"},"Q24764362":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Taaljf2280 01.JPG"},"name":"Ang Bayan ng Taal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Ang Bayan ng Taal historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1572)","inscription":"<p>Unang itinatag sa pook ng Balangon noong 1572. Dahil sa madalas na pagputok ng bulkan ay inilipat ang bayan sa kasalukuyang pook. Naging kabisera noong 1732 kaya't taal ang ipinangalan sa buong lalawigan. Nang muling masira ang bayan dahil sa pagputok ng bulkan noong 1754, ang kabisera ay inilipat sa batangan at isinunod dito ang pangalan ng lalawigan. Ang bulkan ng Taal, na pinakamaliit sa buong daigdig, at nasa gitna ng lawa ng Bonbon at sa bunganga ng bulkan ay may isang pulong nasa isa pang maliit na lawa. Pumutok ang bulkan noong 1634, 1635, 1641, 1709, 1718, 1723, 1731, 1749, 1754, 1867, 1874, 1880, 1911 at 1965. Ang ngayo'y mga bayan ng Lemery, San Luis, Agoncillo, San Nicolas, at Sta. Teresita ay dating sakop ng Taal.</p>","title":"Ang Bayan ng Taal"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the municipal hall.","date":"1972","lat":13.88014,"address":"Taal Municipal Hall, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","lon":120.92292},"Q44514157":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Las Piñas Church entrance and historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas","date":"1995","lon":120.98159,"address":"Las Piñas Church, P. Diego Cera Avenue, Las Piñas, Metro Manila","lat":14.48117},"Q28877420":{"lat":6.90148,"address":"Fort Pilar, Zamboanga City","lon":122.08212,"date":"1949","locPhoto":{"file":"Fort Pilar Entrance.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Fort Pilar","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Fort Pilar","inscription":"<p>Founded as southern outpost of Spanish domain under the supervision of Melchor de Vera, 1635; Attacked by the Dutch, 1646; Deserted when troops were concentrated in Manila to drive away Chinese pirates, 1663; Reconstructed by the Society of Jesus, 1666; Rebuilt the management of Juan Sicarra, 1719; Stormed by Dalasi, King Bulig, with 3,000 moros, 1720; Cannonaded by the British, 1798; Witnessed the mutiny of seventy prisoners, 1872; Abandoned by the Spaniards, 1898; Occupied by the Americans under General J.C. Bates 1899; Seized by the Japanese, 1942; Taken over by the Republic of the Philippines, July 1946.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Fort Pilar Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":"This historical marker is located on the wall (previously a pedestal) just to the right of the main entrance of the fort."},"Q46996498":{"lat":14.3857,"address":"General Trias Church, General Trias, Cavite","lon":120.88012,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Heneral Trias","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Heneral Trias","inscription":""},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of General Trias historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1992-12-12"},"Q22295396":{"lon":121.16374,"lat":13.94092,"address":"Lipa Cathedral, Lipa, Batangas","date":"2011-04-12","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Arsobispado ng Lipa","inscription":"<p>Unang ipinahayag ng mga Agustino ang ebanghelyo sa ngayo'y lalawigan ng Batangas, 1572. Naging bahagi ng Obispado ng Maynila, 1579 at Arsobispado ng Maynila, 1595. Itinatag ang Obispado sa pamamagitan ng dekretong konsistoryal “Novas Erigere Ecclesias” ni Papa San Pio X, sakop ang lalawigan ng Batangas, Laguna, Tayabas, at Mindoro, 10 Abril 1910. Naging katedra ang Lipa. Giuseppe Petrelli, D.D., unang obispo, Abril 1910–Marso 1916. Alfredo Verzosa, unang Filipinong obispo, 1916–1950. Naging arsobispado na binubuo ng lalawigan ng Batangas, 20 Hunyo 1972. Alejandro Olalia, unang arsobispo.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Arsobispado ng Lipa historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Arsobispado ng Lipa"},"Q43301560":{"lon":121.00392,"address":"Pandacan Church, 833 Jesus Street cor. Pandacan Street, Pandacan, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59308,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1732 ng paring Francisco del Rosario, O.F.M., ang simbahan at kumbento ay nayari noong 1760. Nasiraan dahil sa lindol ng 1852 at ng 1937. Ipinaayos ng paring Francisco Teodoro. Ang kasalukuyang simbahan ay itinayo sa pamamahala ng paring Victor R. Serrano at binasbasan ng arsobispo Jaime L. Sin noong ika-31 ng Marso, 1974.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan"},"photo":{"file":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the church.","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan","locPhoto":{"file":"09708jfSanto Niño de Pandacan Parish Church Manila Schools Landmarksfvf 05.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"date":"1976-07-13"},"Q28937459":{"lon":125.60793,"lat":7.06462,"address":"Davao City Hall, Davao City","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Davao City Hall","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo bilang gusaling munisipal ng Davao, 1926. Nilagdaan ni Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon ang Commonwealth Act No. 51 na bumuo sa Karta ng Lungsod ng Davao, 16 Oktubre 1936. Pinasinayaan ni Kalihim Elpidio Quirino ang Kata sa harapan ng gusali, 1 Marso 1937. Nasira nong panahon ng digmaan, 1945. Muling ipinatayo ayon sa orihinal na disenyo, 1947. Sentro ng pamahalaan sa pagtaguyod ng Davao bilang pangunahing lungsod sa silangang bahagi ng Mindanao noong panahon ng mga Amerikano.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"City Government of Davao","file":"Davao City Hall historical marker.jpg"}}},"name":"Davao City Hall","locPhoto":null,"date":"2012"},"Q40319282":{"date":"2002","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Fernanda Balboa 1902 - 1999.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Fernanda Balboa","inscription":"","subtitle":"1902–1999"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Fernanda Balboa","lon":120.97801,"address":"Muralla Street cor. Gen. Luna Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58682},"Q50413542":{"name":"Simbahan ng Siquijor","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Siquijor","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"date":"1984-05-19","address":"Siquijor Church, Siquijor","lat":9.21539,"lon":123.51397},"Q28973983":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ramos House","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","title":"Ramos House","inscription":"<p>On this site has stood for years the house of the couple Narciso Ramos, lawyer, journalist, statesman and diplomat, and Angela Valdez, one-time English supervisor of the Pangasinan Vocational High School. In this house were born and raised their children: Leticia Ramos Shahani, ambassador and senator; Fidel, AFP Chief of Staff, Secretary of the Department of National Defense and eighth President of the Republic of the Philippines; and Gloria Ramos-Rodda.</p><p>This marker was made possible through the initiative of Kaluyagan Nen Palaris and daughters of Princess Urduja Executive Committee headed by Justice and Mrs. Porfirio V. Sison.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Ramos house 2 historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1993","lat":16.02951,"address":"The President Hotel, Lingayen, Pangasinan","lon":120.23264},"Q44821150":{"lon":120.47503,"address":"Badoc Church, Soriano Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","lat":17.92783,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Simbahan ng Badoc historical marker.jpg","credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Badoc"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Badoc","date":"1980"},"Q36178435":{"lon":123.20126,"lat":13.69911,"address":"Quipayo Church, Calabanga, Camarines Sur","date":"1979","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Quipayo Church National Historical Institute marker.jpg","credit":"Jun pasa {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Simbahang Parokya ng Quipayo","inscription":"<p>Isa sa pinakamatatandang simbahan sa Kabikolan. Ito ay itinatag noong 1578 ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano na sina Prayle Pablo de Jesus at Bartolome Ruiz. Pinakaulo ng mga naunang misyon, ang bayan ay sumakop sa mga bisita ng Ligmanan (Libmanan), Bangon (Siruma), Calabangan (Calabanga) at Bombon hanggang sa ang mga ito ay nagsarili noong mga taong 1586, 1687, at 1749, ayon sa pagkakabanggit. Mula noong 1902 hanggang sa kasalukuyan, ang Quipayo ay naging parokyang baryo ng bayan ng Calabanga. </p><p> Buhat sa orihinal na nipa at kahoy ang kasalukuyang simbahang tisa ay ipinatayo sa pamamahala ni Prayle Francisco Gaviria noong 1616. Gayunman, ang harapan ng simbahan ay nagiba nong 1949 dahil sa malakas na pag-ulan. Patrona ng parokya ay ang Birhen ng Imakulada Konsepsiyon. Noong 1659, naging pangalawang patron nito si San Roque.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahang Parokya ng Quipayo"},"Q24705458":{"lon":120.93608,"lat":14.42956,"address":"Imus Cathedral, Imus, Cavite","date":"2006-11-13","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang simbahang parokyal ng mga paring Rekoletos sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora Del Pilar at San Juan Bautista at sa pamamahala ni Francisco de Santiago, Orsa, bilang unang kura paroko, 1795. Mula sa Toclong inilipat sa Balangon, ang kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1823. Ipinatayo ang simbahang gawa sa bato at ladrilyo sa ilalim ni Nicolas Becerra, Orsa, na nagsibli mula 1821 - 1840. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1897. Naging katedral at luklukan ng Diyosesis ng Imus, 1961.</p>","title":"Katedral ng Imus"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Katedral ng Imus historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the western front entrance of the cathedral.","name":"Katedral ng Imus","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Imus Cathedral historical marker location.jpg"}},"Q24816799":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located beneath a statue of Felipe Agoncillo that is erected at the front lawn of the Don Gregorio Agoncillo Mansion.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion 1859–1941","inscription":"<p>Abogado, estadista, at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Taal 26 Mayo 1859. Batsilyer sa Artes, Ateneo Municipal de Manila; Lisensiyado sa Batas, Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas. Masiglang kagawad ng Lupong Pilipino ng Himagsikan sa Hong Kong. Ministro ng Plenipotensiyaryo noong unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Caballero dela Cruz Roja Española, iginawad ng Pamahalaang Kastila. Diputado ng unang purok ng Batangas sa Asamblea Pilipina, 1907–09. Kalihim Panloob ng gabinete ni Gobernador Wood, 1924–25. Pangulo sa loob ng anim na sunud-sunod na taon ng Colegio de Abogados de Filipinas. Pangulo ng Unang Kongreso ng Pilipinas sa Pagsasarili, Maynila, 22–26 Pebrero 1930. Namatay sa Maynila 29 Setyembre 1941.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion historical marker.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Taaljf2115 13.JPG"},"name":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion 1859–1941","date":"1955","lon":120.92528,"lat":13.87818,"address":"Don Gregorio Agoncillo Mansion, Palico-Balayan-Batangas Road cor. Calle Felipe Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas"},"Q46546191":{"date":"2002","name":"Ang Escuela Pia ng Prieto-Diaz","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Ang Escuela Pia ng Prieto-Diaz"},"photo":null}},"lat":13.03975,"address":"Prieto Diaz Central School, Prieto Diaz, Sorsogon","lon":124.19542},"Q37625398":{"lon":120.97441,"lat":14.57955,"address":"Quirino Grandstand, Parade Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a bust of Elpidio Quirino near the southern end of the Quirino Grandstand.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Elpidio Quirino (Quirino Grandstand) historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, Nobyembre 16, 1890. Nagtapos ng elementarya sa Aringay, La Union at sekondarya sa Manila High School, 1911. Nagkamit ng Titulo sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1915. Nagsimulang maglingkod sa bayan bilang guro sa Caparian, Agoo, La Union sa gulang na 16. Nahirang na pribadong kalihim ng Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa ilalim ng panunungkulan ng Gobernador Heneral Frank Murphy at Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor. Nahalal na kinatawan ng Ilocos Sur, 1919; senador 1922, 1931, 1941; delegado sa Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal, 1934; at pangalawang pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1946. Naging pangulo sa pagkamatay ni Pangulong Manuel A. Roxas, 1948; nahalal na pangulo, 1949. Namatay, Pebrero 29, 1956. Ang kanyang panunungkula’y kinatampukan ng muling pagpapayabong sa ekonomiya ng bansa na sinira ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at pagpapanumbalik ng kapayapa’t muling pananalig ng mamamayan sa pamahalaan.</p>","title":"Elpidio R. Quirino","subtitle":"(1890–1956)"}}},"name":"Elpidio R. Quirino","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09500jfElpidio Quirino Monument Grandstand Rizal Parkfvf 02.jpg"},"date":"1990"},"Q43590262":{"date":"1962-10-17","name":"Dr. Maximo Viola","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Dr. Maximo Viola","subtitle":"1857–1933"},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"FvfViola8154 01.JPG"}}},"lat":15.14013,"address":"Cagayan Valley Road cor. Viola Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","lon":120.96779},"Q38226290":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Birthplace of Gregorio Sanciangco","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Birthplace of Gregorio Sanciangco","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JfBirthplaceGregorioSanciangcoMemorialfvf 09.JPG"}}},"date":"1952","lat":14.66213,"address":"Sanciangco Street, Malabon, Metro Manila","lon":120.9563},"Q28933123":{"date":"2008-03-13","name":"Macabalan Wharf","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga Espanyol sa Cagayan de Misamis ika-labinsiyam na siglo. Nagsilbing daungan ng mga sasakyang pandagat mula Maynila, Cebu, Maribojoc, Iloilo at Romblon. Naging kutang tanggulan ng mga Cagayanon upang pigilan ang pagsakop ng mga Amerikano sa Cagayan de Misamis, Enero-Marso 1900. Nasakop ng mga Amerikano, 25 Abril 1900. Dito dumaong sina Hen. Douglas MacArthur at pamilya mula Corregidor, 13 Marso 1942. Tumungo sa Del Monte Airfield, Bukidnon at lumpipad patungong Australya, 17 Marso 1942.</p>","title":"Macabalan Wharf","subtitle":null}}},"lat":8.50114,"address":"Macabalan Wharf, Cagayan de Oro","lon":124.66431},"Q28927583":{"lat":6.90391,"address":"Zamboanga City Hall, Zamboanga City","lon":122.07628,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Bahay-Pamahalaan ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(Dating Panlalawigang Kapitolyo ng Zamboanga)","title":"Bahay-Pamahalaan ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga","inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1905–1907 ng Pamahalaang Pederal ng Estados Unidos. Ang gusaling ito ang naging luklukan ng Pamahalaan ng Lalawigang Muslim noong panahon ng mala-militar na pananakop ng mga Amerikano, 1903–1913; ng Kagawaran ng Mindanao at Sulu noong panahon ng sibil na pananakop ng mga Amerikano, 1914–1920; ng Lalawigan ng Zamboanga, 1921–1945; at ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga mula noong 1937 hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"City Hall of Zamboanga historical marker 10.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"date":"1969"},"Q35093587":{"address":"Loay Church, Loay, Bohol","lat":9.60099,"lon":124.01206,"date":"2004","name":"Simbahan ng Santisima Trinidad ng Loay","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang Loay bilang Barrio Santisima Trinidad sa ilalim ng Parokya ng San Pedro Apostol ng Loboc noong ika-18 dantaon. Naging parokya sa pangangasiwa ng mga misyonerong Rekoletos, 1799. Itinayo ang simbahan, 1822; ang kumbento, 1838; ang kampanaryo, 1865. Naglingkod dito si Padre Leon Inchausti, martir ng digmaang sibil sa Espanya (1936-1939) na kinanonisa bilang santo noong 1999. Mahalagang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Pilipino-Espanyol. Inihayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 18 Agosto 2003.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Santisima Trinidad ng Loay","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Loay Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}}},"Q40316780":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"WWII Victims at Fort Santiago historical marker, Manila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"In Memory of the Victims at Fort Santiago"}}},"name":"In Memory of the Victims at Fort Santiago","locPhoto":null,"date":"1995","lon":120.96961,"lat":14.59486,"address":"Fort Santiago, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q22298034":{"lon":120.97329,"lat":14.59175,"address":"Manila Cathedral, Sto. Tomas Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1958","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila","inscription":"<p>First cathedral built in 1581, damaged by a typhoon, 1582 and destroyed by fire, 1583. Second cathedral built of stone in 1592 and partially destroyed by earthquake, 1600. Third cathedral built of stone in 1614 and destroyed by the earthquake of 1645. Fourth cathedral magnificently built in 1654-1671 by Archbishop Miguel Poblete and destroyed by the earthquake ofv3 June 1863. Fifth cathedral built in 1870-1879 under architects Luciano Oliver, Vicente Serrano Salaverria and Eduardo Lopez Navarro and solemnly blessed in December 1879. The center of the cross on the dome is a reference point of astronomical longitudes of Manila in 1945. Sixth cathedral reconstruction 1954-1958; under the direction of Archbishop Rufino J. Santos of Manila mainly with the support of the people. Fernando Ocampo, architect.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila historical marker (corrected).jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the cathedral.","locPhoto":{"credit":"H.abanil {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Manila Cathedral Facade.JPG"},"name":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila"},"Q50426496":{"date":"2000","locPhoto":null,"name":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1873–1898)","inscription":"","title":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"address":"Dumaguete South Road, Bacong, Negros Oriental","lat":9.24511,"lon":123.29514},"Q37153825":{"date":"1986","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa bato at kahoy noong 1824 ni Don Angel Pantaleon de Miranda at kanyang maybahay, Doña Rosalia de Jesus, ang nagtatag ng Angeles (Dating Culiat), Pampanga noong 1796. Minana ng kanilang anak na si Doña Juana Miranda de Henson at pagkaraan ay tinirahan ng mga tagapagmana ni Don Jose P. Henson. Kasalukuyang tahanan ni Don Vicente N. Henson, Sr. Naging tuluyan din ng hukbong rebolusyonaryo ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo noong panahon ng Digmaaang Pilipino-Amerikano, 1899.</p>","title":"Bahay ni Angel Pantaleon de Miranda","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Bahay ni Angel Pantaleon de Miranda","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.58953,"address":"Angel Pantaleon de Miranda House, 770 Santo Rosario Street, Angeles","lat":15.13533},"Q24849479":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Mauban","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The town, successfully located at the Pinagbayanan, Balaybalay, and Soledad, was transferred to this site in 1647. The first church and the first convent, constructed in 1647, were demolished in 1769. The second church and the second convent were completed in 1773. The convent were badly damaged in the earthquake of 1830 and rebuilt between 1836 and 1945. The old church collapsed during the earthquakes of July, 1880. The present church was built in 1891. The belfry, constructed in 1773, was seriously damaged during the earthquakes of 1880 and the portion of which remained was partially destroyed again by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>","title":"Church of Mauban","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1939","lat":14.1903,"address":"Mauban Church, Mauban, Quezon","lon":121.731},"Q46484367":{"date":"2014-01-21","name":"Padre Modesto de Castro","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Urbanroamer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Naic Church and Convent 8.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Padre Modesto de Castro","subtitle":"1819–1864"}}},"lat":14.31985,"address":"Naic Church, Naic, Cavite","lon":120.76406},"Q40313447":{"address":"San Agustin Church, Gen. Luna Street cor. Real Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58922,"lon":120.97522,"date":"1998","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"02342jfManila Intramuros Streets Buildings Churches Landmarksfvf 15.jpg"},"name":"Church of San Agustin","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Oldest stone church in the Philippines. Plans were approved in 1586. Construction started in 1587 and completed in 1607 under the supervision successively of Augustinian Fathers Francisco de Bustos, Ildefonso Perez, Diego de Avila and Brother Alonso de Perea. Its architect was Juan Macias. It has withstood many earthquakes from 1645 up to the present and survived the British invasion in 1762, the Spanish–American War in 1898 and the Japanese invasion in 1942. The church choir has 68 carved molave seats with narra inlaids, an artistic lectern and parchment cantorals of the 17th and 18th centuries. The church and its graves were profaned during the British occupation of Manila in 1762. The ashes of early Spanish conquistadores Legazpi, Salcedo, Lavezares, and blessed Pedro de Zuniga and others now rest in the easternmost chapel of the transept. Terms for the American occupation of Manila were prepared in the vestry of the church in 1898. The First Philippine Plenary Council was held here in 1953. Chosen as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO in 1993.</p>","title":"Church of San Agustin"},"photo":{"file":"Church of San Agustin historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall of the northeastern side of the church facade."},"Q45153368":{"date":"2006","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Bagacay Point Lighthouse historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Parola ng Bagacay Point","inscription":"<p>Itinayo sa lupaing inilaan ni Gobernador Heneral William Howard Taft, 1904. May taas na 72 talampakan at nagbibigay liwanag na umaabot ng may 17 milyang-dagat. Nagsisilbing gabay sa mga sasakyang dagat na naglalayag sa bukana ng hilagang-silangan ng Cebu Harbor. Isa sa mga nalalabing parolang may mahalagang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Amerikano sa bansa. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 13 Agosto 2004.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Parola ng Bagacay Point","lon":124.01854,"lat":10.38327,"address":"Bagacay Point Lighthouse, Liloan, Cebu"},"Q44455814":{"address":"Rizal Avenue, Rizal Avenue cor. Claro M. Recto Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.60332,"lon":120.98209,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Founding site of the Asociacion Feminista Filipina","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina site historical marker in Santa Cruz 2.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"text":{"title":null,"inscription":"<p>In a building on this site was organized the Asociacion Feminista Filipinas on 30 June, 1905.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1955"},"Q46487777":{"address":"Imus Plaza, Castañeda Street cor. Maestro G. Tirona Street, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42895,"lon":120.9362,"date":"1954","locPhoto":null,"name":"Imus","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"ImusCavitejf0433 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Formed part of the Hacienda de Imus owned by the Recollect Fathers, 1686. Organized into a municipality, 1795. Occupied by the Revolutionists, September 1, 1896. Seat of the Revolutionary Assembly, January, 1897. Retaken by the Spaniards, March 28, 1897. Reoccupied by the Filipinos, May 28, 1898, until the establishment of civil government under the Americans, June 11, 1901. Taken by the Japanese, January 1, 1942. Liberated by the Americans, February 4, 1945.</p>","title":"Imus","subtitle":null}}}},"Q44702634":{"date":"1988","locPhoto":{"credit":"Nmcast {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pres. Ramon Magsaysay monument in Mt. Manunggal, Balamban, Cebu.jpg"},"name":"Ramon Magsaysay","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the pedestal for the bust of Ramon Magsaysay.","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1907–1957)","title":"Ramon Magsaysay","inscription":""}}},"lat":10.45047,"address":"Mount Manunggal, Balamban, Cebu","lon":123.81407},"Q24004133":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Paco Park - José Rizal memorial.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Jose Rizal","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Executed 30 December 1896; interred secretly in this spot by the authorities on the same day; guarded for fifteen days by the Guardia Civil Veterana. Remains exhumed 17 August 1898, placed in an urn made by Teodoro Romualdo de Jesus, deposited in the house of his mother in Estraude Street, Binondo, and on 30 December 1912 laid beneath his monument at the Luneta.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal Marker on Paco Cemetery.JPG"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the ground, in front of a cross monument dedicated to José Rizal.","date":"1957","address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.5817,"lon":120.98873},"Q24882639":{"lon":121.3451,"address":"Villa Escudero, Kilometer 91, Pan-Philippine Highway, Tiaong, Quezon","lat":13.99412,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Don Placido Escudero Dam","inscription":"<p>Don Ciriaco Nadres, Duly authorized by the Spanish Government, Constructed here in 1872 a dam of adobe stone and lime mortar for irrigating his land on this side of the brook. Don Hermenegildo, his son, sold the property in 1890 to Don Placido Escudero and his wife, Dona Claudia Marasigan, who in 1904 reconstructed this dam with hard stone and cement mortar. Their only son Don Arsenio and Dona Rosario Adap his wife, rebuilt this dam in 1937 for irrigation, and for the hydro-electric plant, supplying power and light to the “Cooperative Coconut Products Inc.” and to “Villa Escudero” 1938.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Don Placido Escudero Dam","date":"1938"},"Q46155194":{"lat":14.38528,"address":"96th Street cor. Corregidor Street, General Trias, Cavite","lon":120.87959,"date":"2009","locPhoto":null,"name":"Bahay na Tinigilan ni Andres Bonifacio","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GeneralTrias,Cavitejf2987 12.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Bahay na Tinigilan ni Andres Bonifacio"}}}},"Q44454498":{"lat":15.34484,"address":"Capas, Tarlac","lon":120.59417,"name":"Death March","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"text":{"en":{"subtitle":"April 1942","inscription":"<p>At this railroad station of Capas, the Filipino and American prisoners of war who survived the horrendous trip from San Fernando, during which so many smothered to death in the densely crowded cars, were unloaded and force, although on the point of collapse to march the 6 kilometers to Camp O’Donnell, where they were concentrated.</p>","title":"Death March"},"tl":{"inscription":"<p>Sa himpilang daang-bakal na ito ng Capas, ang mga bihag ng digmang kawal Pilipino at Amerikano na himalang nakaligtas sa makahayup na paglalakbay mula San Fernando, ay muling pinaglakad gayong mga nag-aagaw buhay, hanggang Kampo O’Donnell na may 6 kilometro ang layo. Sa impiyernong kulungang yaon, sila’y naging bilanggo.</p>","title":"Death March","subtitle":"April 1942"}},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Death March (Capas) April 1942 historical marker .jpg"}},"date":"1967"},"Q35004190":{"lon":124.40502,"address":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church, Duero, Bohol","lat":9.70773,"date":"2015","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Duero"},"photo":null}},"name":"Simbahan ng Duero","locPhoto":null},"Q41080609":{"lat":14.59121,"address":"Arzobispo Street cor. Postigo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97241,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Pook na Kinatatayuan ng Unang Seminaryong Diyosesano ng Pilipinas","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"First Diocesan Seminary site historical marker in Manila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Ang Pook na Kinatatayuan ng Unang Seminaryong Diyosesano ng Pilipinas"}}},"date":"2000"},"Q46869441":{"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Balay na Tisa","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","subtitle":"(Sarmiento-Osmeña House)"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Balay na Tisa","locPhoto":null,"date":"2010-05-29","lon":123.64272,"address":"Sarmiento-Osmeña House, Santa Catalina Street, Carcar, Cebu","lat":10.10201},"Q25080039":{"address":"Casa Hacienda de Naic, Naic, Cavite","lat":14.32046,"lon":120.76354,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NaicChurchjf9481 10.JPG"},"name":"Casa Hacienda de Naic","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the building.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa mismong gusaling ito, ngayo'y Mababang Paaralan ng Naic, isinagawa at isinakatuparan noong Abril 19, 1897 ang Acta de Naic o Naic Military Agreement, isang kasunduan nina Bonifacio at ng kanyang mga kapanalig na salungat sa mga panuntunan na pinagkasunduan ng mga manghihimagsik sa Kumbensiyon ng Tejeros, na ginanap noong Marso 22, 1897.</p><p>Dito rin binuo ni Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo, makaraan ang mahal na araw nang taon ding yaon ang kanyang 'Cabinet of Reconciliation,\" o ang pagsasaayos ng gabinete ng kanyang pamahalaan na hindi nabuo sa Kumbensiyon ng Tejeros.</p>","title":"Casa Hacienda de Naic"},"photo":{"file":"Casa Hacienda de Naic historical marker (corrected).jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"1998"},"Q28855047":{"lat":10.10451,"address":"Mercado Mansion, Jose Rizal Street, Carcar, Cebu","lon":123.64139,"date":"2010-05-29","locPhoto":null,"name":"Mercado Mansion","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Mercado Mansion","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker of Mercado Mansion.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}}},"Q37593057":{"lon":120.9794,"lat":14.59453,"address":"Liwasang Bonifacio, Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"2013","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the southern face of the pedestal of a statue of Andres Bonifacio at the middle of the plaza.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Andrés Bonifacio historical marker at the Liwasang Bonifacio, Manila.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","title":"Andres Bonifacio","subtitle":"30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897"}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Statue of Andrés Bonifacio at Liwasang Bonifacio, Manila.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Andres Bonifacio"},"Q44503063":{"lon":120.97443,"address":"Binondo Church, Quitin Paredes Road, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59991,"date":"1971-05-14","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Binondo","inscription":"<p>Dito itinatag ng mga paring Dominikano ang misyon para sa mga Intsik noong 1587 at naging parokya noong 1596. Nasira nang pumasok ang mga Ingles noong 1762. Inilipat sa paring sekular noong 1769 at ibinalik sa Dominikano noong 1822. Ibinalik sa mga paring sekular noong 1898. Ang simbahan at bagong kumbento ay inayos noong 1946–1971.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BinondoChurch HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Binondo"},"Q35009205":{"lon":123.84351,"lat":9.74045,"address":"Santa Cruz Parish Church, Maribojoc, Bohol","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Maribojoc Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang misyon at parokya sa patronato ng Santa Cruz, 1767. Inilipat sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Manuel Plaza, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan na yari sa korales at bato, 1852. Natapos sa pamumuno ni Padre Fernando Rubio Lucas Martinez, O.A.R., 1872; ang kumbento at kampanaryo na may orasan, 1877-1898. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan, mga taong 1930. Ipinaayos ng Comite de Obras ang mga retablo, 1934. Nailigtas nang sunugin ang bayan ng Maribojoc noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1942-1945. Itinalaga bilang Diocesan Shrine of San Vicente Ferrer, 2005. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang kolonyal noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Maribojoc","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Maribojoc","date":"2009"},"Q43302099":{"lon":121.07214,"address":"University of the Philippines College of Law, Osmeña Avenue cor. F. Ma. Guerrero Street, Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.65642,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of Malcolm Hall.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"UniversityofthePhilippinesCollegeofLawjf2819 01.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"University of the Philippines College of Law","subtitle":null}}},"name":"University of the Philippines College of Law","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"UPDilimanjf2829 06.JPG"},"date":"2012"},"Q41646542":{"lon":120.9373,"address":"J. P. Rizal Street, Obando, Bulacan","lat":14.70934,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"0337jfPag-Asa Poblacion Catanghalan Panghulo Obando, Bulacan Landmarksfvf 09.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Ang Bayan ng Obando"}}},"name":"Ang Bayan ng Obando","locPhoto":null,"date":"1973-05-19"},"Q28973743":{"date":"1995","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","title":"Ramos House","inscription":"<p>For many years on this site was located the rented family house of Narciso Ramos (lawyer, journalist, statesman and diplomat) and Angela Valdez (former English supervisor of Pangasinan Vocational High School).</p><p>It was here that their eldest child Fidel, and first daughter Leticia, were born, raised and spent their formative years: Fidel, former Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces of the Philippines, former Secretary of National Defense and in 1992 elected 12th President of the Republic of the Philippines, Leticia Ramos Shahani, ambassador, senator and Senate President Pro-Tempore. Gloria Ramos da Rodda, their third child and a Philippine consul, was born in the Pangasinan Provincial Hospital in Dagupan.</p><p>The house was destroyed during World War II and the present structure, which now houses family mementos, was constructed in January 1995 through the donations of the Ramos Foundation and the Agpoon family.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ramos House historical marker in Lingayen, Pangasinan (cropped).jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ramos House","lon":120.23237,"lat":16.0292,"address":"Lingayen, Pangasinan"},"Q37726263":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Aurora Aragon Quezon Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1888–1949)","title":"Aurora Aragon Quezon","inscription":"<p>Lider Sibika at pangunang unang ginang ng bansa sa ilalim ng malasariling pamahalaan ng Pilipinas. Ipinanganak noong ika-19 ng Pebrero 1888 sa Baler, Tayabas (Ngayo'y sakop ng lalawigan ng Aurora). Nag-aral sa paaralang Normal ng Pilipinas. Ikinasal sa Hongkong kay Manuel Luis Quezon, Pangulo ng Senado noong 1918. Mga anak: Maria Aurora, Maria Zeneida, Lusia Corazon Paz and Manuel L.. Jr. Nagtatag at nagsagawa ng iba't ibang batayan ng kaalaman para sa mamamayan lalo na ng kabataan sa Baler upang mapaunlad ang karunungang bumasa at sumulat at maitaguyod ang mga tungkuling pambayan. Makaraang mamatay ang Pangulong Quezon (1944)nag taguyod ng mga gawaing panlipunan at panrelihiyon para mapabuti ang pamantayan ng pamumuhay at pagbibigay ng karunungan at biyaya sa mga kapuspalad. Namuno para makilalang isang pambansang samahan ang Krus na Pula at naging unang babaeng pangulo nito. Tinangkilik ang pagtatayong-muli ng makasaysayang simbahan ng Baler. Habang pauwi ng Baler, tinambangan ng isang pangkat ng HUKBALAHAP sa Nueva Ecija at kasamang napatay si Maria Aurora, manugang na Felipe Buencamino III at ilang kaibigan noong ika-28 ng Abril 1949. Bilang parangal sa kanya, itinatag ang sub-lalawigan ng Aurora noong 1951 sa pamamagitan ng batas ng republika blg. 648 at ginawang lalawigan ito sa bisa ng batas pambansa blg. 7 noong 1978.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located outside Aurora Aragon's replica house by the corner of Rizal and San Luis streets of Baler.","name":"Aurora Aragon Quezon","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Aurorahousejf.JPG"},"date":"1985","lon":121.56261,"lat":15.75868,"address":"Rizal Street cor. San Luis Street, Baler, Aurora"},"Q24189973":{"address":"Holy Rosary Minor Seminary, Naga, Camarines Sur","lat":13.62812,"lon":123.18659,"name":"Holy Rosary Seminary","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Holy Rosary Minor Seminary NCHP Marker.jpg","credit":"Jun Pasa {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Holy Rosary Seminary","inscription":"<p>Dating Casa de Clerigos na itinatag ni Obispo Andres Gonzales, O.P., sirka 1700. Ipinatayo ni Obispo Juan Antonio de Orbigo, O.F.M., ang bagong bahay seminaryo, 1785; Pinanganlang Seminario Conciliar de Nueva Caceres. Pinasinayaan ni Obispo Domingo Collantes, O.P., 1793; Natapos noong 1845. Nasira ng bagyo, 1856; at tinupok ng apoy, 1860. Muling ipinatayo at pinalaki ni Obispo Francisco Gainza, O.P., 1862; Inilipat ang pamamahala sa Vincentian Fathers, 1865. Pinanganlang Seminario del Santisimo Rosario ni Obispo Francisco Reyes, 1925. Bahagyang nasira nang bombahin ng mga sundalong Hapon, 1945, at ipinaayos ni Arsobispo Pedro Santos. Pinanganlang Holy Rosary Seminary sa ilalim ng klerikong Diyosesano, 1964. Malubhang napinsala ng bagyo, ipinaayos ni Arsobispo Teopisto Alberto, 1970. Bukod sa ilang pambansang bayani, mga martir at rebulusyonaryo, 19 sa mga obispo na kasalukuyang nakatalaga sa iba't ibang bahagi ng kapuluan ang katangi-tanging kontribusyon ng seminaryong ito. </p><p> Sa bisa ng kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugna ng mga Kautusan bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang seminaryong ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"}}},"date":"1988"},"Q24243017":{"date":"1982","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument dedicated to the Fifteen Martyrs of Bicol.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Jblaza; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol historical marker 2.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mga ilustrado ng Bikol na dinakip at nilitis ng Komisyong Militar noong 29 Disyembre 1896 sa bintang na balak na pagpatay sa lahat ng Kastila sa iba't ibang dako ng Kabikulan. Walang kasalanan sa krimeng ibinibintang sa kanila. Sila ay binaril sa Luneta, Maynila, noong 4 Enero 1897. </p><p> Mga binaril: Domingo Abella, Manuel Abella, P. Severino Diaz, P. Inocencio Herrera, Camilo Jacob, Florencio Lerma, Mariano Melgarejo, Cornelio Mercado, P. Gabriel Prieto, Tomas Prieto at Macario Valentin. Namatay sa bilangguan: Leon Hernandez at Mariano Ordenanza. Namatay samantalang tapon: Ramon Abella at Mariano Araña. </p><p> Ang bangkay ng mga martir na ito ay inilagak sa iisang hukay na hindi natunton kailanman.</p>","title":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":{"file":"Plaza Quince Martires.jpg","credit":"Melandriaromero {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol","lon":123.18593,"lat":13.62445,"address":"Naga, Camarines Sur"},"Q52144727":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NasugbuBatangasjf0339 39.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito dumaong ang mga sundalo ng Unang Batalyon at 188<sup>th</sup> Glider Infantry ng 11<sup>th</sup> Airborne Division sa pangunguna ni Lt. General Robert Eichelberger, 31 Enero 1945. Nagsilbing kabalikat ng hukbong Amerikano ang mga gerilyang Filipino na pinangunahan ni Tenyente Koronel Marcelo Castillo at Koronel Eleuterio L. Adevoso.</p>","title":"Pagdaong sa Nasugbu","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Pagdaong sa Nasugbu","locPhoto":null,"date":"2007","lon":120.62502,"address":"Apacible Boulevard, Nasugbu, Batangas","lat":14.07124},"Q42699840":{"lon":120.89233,"lat":14.47703,"address":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School, Padre Burgos Avenue cor. Crisostomo Street, Cavite City, Cavite","date":"1964-11-30","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School","inscription":""},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School"},"Q37705570":{"address":"Shrine of the National Flag, Bucandala-Alapan Road, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.40373,"lon":120.91516,"date":"2014","name":"Labanan sa Alapan","locPhoto":{"file":"Battle of Alapan Monument in Imus Heritage Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a monument of a lady brandishing the Philippine Flag at a battle. The monument is at the western portion of the park.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Alapan, Imus, Kabite, noong 28 Mayo 2898, naipagtagumpay ang kaunaunahang labanan sa mga hangganan ng Kawit nang muling magbangong-lakas laban sa Espanya ang himagsikan itinatag ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo. Ang labanang ito ang naging palatandaan ng ating matagumpay na pagpupunyaging maibagsak ang paghahari ng mga Kastila at ng pagsilang ng unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Sa pook din ito unang iwinagayway ang bandilang Pilipino.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Alapan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Battle of Alapan Historical Marker at Imus Heritage Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}}},"Q23920517":{"date":"1950","locPhoto":{"credit":"Oloapsaziracav {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Laoag Church main entrance.jpg"},"name":"Church of Laoag","locDesc":"The marker is located on the wall immediately to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Church of Laoag historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Eric Jam; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Laoag","inscription":"<p>Chapel of wood and thatch built on this site when the Augustinian friars founded the parish, 1580. Replaced by this church of Italian Renaissance; foundation laid, 1612. Looted by the Chieftain Almazan who took possession of Virgin Mary's crown and proclaimed himself king, 1661. Damaged by fire, 1843; Repaired by Obras Publicas under Engineer Antonio de la Camara and Fray Santiago Muniz, 1873-1880. Occupied by Revolutionists, 1898; by American forces, 1899. Ownership contested by Aglipayans, 1901. Scene of Diocesan Marian Congress, 1932 and 1949.</p>"}}},"lat":18.19402,"address":"Laoag Cathedral, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","lon":120.59323},"Q39696558":{"date":"2013-04-22","name":"Labanan sa Malinta","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naganap ang sagupaan ng mga sundalong Pilipino at Amerikano hindi kalayuan sa Simbahan ng Malinta, kung saan napaslang ang ilang kawal ng 22<sup>nd</sup> U.S. Infantry kabilang si Col. Harry C. Egbert, 26 Marso 1899. Bagaman nadepensahan ng mga Pilipino sa unang bahagi ang kanilang posisyon sa Malinta, kalauna’y napilitan silang umatras pahilaga sa paglusob ng dagdag na kawal ng puwersang Amerikano.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Malinta","subtitle":"26 Marso 1899"},"photo":{"file":"Labanan sa Malinta historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines"}}},"lat":14.69097,"address":"MacArthur Highway, Valenzuela, Metro Manila","lon":120.96919},"Q41329465":{"lon":121.41742,"lat":14.27553,"address":"Old Laguna Provincial Capitol Building, Pedro Guevarra Avenue, Santa Cruz, Laguna","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng Pamahalaang Panlalawigan ng Laguna sa ilalim ni Gobernador Juan Cailles ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto William E. Parsons, 1907. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at ipinaayos sa pamamagitan ng U.S.–Philippine Rehabilitation Act of 1946 at natapos, 1949. Muling ipinaayos, 2012, at nananatiling sento ng pamamahala sa lalawigan.</p>","title":"Ang Gusaling Pamahalaan ng Laguna"},"photo":null}},"name":"Ang Gusaling Pamahalaan ng Laguna","locPhoto":null,"date":"2015-08-28"},"Q47005963":{"date":"1958-12-05","name":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.14299,"address":"People's Park in the Sky, Tagaytay, Cavite","lon":121.02197},"Q41323794":{"lon":121.43713,"lat":14.26403,"address":"F.T. San Luis Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna","date":"1988-09-20","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Battle of Sambat historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sukdulan ng unang labanan sa Laguna ng Katipunan, Sangay Maluningning, at ng lakas Kastila. Napaurong sa dami ng nasawi sa Sta. Cruz noong Nobyembre 15, 1896 ng mga casadores na may mga riple at artileriya ang 3,000 na may mga itak, sibat at ilang baril na rebulusyonaryong buhat sa Pagsanjan, Lumban, Paete, Pakil, Siniloan, Cavinte, Sta. Cruz, Magdalena at mga karatig-bayan na pinamumunuan ni Hen. Severino Taino. Huling napuksa sa tatlong oras na sagupaan sa pook na ito noong Nobyembre 16 ng Southern Expeditionary Force kasama ang 70th Infantry Regiment ni Heneral Jaramillo buhay sa Batangas ang panlikod na hanay ni Kol. Francisco Abad at ng mga cuadrilleros ng Bay. Napatay ang 'Bayani ng Sambat' at daan-daang mga katipunero sa dalawang araw na mabangi at madugong paghahamok.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Sambat"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa Sambat"},"Q46864313":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Carcel de Cebu","inscription":""},"photo":null},"ceb":{"text":{"title":"Karsel sa Sugbo","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":"The Tagalog historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the museum while the Cebuano marker is located to the right.","locPhoto":{"file":"Museo Sugbo.jpg","credit":"Ringer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Carcel de Cebu","date":"2009-08-13","lon":123.90645,"lat":10.3038,"address":"Museo Sugbo, M. J. Cuenco Avenue, Cebu City"},"Q23935031":{"name":"Felipe G. Calderon","locPhoto":{"file":"Plaza Calderon, Sta Ana Manila.jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located beneath a bust of Felipe G. Calderon near the eastern end of Plaza Calderon facing the Santa Ana Church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Felipe G. Calderon historical marker.jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pedagogue, lawyer, writer, scholar and patriot. Drafted the Constitution of the first Philippine Republic. Founder of the Colegio de Abogados de Filipinas and the Escuela de Derecho de Manila, 1899. First president, Asociacion de Tagalistas, 1904. Organizer, Asociacion Historica de Filipinas, 1905. Son of Jose Gonzales Calderon and Manuela Roca born 4 April 1868 in (Santa Cruz de Malabon) Tanza, Cavite. Lived in the district of Santa Ana. Died 6 June 1908.</p>","title":"Felipe G. Calderon","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1954","address":"Plaza Calderon, Pedro Gil Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58175,"lon":121.01288},"Q23797154":{"lat":14.16552,"address":"University of the Philippines Los Baños, Pedro R. Sandoval Avenue cor. Harold Cuzner Royal Palm Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","lon":121.24213,"name":"College of Agriculture","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag upang magsagawa ng pananaliksik at pag-aaral sa agrikultura, 6 Marso 1909. Binuksan sa mga mag-aaral, 14 Hunyo 1909. Dr. Edwin B. Copeland, unang dekano 1909-1917. Itinayo ang pangunahing gusali, 21 Mayo 1911. Itinanghal na pangunahing kolehiyo ng agrikulturang tropikal sa Pilipinas ng University of Illinois, 1923. Bienvenido Ma. Gonzalez, unang Filipinong Dekano 1927-1939. Nagsilbing himpilan ng mga Hapon, 1941, at naging piitan ng mga banyagang bihag. Muling nagbukas, 25 Hulyo 1946. Naging bahagi ng bagong Unibersidad ng Pilipinas Los Banos sa Bisa ng P.D. No. 58, 20 Nobyembre 1972. Ginawaran ng Ramon Magsaysay Award, 1977. Naging sentro ng karunungang pang-agrikultura sa Asya.</p>","title":"College of Agriculture"},"photo":{"file":"UPLB College of Agriculture historical marker.jpg","credit":"Mjuadiong {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"2010"},"Q28869059":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LazatinHouse HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lazatin House","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 27 January 2003</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Lazatin House","date":"2003","lon":120.69049,"lat":15.02567,"address":"Lazatin House, S. Lazatin Street cor. Consunji Street, San Fernando, Pampanga"},"Q23779734":{"date":"2011","locPhoto":{"file":"Largest Rizal Monument (cropped).jpg","credit":"Jtcueno {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"Jose Rizal","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the monument’s pedestal.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker (Calamba monument).jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo, 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, ngunit muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang na rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>"}}},"lat":14.19586,"address":"Rizal Monument, Chipeco Avenue Extension, Calamba, Laguna","lon":121.15976},"Q51168711":{"lon":120.9633,"lat":14.95816,"address":"San Juan de Dios Church, San Rafael, Bulacan","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Battle of San Rafael (Bulacan) historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Labanan sa San Rafael"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa San Rafael","date":"1997-11-30"},"Q28912690":{"date":"2008","name":"Bantayan ng Biliran","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Biliran Watchtower historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo sa burol na ito ni Padre Gaspar Ignacio de Guevara kasama ang simbahan at kuta ng nagsilbing santuaryo ng mga mananampalataya, 1765 - 1774. Tanging natira nang sunugin ng mga piratang moro ang pook, 1774. Ginamit sa pagpapalaganap ng relihiyong komyunal sa Biliran, Leyte at Samar. Halimbawa ng arkitektura na yari sa korales at bato noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Ipinaayos, 2000.</p>","title":"Bantayan ng Biliran"}}},"lat":11.46394,"address":"Biliran Watchtower, Biliran","lon":124.47981},"Q30097970":{"date":"1966","locPhoto":null,"name":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna","inscription":"<p>On the plaza, in front of this building, formerly the Presidential Headquarters of the First Philippine Republic, General Antonio Luna and his aide Colonel Francisco Roman were assasinated in the afternoon of 5 June 1899, by members of General Emilio Aguinaldo's presidential guard.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"College of the Immaculate Conception, Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","lat":15.48919,"lon":120.96395},"Q30087463":{"date":"1976-08-30","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Pinaglabanan Shrine NHCP historical marker vicinity.jpg"},"name":"Pang-alaalang Dambana ng Pinaglabanan","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main steps of the Pinaglabanan Shrine.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Pinaglabanan Shrine NHCP historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ginawang Pambansang Dambana sa bisa ng Utos Pampangulo Blg. 260, Agosto 1, 1973.</p><p>Ang pook at bantayog ay sinimulang itayo ng Pang-alaalang Komisyon ng Pinaglabanan na itinatag sa bisa ng Utos Tagapagpaganap Blg. 394. Inilipat sa Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan noong Pebrero 4, 1974.</p>","title":"Pang-alaalang Dambana ng Pinaglabanan"}}},"address":"Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan, Metro Manila","lat":14.60475,"lon":121.03047},"Q46995384":{"date":"1973","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Nazaria Lagos historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa baryo ng Burongan, ngayo’y Jaguimit, Dueñas, Iloilo noong 28 Agosto 1851. Makabayan, at ulirang nars ng mga sugatang Pilipino noong panahon ng himagsikan sa Kabisayaan. Tinahi niya ang bandilang Pilipino na iwinagayway sa Dueñas noong 12 Hunyo 1899, unang anibersaryo ng pagpapahayag ng kalayaan ng Pilipinas. Namatay noong 27 Enero 1945.</p>","title":"Nazaria Lagos","subtitle":"(1851–1945)"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Nazaria Lagos","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.61849,"address":"Dueñas, Iloilo","lat":11.06503},"Q28878285":{"lon":123.42488,"lat":8.65524,"address":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","locDesc":null,"details":{"text":{"tl":{"title":"Casa Real","inscription":"<p>Ito ang pook na kinatatayuan ng Casa Real, ang opisyal na tahanan at gusaling pampangasiwaan ng gobernador pulitiko-militar ng purok. Dito nanahanan si Jose Rizal bilang tapon mula noong 17 Hulyo 1892 hangang Marso 1893 nang ilipat siya sa Talisay, na ngayo’y Dapitan Rizal Shrine.</p>","subtitle":null},"en":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Casa Real","inscription":"<p>This is the site of the Casa Real, official residence and administration building of the politico-military governor of the district. Here, Jose Rizal lived as an exile from July 17, 1892 to March, 1893 when he was transferred to Talisay, now the Rizal Dapitan Shrine.</p>"}},"photo":{"credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Casa Real Marker.jpg"}},"name":"Casa Real","locPhoto":null,"date":"1989"},"Q41657997":{"lon":120.91839,"address":"Gen. Alejo G. Santos Highway, Bustos, Bulacan","lat":14.95277,"date":"2012-08-02","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bulacan Military Area","inscription":"<p>Binuo sa ilalim ng East Central Luzon Guerilla Area (ECLGA) ang Bulacan Military District mula sa apat na rehimento ng puwersang gerilya na kumakatawan sa lalawigan ng Bulacan sa utos ni Maj. Edwin P. Ramsey, 14 Setyembre 1943. Capt. Alejo S. Santos, District Commander. Pinangalanang Bulacan Military Area ni Capt. Bernard L. Anderson ng USAFFE Luzon Guerilla Armed Forces, 21 Disyembre 1943. Ang apat na rehimento ng BMA ay naging sampung rehimento, 1944. Tumulong sa pakikipaglaban sa puwersang Hapon sa mga lalawigan ng Nueva Vizcaya, Pangasinan, Pampanga, Ifugao, at Rizal. Nakipaglaban sa mga Hapones hanggang mapalaya sa mga Hapon ang lalawigan ng Bulacan, Hulyo 1945.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BMA HistoricalMarker Bustos.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Bulacan Military Area"},"Q24702080":{"address":"Gumaca Cathedral, Gumaca, Quezon","lat":13.92144,"lon":122.09942,"date":"1973-11-13","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Gumaca","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1582)","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Gumaca","inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo sa pook na ito noong 1582 at inilipat sa silanga, sakop ng pulo ng Alabat noong 1638. Sinunog ng mga Olandes noong 1655. Muling itinayo ang simbahan dito noong 1690 at natapos noong 1747. Ang gusali at kombento ay inayos at pinaganda noong 1846. Kinikilalang pinakamalaki at pinakamatandang simbahang katoliko sa buong lalawigan ng Tayabas, ngayo'y Quezon.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Gumaca Cathedral historical marker.jpg","credit":"Supermakel {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q23540785":{"address":"Makati Church, Makati, Metro Manila","lat":14.56613,"lon":121.03134,"locPhoto":null,"name":"San Pedro Macati","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"San Pedro Macati","inscription":"<p>The Franciscans were the first missionaries here in 1578. The Jesuits built this church in 1620 and administered it until 1768. Adjoining were the novitiate for the Jesuits and a house of retreat. Both the church and novitiate were dedicated to San Pedro in memory of the Rev. Pedro de los Montes, builder of the church, and of Captain Pedro de Britto, Regidor of Manila, who donated the site called Buenavista in 1607 and endowed the novitiate.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Makati church marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1937"},"Q24237251":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"University of Nueva Caceres","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa daang Burgos, lungsod ng Naga sa pamumuno ni Dr. Jaime Hernandez, unang pangulo, 1948. Pinagtibay ng Securities and Exchange Commission bilang Nueva Caceres Colleges, 18 Mayo 1948. Binuksan ang sekondarya at mga kursong pangkolehiyo, 1 Hulyo 1948; elementarya at ROTC, 1949. Inilipat sa daang J. Hernandez, 1952. Unang paaralan sa Kabikulan na ginawaran ng katayuang unibersidad, 15 Disyembre 1954.</p>","title":"University of Nueva Caceres","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"University of Nueva Caceres historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2008","lat":13.62465,"address":"University of Nueva Caceres, J. Hernandez Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur","lon":123.1842},"Q46509859":{"date":"1951","name":"Lapulapu","locPhoto":{"credit":"Paolobon140 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Targa in ricordo di Lapu Lapu (Mactan).jpg"},"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Lapulapu-beschreibung.jpg","credit":"TrapperFrank {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lapulapu","inscription":"<p>Here, on 27 April 1521, Lapulapu and his men repulsed the Spanish Invaders, killing their leader, Ferdinand Magellan. Thus Lapulapu became the first Filipino to have repelled European aggression.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the pedestal inside an open building on the eastern side of the Mactan Shrine.","lat":10.31081,"address":"Mactan Shrine, Punta Engaño Road, Lapu-Lapu","lon":124.01551},"Q24702672":{"date":"2011","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the pedestal for the statue of José Rizal.","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nakilala sa tawag na Calvario, dating bahagi ng bulubundukin ng Sierra Madre na nang malaon ay nahiwalay sa pagtatabas ng lupa upang gawing kalsada. Pinakamataas na bahagi ng kabayanan na ginamit bilang bantayan at sa mga gawaing panrelihiyon noong panahon ng Espanyol. Naging punong himpilan ng mga sundalong Amerikano at bantayan ng Philippine Constabulary noong panahon ng Amerikano, at ng civilian emergency administration noong panahon ng Hapon. Itinayo ang bantayog para kay Jose Rizal, Disyembre 1925.</p>","title":"Rizal Hill Park","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Rizal Hill Park 4.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Rizal Hill Park 5.jpg"},"name":"Rizal Hill Park","lon":121.73097,"lat":14.18917,"address":"Mauban, Quezon"},"Q27043938":{"lat":13.63154,"address":"Naga Central Road, Naga, Camarines Sur","lon":123.18955,"date":"2016-02-01","locPhoto":{"file":"Jose Maria Panganiban Monument.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right side of the monument dedicated to Jose Ma. Panganiban.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Jose Ma. Panganiban historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Manunulat at pantas ng kilusang propaganda. Isinilang, 1 Pebrero 1863, Mambulao (ngayo'y Jose Panganiban), Camarines Norte. Nag-aral sa ilalim ng mga pari ng La Congregacion de La Mision de San Vicente de Paul sa Seminario Conciliar de Nueva Caceres (ngayo'y Holy Rosary Minor Seminary), Nueva Caceres (ngayo'y Lungsod ng Naga), Camarines Sur. Nag-aral ng medisina sa Barcelona, Espanya, 1888, at naging aktibo sa Kilusang Propaganda sa pamamagitan ng pagsulat ng mga artikulo sa La Solidaridad na uminog sa kalayaan sa pamamahayag at reporma sa sistema ng edukasyon sa Pilipinas. Yumao sa Barcelona, 19 Agosto 1890, na ipinagluksa ng komunidad ng mga Pilipino sa Europa.</p>","title":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","subtitle":"1863–1890"}}}},"Q48316511":{"date":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Legazpi","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Labanan sa Legazpi","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.75285,"address":"Quezon Avenue cor. Rizal Street, Legazpi, Albay","lat":13.1473},"Q24045081":{"date":"1934","name":"San Sebastian Church","locPhoto":{"file":"San Sebastian Basilica main entrance.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"San Sebastian Church (Manila) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"San Sebastian Church","inscription":"<p>Designed by Genaro Palacios. The structural metal of which this church is uniquely built was manufactured in Belgium and erected here by Belgian engineers. The church was solemnly blessed August 16, 1891. Earlier churches built on this site by Recollect friars since 1611 were destroyed by earthquake in 1859, 1863 and 1880.</p>"}}},"lat":14.59946,"address":"San Sebastian Church, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98924},"Q46993491":{"lat":14.11319,"address":"Rizal Park, Magallanes Iraya Street cor. Justo Lukban Street, Daet, Camarines Norte","lon":122.95455,"date":"1961","locPhoto":{"file":"Oldest Jose Rizal Monument in Daet, Camarines Norte by Gina Meneses.jpg","credit":"Firehorse {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"First Rizal Monument","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>First Rizal Monument in the Philippines. Erected by voluntary contributions of the People of Camarines Norte, led by Lt. Col. Ildefonso Alegre and Lt. Col. Antonio Sanz of the Revolutionary Army. Unveiled on 30 December 1898.</p>","title":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument."},"Q44949419":{"address":"Villa Escudero, Kilometer 91, Pan-Philippine Highway, Tiaong, Quezon","lat":13.99521,"lon":121.34222,"name":"Villa Escudero","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Villa Escudero","subtitle":null},"photo":null},"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Villa Escudero","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1984-06-03"},"Q37963698":{"lon":120.98908,"address":"Goldenberg Mansion, General Solano Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59189,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Goldenberg Mansion","inscription":"<p>Built by the Eugster Family from whom it was acquired by the Oidor de la Audiencia, Jose Moreno Lacalle; successively occupied by Admiral Patricio Montojo of the Spanish Navy, 1897–1898, later by the Spanish Royal Navy Club, 1898. Home and Headquarters of General Arthur McArthur, 1899. Became the Offices of the Philippine Preliminary Exposition to the International Exposition, St. Louis, Mo., U.S.A., 1903–1904. Housed the Philippine School of Commerce, 1908. The First Philippine Senate held its sessions here, Oct. 16, 1916. Bought and occupied by Michael Goldenberg, 1950.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Goldenberg Mansion","locPhoto":null,"date":"1957"},"Q25069494":{"lon":120.91866,"address":"Alapan I Elementary School, Alapan Street, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.41572,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument of a lady brandishing the Philippine flag on top of a rocky ground with three stars depicting Luzon, Mindanao and Panay.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this site, on May 28, 1898, between 10:00 A.M. to 3:00 P.M., a bloody encounter ensued between Filipino Revolutionary forces and approximately 270 Spanish Marines, this battle, which resulted in the triumph of Filipino Forces, was taken as a glorious occasion for General Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy to display the Philippine flag for the first time at Cavite Nuevo.</p>","title":"Battle of Alapan"},"photo":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Battle of Alapan Historical Marker in Alapan Elementary School.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Battle of Alapan Monument.jpg"},"name":"Battle of Alapan","date":"1998-05-28"},"Q24262125":{"lon":120.9874,"lat":14.59892,"address":"Nazarene Catholic School, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1847–1923)","title":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna","inscription":"<p>Pintor, manunulat, mambabatas at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa San Isidro, Nueva Ecija noong Setyembre 29, 1847. Nag-aral sa Ateneo Municipal de Manila at Academia de Dibujo y Pintura, 1859. Isa sa mga pensyonado ng pamahalaan sa larangan ng sining na pinag-aral sa Academia de San Fernando, Madrid, Espanya, 1879 at sa Roma, 1882. Sumapi sa Kilusang Propaganda sa Roma at bumalik sa Espanya, 1885. Umuwi sa Pilipinas at muling binuhay ang magasing, La Ilustracion Filipina, 1891. Ilan sa kanyang mga pintura: A Roman Laborer; The Death of St. Francis Xavier at St. Peter Chavez; Highway Men; at 'El Violencellista.' Ang dalawa sa labingdalawa niyang lahok ay nagwagi ng ginto at pilak na medalya sa Eksposisyon sa St. Louis, 1904. Naging propesor: Ateneo Municipal, 1891; Escuela Superior de Pintura, Esculturo y Grabado, 1893; Liceo de Manila, 1900; at isa sa unang tatlong propesor ng U.P. School of Fine Arts, 1909. Nahirang na kagawad sa Kongreso ng Malolos, 1898 at isa sa lumagda ng Saligang Batas ng Unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Namatay noong Marso, 1923.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna","date":"1989"},"Q24838207":{"date":"1952","name":"Municipality of Lemery","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Municipality of Lemery historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Municipality of Lemery","inscription":"<p>The town of Lemery was founded in 1862 during the administration of Governor General Jose Lemery. Jose Cabrera was it's first Gobernadorcillo. Others were Miguel Agoncillo, Eleno Aniversario, Basilio Gatachalian, Mariano Generoso, Perpetuo Ilustre, Mariano Marella, Juan Medina, Brigido Morales, Ramon M. Mitra, Ramon Noble, Victoriano Noble, Agapito Panganiban, and Pioquinto Reyes.</p><p>Lemery was annexed to the municipality of Taal in 1904.</p><p>Again became a municipality in 1907 with Perpetuo de Joya as Municipal President.</p><p>The eruption of nearby Taal volcano in January 1911 killed hundreds of its inhabitants.</p><p>Occupied by the Japanese imperial army in 1942, One third of the town was burnt by enemy artillery when it was liberated by the Americans aided by Filipino Guerillas on 6 March 1945.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Lemery, Batangas","lat":13.88367,"lon":120.914},"Q28927264":{"lon":123.42497,"lat":8.6546,"address":"Dapitan Church, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","date":"1989","details":{"photo":{"file":"Saint James Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"en":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this spot of Saint James Church constructed by the Jesuits in 1871, Jose Rizal stood while hearing mass every Sunday during his exile in Dapitan in 1892–1896.</p>","title":null},"tl":{"subtitle":null,"title":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Simbahan ng San Jaime na ipinagawa ng mga Heswita noong 1871, tumayo si Jose Rizal tuwing Linngo upang makinig ng misa sa buong panahon ng kanyang pagkapatapon sa Dapitan, 1892–1896.</p>"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"José Rizal at Dapitan Church","locPhoto":null},"Q28855210":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Manuel Severino Hofileña Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 3 dated April 6, 1993 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Hofileña Ancestral House 03.JPG","credit":"Claire Algarme {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Manuel Severino Hofileña Ancestral House","date":"1993","lon":122.97427,"lat":10.80198,"address":"Hofileña Ancestral House, Silay, Negros Occidental"},"Q22341049":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker of the baptistery of Calamba Church.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Resolusyon bilang 2, Agosto 19, 1976, ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan na binigyan ng karapatan ng Seksyon 4 ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang bahaging ito ng Simbahan ng Kalamba ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palantandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Pabinyagan ng Simbahan Katoliko ng Kalamba","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Pabinyagan ng Simbahan Katoliko ng Kalamba","locPhoto":null,"date":"1976","lon":121.16747,"lat":14.21375,"address":"Calamba Church, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna"},"Q52025927":{"name":"Colegio del Buen Consejo","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa pook na dating Beaterio de Santa Rita de Pasig sa pamumuno ni Madre Superyor Consuelo Barcelo, O.S.A. at ipinamahala sa mga Filipinong madre sa pangunguna ni Sor Teresa de Jesus Andrada, O.S.A., 10 Marso 1909. Pinasinayaan sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora del Buen Consejo, 26 Abril 1909. Naging kanlungan ng mga mamamayan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; nasira noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Muling ipinaayos, 1948.</p>","title":"Colegio del Buen Consejo","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Colegio del Buen Consejo.jpg"}}},"date":"2009","lat":14.5602,"address":"Colegio del Buen Consejo, A. Luna Street cor. R. Jabson Street, Pasig, Metro Manila","lon":121.07639},"Q25906814":{"lon":120.98361,"lat":14.59849,"address":"Quiapo Church, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Church of Quiapo historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Quiapo","inscription":"<p>Governor General Santiago de Vera founded the District of Quiapo August 29, 1586. Franciscan missionaries built the first Church, of bamboo and nipa, that was burned in 1639. Rebuilding and repairs at intervals gave the parish the stronger edifice that the earthquake of 1863 partially destroyed. The next Church, completed in 1899, was the work of Rev. Eusebio de Leon and Rev. Manuel Roxas, the latter raising ₱40,000.00 in contributons. A fire on October 30, 1929, left the Church only its scarred walls and belfry, and a parish committee headed by Doña Encarnacion Nakpil de Orense raised the funds for its reconstruction. Juan F. Nakpil, architect, drafted the plans for the reconstructed building. A famous image of Christ bearing the Cross, called the Nazarene, is the center of intense Friday devotions througout the year.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church at the base of the left tower.","locPhoto":{"file":"0208jfQuiapo Central Church Plaza Manila Bridge Riverfvf 09.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"Church of Quiapo","date":"1939"},"Q24845880":{"date":"2013-02-08","locPhoto":null,"name":"Clemencia Castelo Lopez","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1872–1963)","title":"Clemencia Castelo Lopez","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Balayan, Batangas, 23 Nobyembre 1872. Kasama ang kapatid na si Sixto, nagtungo sa Estados Unidos bilang panauhin ng American Anti-Imperialist League, 1902-1903. Nanawagan kay Pangulong Theodore Roosevelt para sa pagpapalaya ng kanyang mga kapatid at pagsalungat sa hindi makatarungang pagdakip sa mga ito, Marso 1902. Nagbigay ng testimonya sa Senado ng Estados Unidos upang tutulan ang pagsakop sa Pilipinas, 15 Marso 1902. Nagtalumpati sa pulong ng New England Women Suffrage Association, 29 Mayo 1902. Bumalik sa Pilipinas, 1904. Isa sa mga nanguna sa pagtatag ng Asociacion Feminista Filipina, 30 Hunyo 1905. Tagapagtaguyod ng karapatan ng mga kababaihan sa Pilipinas. Yumao 4 Hunyo 1963.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Balayan, Batangas","lat":13.94053,"lon":120.73597},"Q24727895":{"lon":120.52321,"lat":15.17983,"address":"Angeles","date":"2003","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"0520jfFort Stotsenburg Parkfvf 23.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(Fort Stotsenburg)","title":"Clark Field","inscription":"<p>Dating pati o pamayanan ng mga Aeta. Naging Camp Stotsenburg bilang paggunita kay Col. John Miller Stotsenburg ng 1st Nebraska Regiment, 1902. Lupang-laan para sa hukbo ng Estados Unidos, 1 Setyembre 1903. Nagtayo ng paliparan at tinawag na Clark Field bilang paggunita sa pilotong si Maj. Harold Merville Clar, 1919. Sinalakay ng mga Hapon, 8 Disyembre 1941. Pook ng labanan ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Pilipino at Hapon. 1945, nanatili sa pamamahala ng Estados Unidos ayon sa kasunduang base militar ng RP-US, 1947. Clark Air Force Base, 1949. Isinara, 1991. Naging Clark Special Economic Zone, 1992.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Clark Field"},"Q46993559":{"date":"1990-02-20","name":"Ang Bahay na Sinilangan ni Pangulong Diosdado Macapagal","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AbDiosdado Macapagal.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Ang Bahay na Sinilangan ni Pangulong Diosdado Macapagal","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.93935,"address":"President Diosdado P. Macapagal Library and Museum, Lubao, Pampanga","lon":120.60037},"Q23665520":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Fort of San Pedro historical marker context.jpg"},"name":"Fort of San Pedro","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of Fort San Pedro.","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Fort of San Pedro","inscription":"<p>The Fort of San Pedro, described in an official report of 1739, is triangular in shape and made of stone and mortar. The three bastions are La Concepcion, San Ignacio de Loyola, and San Miguel–Powder Magazine.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Fort of San Pedro historical marker (perspective corrected).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"date":"1939","address":"Fort San Pedro, Cebu City","lat":10.29264,"lon":123.90563},"Q47069817":{"lon":120.68726,"lat":15.02431,"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"1982-12-11","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"PampangaProvincialCapitoljf56.JPG"},"text":{"title":"Lalawigan ng Pampanga","inscription":"","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Lalawigan ng Pampanga","locPhoto":null},"Q24764629":{"lat":13.78967,"address":"Bauan Church, Bauan, Batangas","lon":121.00781,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Bauan","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Bauan Church in Batangas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The parish of Bauan was administered by the Augustinians from 1596 to the end of the nineteenth century. The church built in the eighteenth century, remodelled and improved by the Rev. Hipolito Huerta and the Rev. Felipe Bravo in the nineteenth century was destroyed by fire on July 13, 1928. The eminent botanist Father Blanco was pastor of this church from 1816 to 1828. Under his administration great impetus was given to the home industries of weaving and dyeing. The Museum of Natural History and the Library of Rare Books collected by Father Bravo were destroyed during the insurrection of 1898.</p>","title":"Church of Bauan","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1939"},"Q36141914":{"lon":120.96791,"lat":14.59889,"address":"Lavezares Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This house was occupied by Dr. Pio Valenzuela together with Ulpiano Fernandez and Faustino Duque, Filipino printers who turned out for Dr. Valenzuela and Emilio Jacinto 2,000 copies of the newspaper entitled \"Ang Kalayaan,\" giving Yokohama as the place of publication to evade suspicion. The first issue was dated January 18, 1896, but was not circulated until the middle of March. The second issue, in preparation, was seized by the Spanish authorities when the revolution broke out that year. </p><p> Original house destroyed February 1945, in the battle of Liberation of Manila in the Second World War.</p>","title":"Where “Ang Kalayaan” Was Printed"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Where Ang Kalayaan was Printed.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Where “Ang Kalayaan” Was Printed","locPhoto":null,"date":"1941"},"Q24702389":{"lat":11.15926,"address":"Palo Cathedral, Palo, Leyte","lon":124.99163,"name":"The Cathedral of Palo","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"The Cathedral of Palo","inscription":"<p>Constructed, 1596 under the direction of the Jesuits who founded Palo. Used for some time as their residence. Taken over by the Augustinians, 1768; by the Franciscans, 1843. Repaired by Fr. Agustin de Consuegra, who built the two towers, 1850; by Fr. Pantaleon de la Fuente, who installed a clock on the facade, 1896. Proclaimed a cathedral, 25 March 1938. Msgr. Manuel Mascariñas, first bishop. Used as hospital, October, 1944 to March, 1945, by American Liberation forces.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"The Cathedral of Palo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Jojit Ballesteros; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1954"},"Q46993504":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Martir ng Camarines Norte","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Martyrs of Camarines Norte historical marker in Daet.jpg","credit":"User:Alhorin {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Alaala sa mga Katipuneros at mga dakilang anak ng Daet at mga karatig bayan na nag-alay ng buhay para sa Inang Bayan noong 1898: Ildefonso Moreno, Tomas Zaldua, Telesforo Zaldua, Marianito Zaldua, Jose Abaño, Jacinto Rada, Vicente Salveria, Isidro Avila, Gavino Saavedra, Domingo Lozada, Angel Zaleta, Gregorio del Valle at Florante Bacerdo at marami pang iba.</p>","title":"Martir ng Camarines Norte"}}},"date":"1992","lat":14.11352,"address":"Rizal Park, Magallanes Iraya Street cor. Justo Lukban Street, Daet, Camarines Norte","lon":122.95433},"Q28927638":{"lon":122.01367,"address":"Zamboanga City","lat":6.92748,"date":"1952","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Zamboanga Beach historical marker 01.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Zamboanga Beach","inscription":"<p>Here on the 10th of March, 1945 the 41st Division, U.S. Army under the command of Maj. Gen. Jens A. Doe landed in order to liberate the City of Zamboanga from the Japanese Forces. Liberation completed on the 12th of March, 1945.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Zamboanga Beach"},"Q36164177":{"date":"2010-04-14","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Established through the cooperation of Ford and Rockefeller Foundations and the Philippine Government to launch an intensive research and development for new methods of rice production, 1960. Dr. Robert F. Chandler, First Director General, 1960–1971. Played a major role in initiating the green revolution in Asia. Successfully bred a new type of rice, IR 8 or Miracle Rice that improved the production of rice in the Philippines, 29 November 1966. It is a major world center of scientific research on rice.</p>","title":"International Rice Research Institute","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"IRRI historical marker 2.jpg"}},"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"IRRI historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Naitatag mula sa pagtutulungan ng Ford at Rockefeller Foundation at ng Pamahalaan ng Pilipinas upang maglunsad ng malawakang pananaliksik at pagpapaunlad ng makabagong pamamaraan sa produksyon ng palay, 1960. Dr. Robert F. Chandler, Jr., unang direktor heneral, 1960–1971. Kabalikat sa paglulunsad ng Green Revolution sa Asya. Matagumpay na nakapaglikha ng bagong uri ng palay, IR8 o Miracle Rice, na nakapagpataas ng produksyon ng palay sa Pilipinas, 29 Nobyembre 1966. Pandaigdigang sentro ng pag-aaral sa agham ng pagtatanim ng palay.</p>","title":"International Rice Research Institute"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"International Rice Research Institute","lon":121.25524,"address":"International Rice Research Institute, Pili Drive, Los Baños, Laguna","lat":14.16883},"Q41079362":{"date":"1989-02-03","locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Pagpapalaya ng Maynila","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Pagpapalaya ng Maynila","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pagpapalaya sa Maynila.jpg"}}},"address":"Postigo Street cor. Arzobispo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59101,"lon":120.97248},"Q28942552":{"lon":119.84925,"address":"Sheik Karimol Makhdum Mosque, Simunul, Tawi-Tawi","lat":4.89805,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque","inscription":"<p>Sinasabi ng mga mananalaysay na ang Islam ay pinalakas sa Pilipinas ni Sheik Makhdum, isang misyonerong Arabe, unang lumunsad sa Tubig-Indangan, Simunul sa pulo ng Tawi-Tawi noong 1380. Dito niya ipinatayo ang kauna-unahang simbahang Muslim sa kapuluan ng Pilipinas na hangang sa kasalukuyan ay nakatayo bilang bahagi ng muling ipinagawang “Tahanan ni Allah.” Pinaniniwalaang ang orihinal na simbahan ay nagtagal ng humigit-kumulan sa 500 taon. Ang orihinal na haligi ay yari sa ipil at pinangangalagaan hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque","date":"1980"},"Q28865543":{"date":"2003","name":"Hizon-Singian House","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Hizon-SingianHouse HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Hizon-Singian House","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 27 January 2003</p>"}}},"locDesc":null,"lat":15.02669,"address":"Hizon-Singian House, Consuji, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.69188},"Q23821137":{"date":"1936","name":"Former Palace of the Governors General","locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This site was formerly occupied by the stately residence of Captain Manuel Estacio Venegas, Secretary to Governor General Diego Fajardo. Venegas died on March 7, 1660, a prisoner at Fort Santiago. His residence was confiscated and became the Palace of the Governors of the Philippine Islands until its destruction by the earthquake of June 3, 1863. These foundations, intended for the new gubernatorial palace, were abandoned when it was decided to make Malacañan the permanent residence of the Governors General.</p>","title":"Former Palace of the Governors General"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker Palacio del Gobernador.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.59185,"address":"Palacio del Gobernador, General Luna Street cor. Andres Soriano Jr. Avenue, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97274},"Q46570505":{"lon":122.42786,"lat":11.52824,"address":"Altavas, Aklan","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Pagdakip kay Heneral Ananias Diokno"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Pagdakip kay Heneral Ananias Diokno","locPhoto":null,"date":"2013-08-30"},"Q39024392":{"address":"Kabesang Pino Street cor. Kabesang Imo Street, Pariancillo Villa, Valenzuela, Metro Manila","lat":14.70855,"lon":120.94515,"date":"1966","locPhoto":null,"name":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela","inscription":"","subtitle":"1869–1956 Dakilang Katipunero at Lingkod ng Bayan"},"photo":{"file":"FvfValenzuelaCity1826 31.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q44820798":{"lon":120.47691,"address":"Juan Luna Shrine, Rizal Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","lat":17.92725,"date":"1957","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Juan Luna historical marker in Badoc.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Birthplace of Juan Luna y Novicio","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Birthplace of Juan Luna y Novicio"},"Q24081292":{"date":"1989-08-08","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Carlos","inscription":"<p>Ang simbahang gawa sa ladrillo ay sinimulang itatag noong 1770 sa pamamahala ni P. Ausina, sa pook na ito kung saan inilipat ang kabayanang Binalatongan, na pinangalanang San Carlos noong 1764. Pinakamalaking simbahan sa Pilipinas sa panahong iyon. Napinsala ng lindol noong 1789, 1796 at 1799. Ang pagtatayo ng kampanaryo at pagsasagawa ng mga pagbabago ay pinamahalaan ni Padre Alvarez Carrozal, 1878-1890.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Simbahan ng San Carlos historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng San Carlos","lon":120.34719,"lat":15.92594,"address":"Saint Dominic de Guzman Parish Church, San Carlos, Pangasinan"},"Q28877414":{"date":"2011","locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Lumang Bayan ng Dapitan","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Old Town of Dapitan historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Lumang Bayan ng Dapitan","inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag na Heritage Zone / Historic Center ng pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 24 Mayo 2011 sa bisa ng NHCP Board Resolution No. 3 S. 2011.</p>"}}},"lat":8.64714,"address":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lon":123.4218},"Q43245232":{"date":"1997","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on an inclined pedestal to the left of the southern stairway of the monument.","name":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"13Cavitejf0322 07.JPG"},"lon":120.87079,"lat":14.2809,"address":"Governor’s Drive cor. City Hall Road, Trece Martires, Cavite"},"Q40311869":{"address":"Gen. Luna Street cor. Anda Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59028,"lon":120.97441,"date":"1995","locPhoto":null,"name":"Memorare – Manila 1945","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker Memorare Manila 1945.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Memorare – Manila 1945","inscription":""}}}},"Q46872637":{"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Silva House","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Silva House","date":"2010-05-29","lon":123.64113,"lat":10.10457,"address":"Silva House, Jose Rizal Street, Carcar, Cebu"},"Q43217957":{"lat":14.67934,"address":"Balanga Cathedral, Aguirre Street cor. J.P. Rizal Street, Balanga, Bataan","lon":120.54062,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of Balanga","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Balanga","inscription":"<p>The spiritual ministration of Balanga formerly belonged to Abucay. Balanga became an independent missionary center in 1739. Rev. Benito Rivas, O.P., strengthened this church by fortifying its wall. Rev. Juan Antonio Vicente, O.P., roofed it with galvanized iron and decorated the interior. Rev. Fernaldo Ma. Miñano, O.P., from 1838–45 constructed the arch of the choir loft and made the baptismal font out of granite from Mariveles. The parochial ministration under the Filipino clergy started with Rev. Mariano Sarili, June 2, 1898.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Balanga historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1940"},"Q41081703":{"lon":120.97224,"lat":14.59092,"address":"Postigo Street cor. Sta. Lucia Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1968","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pintong Postigo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Pintong Postigo"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pintong Postigo"},"Q44452718":{"date":"1984-05-19","name":"Simbahan ng Lazi","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Lazi Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Lazi"}}},"locDesc":null,"address":"Lazi Church, Lazi, Siquijor","lat":9.12765,"lon":123.6335},"Q37707492":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Tejeros Convention House.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"name":"The Tejeros Convention","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right facade of the convention house.","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Tejeros Convention Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"The Tejeros Convention","inscription":"<p>A revolutionary assembly was held March 22, 1897 in the building known as the Casa Hacienda of Tejeros. That once stood on this site. Presided over by Andress Bonifacio. Toward the end of the session, the assembly decided to establish a central revolutionary government and elected Emilio Aguinaldo, president; Mariano Trias, vice president; Artemio Ricarte, captain general;; Emiliano Riego de Dios, Director of War; and Andres Bonifacio, Director of the Interior. Certain events arising in the convention caused Bonifacio to bolt its action.</p>"}}},"date":"1941","lat":14.40119,"address":"General Trias Drive, Rosario, Cavite","lon":120.86072},"Q23677500":{"date":"1941","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"20170812160609!Magellan's Cross historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}"},"text":{"title":"The Cross of Magellan","inscription":"<p>From time immemorial this spot has been set aside to commemorate the erection of a Cross in Cebu by the expedition of Magellan, when King Humabon of Cebu and his Queen, son and daughters, together with some 800 of their subjects were baptized by Father Pedro Valderrama. This hallowed site was improved in 1735 by Rev. Juan Albarran, Prior of San Agustin and in 1834 by Rt. Rev. Santos Gomez Marañon, Bishop of Cebu. The image of the Santo Niño found by the expedition of Legaspi in a house near the present site of the Cathedral of Cebu is venerated by the faithful in the nearby Church of San Agustin.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located above the southern entrance of the building housing the cross.","locPhoto":{"file":"Magellan's Cross Cebu.jpg","credit":"Kingphoto23 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"name":"The Cross of Magellan","lon":123.90193,"lat":10.29354,"address":"Magellan's Cross, Cebu City"},"Q29018590":{"date":"1983","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Maasin Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang pook na ito ay itinatag ng mga misyonerong Heswita noong 1700. Isang pansamantalang simbahan ang ipinatayo subalit ito ay nasira nang sumalakay ang mga Moro noong 1754. Ang Maasin ay naging bayan nang sumunod na taon. Noong 1768 ang pangasiwaan ng simbahan ay inilipat sa mga paring Agustino. Ang simbahan ay muling ipinatayo noong 1771 subalit muling sinira ng mga Moro noong 1784. Sa pangangasiwa ni Padre Serapio Gonzales isang simbahang bato ang itinayo. Ito ay muling nagiba. Noong 1839 si Padre Jose Paco ay nagpatayo ng bagong simbahan na nasunog noong 1882. Muling ipinagawa. Ito ay naging katedral nang maging sede ng bagong Diyosesis ang Maasin noong Agosto 14, 1968. Patrona nito ang Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion.</p>","title":"Katedral ng Maasin","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Katedral ng Maasin","lon":124.83816,"address":"Maasin Cathedral, Maasin, Southern Leyte","lat":10.13255},"Q24927356":{"lat":14.44774,"address":"Baldomero Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit, Cavite","lon":120.92351,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Ang Bahay ni Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bahay ni Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo","inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito na ipinatayo noong 1906 nanirahan si Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo at kanyang mag-anak. Unang ipinatayo na yari sa Narra at Molave, ang bahay ay pinanumbalik ng Intramuros Administration. Noong 1982 ito ay ipinagkaloob ng Punong Ministro Cesar E.A. Virata sa Pamahalaan ng Pilipinas.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Baldomero Aguinaldo House Marker 1.jpg"}}},"date":"1983-06-12"},"Q43357307":{"lon":120.58659,"address":"Dominican Hill Retreat House, Dominican Hill Road, Baguio","lat":16.40402,"date":"2014-09-01","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Diplomat Hotel Marker.JPG","credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Dominican Hill and Retreat House","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo bilang bahay bakasyunan ng mga Dominikano sa Dominican Hill sa Baguio, 1913–1915. Idinisenyo ni Fr. Roque Ruaño , O.P.; pinasinayaan, 1915. Ginawang paaralan at pinangalanang Colegio del Santissimo Rosario, 1915–1918. Nagsilbing kanlungan ng mga pamilya at paring Dominikano noong panahon ng Hapon, 1942–1945. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang huling tanggulan, 1945. Binomba ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Abril 1945; ipinaayos, 1945–1947. Ginawang Diplomat Hotel, 1973–1987. Inilipat ang pagmamamay-ari sa Lungsod ng Baguio, 2005.</p>","subtitle":"(1915)"}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dominican Hill and Retreat House"},"Q24702505":{"name":"Church of Lucban","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Lucban","inscription":"<p>The first church, built in 1595, was ruined in 1629. The second church was constructed between 1630 and 1640, but was seriously damaged by fire in 1733. The present church was completed in 1738 and the convent in 1743.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"St. Louis Bishop Parish Marker Lucban, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"date":"1939","address":"Lucban Church, Lucban, Quezon","lat":14.11503,"lon":121.55397},"Q22082854":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Fort of San Antonio Abad - historical marker vicinity.jpg"},"name":"Fort of San Antonio Abad","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall below a statue of St. Anthony the Great and to the right of the southern entrance of the fort.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Fort of San Antonio Abad","inscription":"<p>The origin of this fort dates from 1584. It was captured by the British in 1762 and rebuilt at the beginning of the nineteenth century, when it was called La Polvorista because it was used as powder magazine. The first battalion of the First Colorado Regiment, under the command of Lt. Col. McCoy, took possession of this fort and hoisted the American flag over it on August 13, 1898.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Fort of San Antonio Abad - historic plaque.JPG","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"date":"1937","address":"Fort San Antonio Abad, Roxas Boulevard, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.56244,"lon":120.98689},"Q50086781":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"","title":"Simbahan ng Camalig"}}},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng Camalig","date":"2014-12-15","lon":123.65474,"address":"Camalig Church, R. Nasol Street cor. B. Buena Street, Camalig, Albay","lat":13.18209},"Q39772690":{"locPhoto":null,"name":"Dental Profession in the Philippines","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Dental Profession in the Philippines","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"PDA marker, Makati 2.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"1961","lat":14.56366,"address":"Ayala Avenue Extension cor. Kamagong Street, Makati, Metro Manila","lon":121.01584},"Q44303134":{"date":"2007","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Bulacan","inscription":""},"photo":{"file":"JC Bulakan 12.jpg","credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Bulacan","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.87942,"lat":14.79499,"address":"Our Lady of Assumption Church, Bulakan, Bulacan"},"Q48370942":{"date":"2017-12-11","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Pook Kung Saan Sinulat ang “Filipinas”, Liriko ng Pambansang Awit","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito sinulat si Jose Palma y Velasquez ang tulang “Filipinas” na naging liriko sa wikang Espanyol ng Himno Nacional Filipina, ngayo’y pambansang awit ng Pilipinas. Nalathala sa pahayagang La Independecia, 3 Setyembre 1899. Ang nasabing pook ay itinatag bilang Munisipalidad ng Bautista noong 1900.</p>","subtitle":"Bautista, Pangasinan"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Pook Kung Saan Sinulat ang “Filipinas”, Liriko ng Pambansang Awit","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.47628,"address":"Bautista, Pangasinan","lat":15.81022},"Q41231668":{"address":"Roque Ablan Shrine, A. Bonifacio Street, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.19222,"lon":120.59885,"date":"2006","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Gov. Roque Ablan Sr. Shrine3.JPG"},"name":"Roque B. Ablan","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the Roque Ablan monument.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Gov. Roque Ablan Sr. Shrine2.JPG","credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Isinilang sa Laoag, Ilocos Norte, 9 Agosto 1906. Nagtapos sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas ng Pilosopiya, 1929, at ng Abogasya, 1930; pumasa sa pagsusulit sa bar ng taon ding iyon. Inihalal na gobernador ng Ilocos Norte, 1937 at 1941. Kasama si Tenyente Feliciano Madamba, binuo ang Ablan-Madamba Guerilla Group of Northern Luzon, Enero 1942. Nanguna sa mga labanan kabilang ang matagumpay na Labanan sa Pampanniki, Solsona, Ilocos Norte, 8 Nobyembre 1941. Huling nakita sa Labanan sa Bumitalag, Piddig, 5 Pebrero 1943.</p>","title":"Roque B. Ablan","subtitle":null}}}},"Q43302605":{"date":"1978","name":"Paul P. de la Gironiere","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Paul P. de la Gironiere","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Paul de la Gironière Estate historical marker 2.jpg"}}},"lat":14.3538,"address":"Jalajala, Rizal","lon":121.32136},"Q28869091":{"lat":14.58,"address":"Luneta Hotel, 414 Kalaw Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.9781,"date":"2014-05-09","name":"Luneta Hotel","locPhoto":{"file":"Luneta Hotel main entrance.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Luneta Hotel historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Luneta Hotel","inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Salvador Farre. Binuksan bilang isang otel, 1919. Dito namalagi ang mga kalahok sa XXXIII International Eucharistic Congress, 1937. Ginawang Noncommissioned Officer’s Club ng mga Amerikano, Hulyo 1941. Isa sa mga naunang mataas na kongkretong gusali sa Maynila noong pangalawang dekada ng ika-20 dantaon. Halimbawa ng istilong French Renaissance.</p>"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall between the two main doorways of the hotel."},"Q51923657":{"name":"Church of Antipolo","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AntipoloChurchjf5277 04.JPG"},"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Antipolo","inscription":"<p>The first Missionaries of Antipolo were Franciscans. The Jesuits administered the Church from 1591 to 1768. Built by Rev. Juan de Salazar, S.J., the church was ready for Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje in 1632. The church was greatly damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1639 and in the earthquakes of 1645, 1824 and 1863. For three centuries now, this church has been the object of religious pilgrimages all over the Philippines. The famous historians PP. Pedro Chirino, S.J., and Pedro Murillo Velarde, S.J., ministered in Antipolo.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AntipoloChurchjf5277 05.JPG"}}},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the northern corner of the cathedral facade.","date":"1937","address":"Antipolo Cathedral, Antipolo, Rizal","lat":14.58778,"lon":121.1764},"Q44643834":{"lon":118.72988,"lat":9.74059,"address":"Immaculate Conception Cathedral, Rizal Avenue, Puerto Princesa","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"San Ezekiel Moreno","inscription":"<p>Paring Agustino Rekoleto at santo. Isinilang sa La Rioja, Espanya, 9 Abril 1848. Dumating sa Maynila, 10 Pebrero 1870. Naordenahang pari sa Katedral ng Maynila, 2 Hunyo 1871. Kabilang sa mga nagtatag ng bayan ng Puerto Princesa bilang unang misyonero, kapelyan ng mga militar at ng colonya penal, 4 Marso 1872. Mula 1873 hanggang 1885, naging kura paroko ng Calapan (Mindoro), Las Piñas, Santo Tomas (Batangas), Sta. Cruz (Maynila) at tagapamahala ng Hacienda ng Imus. Yumao sa Espanya sa sakit na kanser, 19 Agosto 1906. Idineklarang santo ni Papa Juan Pablo II dahil sa ipinakitang kabanalan, kapuri-puring halimbawa, at taospusong pagsilbi sa mga kapuspalad at mga maysakit sa Pilipinas, Espanya at Colombia, 11 Oktubre 1992. Itinuturing na santo at patron ng mga may kanser.</p>","subtitle":"1848–1906"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"San Ezekiel Moreno","locPhoto":null,"date":"2014-12-08"},"Q47721120":{"lat":15.02468,"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.68679,"date":"2009","locPhoto":null,"name":"Honorio Ventura","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"HonorioVentura HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Honorio Ventura","inscription":"","subtitle":"(1887–1940)"}}},"locDesc":null},"Q24727862":{"lon":120.51867,"address":"Clark Freeport Zone, Angeles","lat":15.179,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this Base, at then official residence of the Commanding General of the United States 13th Air Force, Manuel Roxas, First President of the Republic of the Philippines, soldier, statesman and exponent of Philippine-American friendship, died on 15 April 1948.</p>","title":"Death Place of Roxas"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Death Place of Roxas historical marker.jpg"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Death Place of Roxas","locPhoto":null,"date":"1955"},"Q24710143":{"lon":121.39658,"lat":13.82501,"address":"San Juan, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(San Juan de Bocboc)","inscription":"<p>Dating nasa Pinagbayanan. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang pook sa kahilingan ng mamamayan dahil sa madalas na pagbaha ng mga ilog Bancoro at Bangbang at tuluyang paglubog sa tubig ng dating kabayanan noong taong 1883. Ang paglipat ay pinagtibay ng Gobernador Heneral noong Disyembre 12, 1890 sa panahon ng panunungkulan ng Gobernadorsilyo Benedicto de Villa. Naging San Juan de Bolboc sa bisa ng Batas Lehislatibo bilang 2390, Pebrero 28, 1914; San Juan de Nepomuceno bilang parangal sa patron ng bayan, nang mga unang taon ng 1920; at ngayon ay bayan ng San Juan.</p>","title":"Bayan ng San Juan"},"photo":{"file":"Municipality of San Juan historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locDesc":null,"name":"Bayan ng San Juan","locPhoto":null,"date":"1990-12-12"},"Q46883970":{"address":"Mambukal, Murcia, Negros Occidental","lat":10.51222,"lon":123.10353,"date":"2006","name":"Ishiwata Bath House","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Ishiwata Bath House.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo bilang bahagi ng Mambukal Resort na may disenyong neo-classical ni Kokichi Paul Ishiwata, 1927. Mula sa Bundok Kanlaon ang tubig na dumaloy sa anim na kubol na may paliguan, mga tanging nalalabing orihinal na istruktura.</p>","title":"Ishiwata Bath House"}}},"locDesc":null},"Q37978616":{"date":"2014","name":"Andres Bonifacio","locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)","inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897. Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","title":"Andres Bonifacio"},"photo":null}},"locDesc":null,"lat":20.37428,"address":"National Road, Ivana, Batanes","lon":121.91592},"Q29018378":{"date":"2007","locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa Catubig","locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dito nakipaglaban ang mga gerilyang Filipino sa puwersang Amerikano, 15-18 Abril 1900. Pinaligiran ng mga Filipino ang destakamento ng kalaban hanggang mapatalsik ang mga ito. Marami ang napatay samantalang tumakas ang naiwan hanggang nailigtas ng ibang pwersang Amerikano. Isa sa matagumpay na labanang naganap sa kasaysayan ng pambansang pagkilos para sa kalayaan noong panahon ng Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Catubig"}}},"lat":12.40759,"address":"Catubig, Northern Samar","lon":125.0545},"Q23421195":{"lat":14.55586,"address":"Nielson Tower, Makati Avenue, Makati, Metro Manila","lon":121.02464,"date":"1996","name":"Nielson Tower","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NielsonTower HistoricalMarker MakatiCity.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Nielson Tower","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo noong 1937 sa lupaing pag-aari ng mga Ayala at Cia. Ang Nielson Tower ay nagsilbing himpilang pampasahero at sentro ng pamamahala ng Paliparang Nielson. Ginamit mula 1937 hanggang 1947. Ang paliparang ito ang unang makabago at komersyal na paliparang pandaigdig sa bansa at sa magkahiwalay na panahon, ito ay naging punong himpilan ng kapwa hukbong sandatahan ng Hapon at ng Estados Unidos. Sa muling pagsasaayos ng gusali, pinanatili ng Ayala Group of Companies ang orihinal na arkitektura nito bago magkadigma upang magsilbing tagapagpagunita sa pangunguna nito sa larangan ng transportasyon at komunikasyon.</p><p>Ngayon, ang gusaling ito ang kinalalagyan ng Filipinas Heritage Library at nagsisilbing kawing ng bansa sa daigdig sa pamamagitan ng ugnayang pangkaalaman.</p>","subtitle":null}}}},"Q50377908":{"lon":120.9791,"lat":14.59533,"address":"Manila Central Post Office, Magallanes Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1994-06-02","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ManilaCentralPostOfficejf1446 15.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Philippine Post Office","inscription":""}}},"locPhoto":null,"name":"Philippine Post Office"},"Q29018351":{"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Agustin Sumuroy historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Agustin Sumuroy","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Palapag, Samar. Namuno sa pag-aalsa laban sa mga Espanyol bilang protesta sa sapilitang paggawa at mga pang-aabuso sa mga katutubo, 1 Hunyo 1649. Lumaganap ito sa lalawigan ng Cebu, Masbate at Bohol sa Kabisayaan; Iligan, Hilangang Mindanao at Zamboanga sa Mindanao; at Sorsogon at Albay sa Luzon. Ito ay kinikilala bilang unang malawakang paghihimagsik ng mga katutubo. Pinagkanulo at pinaslang ng sariling mga tauhan, 1650.</p>","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Agustin Sumuroy","locPhoto":null,"date":"2008","lon":125.11505,"address":"Palapag, Northern Samar","lat":12.54553},"Q28928184":{"lat":6.90359,"address":"Zamboanga City","lon":122.07713,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Bank of the Philippine Islands Zamboanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Bank of the Philippine Islands Zamboanga","subtitle":null}}},"locDesc":null,"date":"2012"},"Q39773891":{"date":"2008-09-02","locPhoto":null,"name":"Philippine Dental Association","locDesc":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Philippine Dental Association","inscription":"","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"PDA marker, Makati.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"Ayala Avenue Extension cor. Kamagong Street, Makati, Metro Manila","lat":14.56372,"lon":121.01586},"Q40176326":{"lat":14.44511,"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","lon":120.90661,"date":"1998-06-12","name":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence","locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pook ng Pagpapahayag ng Kasarinlan ng Pilipinas historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook ng Pagpapahayag ng Kasarinlan ng Pilipinas","inscription":""}},"en":{"photo":{"file":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>On June 12, 1898, Philippine independence was proclaimed from the center window of the original house of the family of General Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy, President of the First Philippine Republic and leader of the revolution against Spain and America. Through the reading of the Acta de la Proclamacion de la Independencia del Pueblo Filipino by Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista. During this occasion, the Philippine flag made in Hongkong by Doña Marcela Marino de Agoncillo was officially unfurled as the band of San Francisco de Malabon proudly played the Marcha Nacional Filipina (now the Philippine National anthem) composed by Julian Felipe.</p><p>This historical marker is installed by the grateful Filipino people in observance of the centennial of the proclamation of Philippine independence. Unveiled by His Excellency President Fidel Valdez Ramos on June 12, 1998.</p>","title":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence","subtitle":null}}}},"Q37807353":{"lat":14.58426,"address":"Asilo de San Vicente de Paul, 1148 United Nations Avenue, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.99046,"date":"1935","locPhoto":{"file":"Asilo de San Vicente de Paul main gate.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"name":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul","locDesc":"The historical marker is located above the eastern pedestrian gate.","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul","inscription":"<p>The ground and college were donated to the Sisters of Charity for the education of poor girls by Sor Asuncion Ventura, a native of Pampanga, herself a Sister of Charity. The institution was inaugurated on July 26, 1885 and gained great distinction for the design and excellence of its embroidery and needlework.</p>","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul historical marker.jpg"}}}}}